Climbing Mount Improbable is a 1996 popular science book by Richard Dawkins .
Everything I 'm Cracked Up to Be is a book by Boston , Massachusetts - based musician Jen Trynin .
Against Simon ( also known as `` Reply to Simon '' ) is a speech by Lysias , one of the `` Canon of Ten '' Attic orators .
The Tenth Brother ( Slovene : Deseti brat ) written by the Slovene writer Josip Jurčič , is the first novel in Slovene .
Knowledge and Decisions is a non - fiction book by American economist Thomas Sowell .
The Vision of Don Roderick is a poem by Sir Walter Scott , published in 1811 .
`` The Horror at Oakdeene '' is a 1977 horror novella by Brian Lumley .
The Great Gilly Hopkins is a realistic children 's novel by Katherine Paterson .
Tafsir Numani is an exegesis on the Quran attributed to Muhammad Ibn Ibrahim Ibn Jafar al - Numani .
The Apollo of Bellac ( French title : L'Apollon de Bellac or L'Apollon de Marsac ) is a comedic one - act play written in 1942 by French dramatist Jean Giraudoux .
Tiger by the Tail and Other Science Fiction Stories is the first collection of short works by Alan E. Nourse , issued in hardcover by publisher Donald McKay in 1961 .
Speakeasy Dollhouse is a series of immersive plays based on Cynthia von Buhler 's investigations of mysterious deaths in site - specific , historic locations .
The Fall of Colossus is a science fiction novel written in 1974 by the British author Dennis Feltham Jones .
Cube Route is the twenty - seventh book of the Xanth series by Piers Anthony .
The Gangster 's Life ( published in 2011 ) is a Canadian crime fiction novel by Ranj Dhaliwal .
Abarat ( 2002 ) is a fantasy novel written and illustrated by Clive Barker , the first in Barker 's The Books of Abarat series .
The Difference Engine ( 1990 ) is an alternate history novel by William Gibson and Bruce Sterling .
Reincarnation in Venice is a science fiction or mystery book written by popular fiction author Max Simon Ehrlich and published in 1979 by Simon & Schuster in New York .
Captain Underpants and the Big , Bad Battle of the Bionic Booger Boy are the sixth and seventh books in the Captain Underpants series by Dav Pilkey .
The Fever Crumb Series is the title of a series of novels written by British author , Philip Reeve , and is the prequel series to his critically acclaimed Mortal Engines Quartet .
The War Against Cliché ( 2001 ) is an anthology of essays , book reviews and literary criticism from the British author Martin Amis .
The Brown Hand , a well - noted short - story by Sir Arthur Conan Doyle , was first published in The Strand Magazine , May 1899 .
The Plot to Save Socrates is a time travel novel by Paul Levinson , first published in 2006 .
Colloquies is one of the many works of the `` Prince of Christian Humanists '' , Desiderius Erasmus .
Dragonkeeper is a children 's fantasy novel by Australian author Carole Wilkinson .
Iola Leroy or , Shadows Uplifted , an 1892 novel by Frances Harper , is one of the first novels published by an African - American woman .
The Great Divorce is a theological dream vision by C. S. Lewis , in which he reflects on the Christian conception of Heaven and Hell .
The Sweetest Dream is a 2001 novel by British Nobel Prize in Literature - winner Doris Lessing .
The History Man ( 1975 ) is a campus novel by the British author Malcolm Bradbury set in 1972 in the fictional seaside town of Watermouth in the South of England .
Raska på , Alfons Åberg is a 1975 children 's book by Gunilla Bergström .
The Parrot 's Theorem is a French novel written by Denis Guedj and published in 1998 .
The Nature and Origins of Mass Opinion is a 1992 non - fiction book by political scientist John Zaller that examines the processes by which individuals form and express political opinions and the implications this has for public opinion research .
Ricky Rapper ( Finnish : Risto Räppääjä ) is a main character in a series of children 's fantasy books and comic strips by Finnish writers Sinikka Nopola and Tiina Nopola .
A Handful of Fog is a 1979 novel by Sami Michael , published by Am Oved publishing house .
Revolt on Alpha C is a juvenile science fiction novel written by Robert Silverberg and published by Crowell in 1955 .
The name Webster 's Dictionary may refer to any of the line of dictionaries first developed by Noah Webster in the early nineteenth century and numerous unrelated dictionaries that adopted Webster 's name just to share his prestige .
The Pelican Brief is a legal - suspense thriller written by John Grisham in 1992 .
Down These Mean Streets is a memoir by Piri Thomas , a Latino of Puerto Rican and Cuban descent who grew up in El Barrio ( aka Spanish Harlem ) , a section of Harlem that has a large Puerto Rican population .
Oru Desathinte Katha ( English : The Story of a Locale ) is a Malayalam novel written by S. K. Pottekkatt in 1971 .
The Legend of Sigurd and Gudrún is a book containing two narrative poems and related texts composed by J. R. R. Tolkien .
The History of Tom Jones , a Foundling , often known simply as Tom Jones , is a comic novel by the English playwright and novelist Henry Fielding .
The Glove of Darth Vader is the first book of the Jedi Prince series by Paul Davids and Hollace Davids , and was released in June 1992 .
The Woofits is a series of children 's books written in the 1980s by the British television and radio personality Michael Parkinson , best known for his TV chat shows .
La Tumba ( The Grave ) is a 1964 controversial novel written in Spanish by José Agustín .
Duck for President is a children 's book written by Doreen Cronin and illustrated by Betsy Lewin .
Tre kom tilbake ( English : Three Returned ) is an autobiographical book from 1946 written by Norwegian pilot Jens Müller on his war experiences during World War II . The book centers particularly on his participation in the 1944 mass escape from the German prisoner - of - war camp Stalag Luft III .
Neuróticos on line is a book by Argentine author Luis Pescetti .
Chronicles of the Canongate is a collection of stories by Sir Walter Scott , published in 1827 and 1828 .
Radio Golf is a play by American playwright , August Wilson , the final installment in his ten - part series , The Pittsburgh Cycle .
`` Lycidas '' ( /ˈlɪsɪdəs/ ) is a poem by John Milton , written in 1637 as a pastoral elegy .
Instincts of the Herd in Peace and War is the title of an influential book by English surgeon Wilfred Trotter , published in 1916 .
Antiquities of the Jews ( Greek : Ἰουδαϊκὴ ἀρχαιολογία , Ioudaikē archaiologia ; Latin : Antiquitates Judaicae ) , also Judean Antiquities ( see Ioudaios ) , is a 20-volume historiographical work composed by the Jewish historian Flavius Josephus in the 13th year of the reign of Roman emperor Flavius Domitian which was around AD 93 or 94 .
A Cavern of Black Ice is the first book in the Sword of Shadows fantasy series by J. V. Jones .
The Beginning Was the End is a 1971 pseudo - scientific book written by Oscar Kiss Maerth that claims that humankind evolved from cannibalistic apes .
I Know This Much Is True is a novel by Wally Lamb , published in 1998 .
`` The Prowler in the City at the Edge of the World '' is a short story by Harlan Ellison , first published in his 1967 anthology , Dangerous Visions .
`` Retreat Syndrome '' is a 1965 short story written by Philip K. Dick .
The Crows of Pearblossom is a children 's book written by Aldous Huxley , the English novelist , essayist and critic .
Illustrissimi or `` To the Illustrious Ones '' , is a collection of letters written by Pope John Paul I when he was Patriarch of Venice .
Raja Gidh ( Urdu : راجه گدھ‎ ) by Bano Qudsia is an Urdu novel .
Book of My Mother ( French : Le Livre de ma mère ) is a 1954 memoir by the Swiss writer Albert Cohen .
The Methods of Ethics is a book on utilitarianism first published in 1874 by the English philosopher Henry Sidgwick .
Three Days Before the Shooting ... is the title of the edited manuscript of Ralph Ellison 's never - finished second novel .
The Knight of Sainte - Hermine ( published in France in 2005 under the title Le Chevalier de Sainte - Hermine ) is an unfinished historical novel by Alexandre Dumas , believed to be Dumas ' last major work .
Captain Salt in Oz ( 1936 ) is the thirtieth in the series of Oz novels created by L. Frank Baum and his successors , and the sixteenth written by Ruth Plumly Thompson .
Dirty Sexy Politics is a 2010 political memoir written by Meghan McCain , the daughter of Republican Senator John McCain , about the 2008 United States presidential election .
The Vampire Chronicles is a series of novels by Anne Rice that revolves around the fictional character Lestat de Lioncourt , a French nobleman turned into a vampire in the 18th century .
The Children of the Abbey is a novel by the Irish romantic novelist Regina Maria Roche .
Profiles in Folly is a historical book written by Alan Axelrod which is composed of many other true stories within the book itself , beginning with the Trojan War in `` The Decision To Let Danger In '' , and ending with Hurricane Katrina in `` The Decision to Stop Short of Leadership '' .
The Curse of Lono is a book by Hunter S. Thompson describing his experiences in Hawaii in 1980 .
The View from Serendip is a collection of essays and anecdotes by Arthur C. Clarke , first published in 1977 .
Yo - Yo Boing ! is a Spanglish novel by Puerto Rican poet and novelist Giannina Braschi .
Uncle Remus is the fictional title character and narrator of a collection of African - American folktales adapted and compiled by Joel Chandler Harris , published in book form in 1881 .
Hubertus Bigend is a fictional character appearing in the later novels of science fiction and literary author William Gibson .
Malory Towers is a series of six novels by English children 's author Enid Blyton , featuring the fictional Cornish seaside boarding school of the same name .
Arkham 's Masters of Horror is an anthology of fantasy and horror stories edited by Peter Ruber .
The Giaour is a poem by Lord Byron first published in 1813 by T. Davison and the first in the series of his Oriental romances .
What Really Happened to the Class of ' 65 ? is a 1976 non - fiction book by Michael Medved and David Wallechinsky .
Soul River ( Collection of twelve Novellas and short stories ) is a 2012 Georgian book by author Miho Mosulishvili .
Under the Deodars ( published 1888 ) is a collection of short stories by Rudyard Kipling .
No Turn Unstoned is a collection of `` the worst theatrical reviews in history '' compiled by the actress Dame Diana Rigg .
`` Death and the Compass '' ( original Spanish title : `` La muerte y la brújula '' ) is a short story by Argentine writer and poet Jorge Luis Borges ( 1899 - -1986 ) .
Our Man in Beirut is the debut book by British - Lebanese author and publisher Nasri Atallah .
The Glass Bees ( German : Gläserne Bienen ) is a 1957 science fiction novel written by German author Ernst Jünger .
Supernatural Horror in Literature is a long essay by the horror writer H. P. Lovecraft surveying the topic of horror fiction .
Bellarion the Fortunate , published in 1926 , is an historical novel by Rafael Sabatini .
Going Wrong ( 1990 ) is a novel by English crime writer Ruth Rendell .
`` Time Enough '' ( alternate title : `` Enough Time '' ) is a science fiction short story written by Damon Knight .
Fossil Hunter is a novel written by Canadian science fiction author Robert J. Sawyer .
Tearing Down the Wall of Sound is a biography of record producer Phil Spector , written by Mick Brown and published in 2008 .
Anandamath ( Bengali : আনন্দমঠ Anondomôţh ; first English publication title : The Abbey of Bliss ) is a Bengali novel , written by Bankim Chandra Chattopadhyay and published in 1882 .
Why Orwell Matters , released in the UK as Orwell 's Victory , is a book - length biographical essay by Christopher Hitchens .
A Tract of Time is an antiwar novel from 1966 by Smith Hempstone , that covers the time period about 1960 , when there was an attempted coup of South Vietnamese President Ngo Dinh Diem .
Jack , or The Submission ( French : Jacques ou la soumission ) is an absurdist play by Eugène Ionesco , the first of two about Jack and his family ( the second being The Future is in Eggs ) , all of whom are named after Jack ( Father - Jack , Mother Jack , etc . ) .
Kings of the Water is the third novel from writer Mark Behr , published in November 2009 .
Time Out of Joint is a dystopian novel by Philip K. Dick , first published in novel form in the United States in 1959 .
Mr. Monk Goes to Germany is the sixth novel by Lee Goldberg to be based on the television series Monk .
Loser Takes All is a 1955 novella by British author Graham Greene .
The Pit of the Serpent is a Sailor Steve Costigan short story by Robert E. Howard .
The Fifty Year Sword is a novella written by Mark Z. Danielewski .
Scattered Poems is a collection of spontaneous poetry by Jack Kerouac .
Poetics of Cinema 2 ( 2007 ) is the second of two volumes of film theory by Chilean filmmaker Raúl Ruiz .
The World Set Free is a novel written in 1913 and published in 1914 by H. G. Wells .
Ninth Key is a novel written by Meg Cabot for teenagers and young adults .
A Fairly Honourable Defeat is a novel by the British writer and philosopher Iris Murdoch .
The Brave Cowboy ( 1956 ) was Edward Abbey 's second published novel ( as detailed in James M. Cahalan 's biography of Abbey ) .
Eve 's Diary is a comic short story by Mark Twain .
America in the King Years is a three - volume history of Dr. Martin Luther King , Jr. and the Civil Rights Movement by Taylor Branch , which he wrote between 1982 and 2006 .
Nightmare Abbey was a novella by Thomas Love Peacock , and his third long work of fiction to be published .
The Color Purple is a 1982 epistolary novel by American author Alice Walker that won the 1983 Pulitzer Prize for Fiction and the National Book Award for Fiction .
John Locke 's Of the Conduct of the Understanding describes how to think clearly and rationally .
The Door to December is a novel by author Dean Koontz , released in 1985 .
Epistulae ex Ponto ( Letters from the Black Sea ) is a work of Ovid , in four books .
The Power of Darkness ( Russian : Власть тьмы , Vlast ' t'my ) is a five - act drama by Leo Tolstoy .
Schindler 's Ark ( released in America as Schindler 's List ) is a Booker Prize - winning novel published in 1982 by Australian novelist Thomas Keneally , which was later adapted into the highly successful movie Schindler 's List directed by Steven Spielberg .
Know Ye Not Agincourt ? by Leslie Barringer is a historical novel set in fifteenth century England and France .
The Fall of the Pagoda ( Chinese : 雷峰塔 ; pinyin : Léi Fēng Tǎ ) is a semi - autobiographical novel written by Eileen Chang .
Think and Grow Rich was written in 1937 by Napoleon Hill and is a personal development and self - improvement book .
Gösta Berling 's Saga ( Swedish : Gösta Berlings saga ) is the debut novel of Swedish author Selma Lagerlöf , published in 1891 .
New Writings in SF 30 is an anthology of science fiction short stories edited by Kenneth Bulmer , the ninth volume of nine he oversaw in the New Writings in SF series in succession to the series ' originator , John Carnell , and the final volume in the series .
The Economic Consequences of the Peace ( 1919 ) is a book written and published by John Maynard Keynes .
Puck of Pook 's Hill is a fantasy book by Rudyard Kipling , published in 1906 , containing a series of short stories set in different periods of English history .
Defensio pro Populo Anglicano is a Latin polemic by John Milton , published in 1651 .
Midworld ( 1975 ) is a science fiction novel written by Alan Dean Foster .
The Dark Lord of Derkholm , simply Dark Lord of Derkholm in the United States , is a fantasy novel by the British author Diana Wynne Jones , published autumn 1998 in both the U.K. and the U.S. It won the 1999 Mythopoeic Fantasy Award for Children 's Literature .
Spike and Suzy ( British title ) or Willy and Wanda ( American title ; Dutch : Suske en Wiske , French : Bob et Bobette ) is a Belgian comics series created by the comics author Willy Vandersteen .
Toward a Meaningful Life is a book authored by Chabad Hasidic writer Simon Jacobson .
Entre Marx y una Mujer Desnuda ( Between Marx and a Nude Woman ) is a 1976 novel written by the Ecuadorian poet Jorge Enrique Adoum .
The Heart of Jade ( Spanish : El corazón de piedra verde ) is a novel by Spanish author Salvador de Madariaga , first published in 1942 .
The Unconquerable is a short story traditionally credited to Thomas Hardy , though its true authorship has long been the subject of controversy .
The King 's Orchard is an historical novel by the American writer Agnes Sligh Turnbull ( 1888 - -1982 ) based upon the life of James O'Hara ( 1752?--1819 ) , an American industrialist .
Essay on the Origin of Languages ( French : Essai sur l'origine des langues ) is an essay by Jean - Jacques Rousseau published posthumously in 1781 .
On the Chersonese is a political oration delivered by the Athenian statesman and orator Demosthenes in 341 BC . A short time later Demosthenes delivered one of his most famous speeches , the Third Philippic .
Petals of Blood is a novel written by Ngũgĩ wa Thiong'o and first published in 1977 .
The ABC of Communism ( Russian : Азбука коммунизма Azbuka Kommunizma ) is a book written by Nikolai Bukharin and Yevgeni Preobrazhensky in 1919 , during the Russian Civil War .
A Brief History of Chinese Fiction ( Chinese : 中國小說史略 ; pinyin : Zhongguo xiaoshuo shilue ) is a book written by Lu Xun as a survey of traditional Chinese fiction .
Vampire Lesbians of Sodom is a satirical play written by Charles Busch .
The Canon of Judo is a book was originally published in 1956 , and written by Kodokan 10th dan , Kyuzo Mifune ( 1883 - 1965 ) .
Fire Angels is a 1998 fantasy fiction novel by Jane Routley .
4.50 from Paddington is a detective fiction novel by Agatha Christie , first published in November 1957 .
Introducing Kafka , also known as R. Crumb 's Kafka , is an illustrated biography of Franz Kafka by David Zane Mairowitz and Robert Crumb .
Terra Obscura is a 2003 comic book miniseries spin off from Alan Moore 's Tom Strong series .
Kiss the Dust is a book written by Elizabeth Laird on the conflicts between the Kurds and the then Saddam Hussein - led Iraqis .
The Golden Egg ( Dutch : Het Gouden Ei ) , published as The Vanishing in English - speaking countries , is a psychological thriller novella written by Dutch author Tim Krabbé , first published in 1984 .
Riverworld is a fictional planet and the setting for a series of science fiction books written by Philip José Farmer ( 1918 - 2009 ) .
Joris of the Rock is a fantasy novel by Leslie Barringer , the second book in his three volume Neustrian Cycle .
A Place of Safety is a crime novel by Caroline Graham , the sixth in her popular Chief Inspector Barnaby series , which has been adapted into the successful ITV drama Midsomer Murders .
The Book of the Damned was the first published nonfiction work of the author Charles Fort ( first edition 1919 ) .
La Symphonie pastorale is a French novella written by André Gide published in 1919 .
Death and the Dervish ( Serbo - Croatian : Derviš i smrt/Дервиш и смрт ) is a novel by Yugoslav / Bosnian writer Meša Selimović , published in 1966 .
Life After God is a collection of short stories by Douglas Coupland , published in 1994 .
Meta 4 is a five - issue comic book series by Ted McKeever published by ShadowLine .
Elsewhen ( 1941 ) is a novella by Robert A. Heinlein , concerning time travel and parallel universes .
The Sunbird is a 1972 novel by Wilbur Smith about an archeological dig . The novel was a favourite of Smith 's , who claimed it was heavily influenced by H. Rider Haggard .
Den svenska sångboken ( `` The Swedish Song book '' ) is a 1997 Swedish book with 331 songs ( in 2003 a new version with 365 songs was published ) , written by Anders Palm and Johan Stenström .
Letters to a Young Mathematician ( ISBN 0 - 465 - 08231 - 9 ) is a 2006 book by Ian Stewart , and is part of Basic Books ' Art of Mentoring series .
The Foundling and Other Tales of Prydain is a collection of short high fantasy stories for children by Lloyd Alexander .
Times Without Number is a time travel / alternate history novel by John Brunner .
Glass People is the second novel written by American writer Gail Godwin .
Hunches in Bunches is a children 's book written and illustrated by Theodor Geisel under the pen name Dr. Seuss and published by Random House on October 12 , 1982 .
The Three Robbers is a children 's book by Tomi Ungerer .
Practical Ethics ( 1979 ; second edition 1993 ; third edition 2011 ) is an introduction to applied ethics by bioethical philosopher Peter Singer .
Transmetropolitan is a cyberpunk , transhumanist comic book series written by Warren Ellis , co - created and designed by Darick Robertson , and published by DC Comics .
Hard Freeze is a 2002 novel by American writer Dan Simmons .
I , the Jury is the 1947 debut novel of American crime - fiction writer Mickey Spillane , the first work to feature private investigator Mike Hammer .
A Bird in the House , first published in 1970 , is a short story sequence written by Margaret Laurence .
The Armourer 's House is a children 's historical novel by Rosemary Sutcliff and first published in 1951 .
Buckdancer 's Choice ( 1965 ) is a collection of poems by James Dickey .
The Cluetrain Manifesto is a work of business literature collaboratively authored by Rick Levine , Christopher Locke , Doc Searls , and David Weinberger .
A Dialogue Concerning Oratorical Partitions , also called De Partitione Oratoria Dialogus , Partitiones Oratoriae , or De Partitionbus Oratoriae , translated to be `` On the subdivisions of oratory '' -- is a rhetorical treatise , written by Cicero .
The Baroque Cycle is a series of novels by American writer Neal Stephenson .
Historias de los señores Moc y Poc is an Argentine children 's book by Luis Pescetti .
Lebensrückblick ( English : Looking Back ) is an autobiographical text written by Lou Andreas - Salomé and compiled by Ernst Pfeiffer , who edited and published Andreas - Salomé 's literary remains in 1951 , some 15 years after her death .
Elvis and Gladys ( ISBN 1 - 57806 - 634 - 4 ) is a biography of rock and roll singer Elvis Presley by author and film industry insider , Elaine Dundy .
The Million Dollar Kick is a children 's story written by American novelist Dan Gutman , another installment in the Million Dollar book series , following The Million Dollar Shot .
Natural Law and Natural Rights is a 1980 book by philosopher John Finnis , a seminal contribution to the philosophy of law and a restatement of natural law doctrine .
The Lake of Dead Languages is the 2002 mystery debut novel of writer Carol Goodman , who won the Hammett Prize for her 2004 book The Seduction of Water .
Fugitive Pieces is a novel by Canadian poet Anne Michaels .
My Dateless Diary is a collection of autobiographical essays by R. K. Narayan published in 1960 .
Dragonvarld is a trilogy of fantasy novels by Margaret Weis .
Due to Lack of Interest , Tomorrow Has Been Canceled is a 1969 book by Irene Kampen , an account of her return to school at the University of Wisconsin--
`` The Ugly Duckling '' ( Danish : Den grimme ælling ) is a literary fairy tale by Danish poet and author Hans Christian Andersen ( 1805 -- 1875 ) .
In One Person is a 2012 novel by American author John Irving , his 13th since 1968 .
Broučci is a classic children 's book by Jan Karafiát published in the Czech language in the early 1870s .
Historia Regum Britanniae ( English : The History of the Kings of Britain ) is a pseudohistorical account of British history , written around 1136 by Geoffrey of Monmouth .
Tamerlane and Other Poems is the first published work by American writer Edgar Allan Poe .
25 Images of a Man 's Passion , or The Passion of a Man is the first wordless novel by Flemish artist Frans Masereel ( 1889 - -1972 ) , first published in 1918 under the French title 25 images de la passion d'un homme .
The Calcutta Chromosome is a 1995 English - language novel by Indian author Amitav Ghosh .
India 's Global Powerhouses - How They Are Taking on the World is a 2009 book by Nirmalya Kumar .
The Kandy - Kolored Tangerine - Flake Streamline Baby is the title of Tom Wolfe 's first collected book of essays , published in 1965 .
Dynastia Miziołków is a children 's novel written by Joanna Olech , illustrated originally by Magda Jasny , and published by Egmont Media Group .
The Seventh Secret is a 1986 novel by Irving Wallace using an alternate history of Adolf Hitler having survived World War II .
Moominvalley in November ( Swedish : Sent i november , ' Late in November ' ; Finnish : Muumilaakson marraskuu ) is the ninth and final book in the Moomin series by Finnish author Tove Jansson , and was first published in both her native Swedish and English in 1971 .
A Woman in Berlin ( German : Eine Frau in Berlin ) ( 1959/2003 ) is an anonymous memoir by a German woman ( reputed in 2003 to be journalist Marta Hillers ) .
Memoirs of a Woman of Pleasure ( popularly known as Fanny Hill ) is an erotic novel by English novelist John Cleland first published in London in 1748 .
The Poor Bride ( Бедная невеста , Bednaya nevesta ) is a play by Alexander Ostrovsky , written in 1851 and first published in the No.4 , 1852 issue of Moskvityanin magazine .
The Crystal Singer , or Crystal Singer in the U.S. , is a young - adult , science fiction novel by Anne McCaffrey , first published by Severn House in 1982 .
The Gathas ( /ˈɡɑːtəz , -tɑːz/ ; Avestan : Gāθās ) are 17 hymns believed to have been composed by Zarathusthra ( Zoroaster ) himself .
Let Us Compare Mythologies is the first poetry book by Canadian poet and songwriter Leonard Cohen .
If Rock & Roll Were a Machine is a young adult novel written by Terry Davis .
Drapier 's Letters is the collective name for a series of seven pamphlets written between 1724 and 1725 by the Dean of St Patrick 's Cathedral in Dublin , Jonathan Swift , to arouse public opinion in Ireland against the imposition of a privately minted copper coinage that Swift believed to be of inferior quality .
The Pot of Gold and Other Stories is a collection of children 's short stories written by American author Mary Eleanor Wilkins Freeman .
The costumed crime - fighter the Blonde Phantom , created by writer - editor Stan Lee and artist Syd Shores , debuted in All Select Comics # 11 ( Fall 1946 ) .
Balthasar 's Odyssey ( French : Le Périple de Baldassare ) is a 2000 novel by Amin Maalouf set in 17th century Europe and the Levant .
The Boy Who Knew Everything is the sequel to Victoria Forester 's first book The Girl Who Could Fly .
The House of Hunger ( ISBN 0 - 435 - 90986-X ) ( 1979 ) is a short story collection by the late Dambudzo Marechera .
The Only Investment Guide You 'll Ever Need is a book written by Andrew Tobias and concerns commonsense rules that the ordinary saver can live by .
Flesh and Fire is the first book in The Vineart War trilogy by Laura Anne Gilman .
Let 's All Kill Constance is a 2002 mystery novel by Ray Bradbury .
Fire Bringer is a young adult fantasy novel by David Clement - Davies published in 1999 , in the United Kingdom and 2000 , in the United States .
Jefferson and His Time is a six - volume biography of US President Thomas Jefferson by American historian Dumas Malone , published between 1948 and 1981 .
A Beautiful Place to Die is the debut novel of award - winning filmmaker Malla Nunn .
Mulata de tal is a novel by Nobel Prize - winning novelist Miguel Ángel Asturias .
The Real Inspector Hound is a short , one - act play by Tom Stoppard .
Through Wolf 's Eyes is the first book in the Firekeeper Saga by Jane Lindskold .
En ménage ( English : Married Life ) is a novel by the French writer Joris - Karl Huysmans , first published in February 1881 by Charpentier .
Asrar al - Tawhid fi Maghamat al - Sheikh Abusa'id ( Arabic : اسرار التوحید فی مقامات ابو سعید‎ , `` The Mysteries of Unification '' ) is a work of 12th century Persian literature about the Sufi mystic Abū - Sa'īd Abul - Khayr .
On further improving party ideological work was the March 8 , 1981 concluding speech by Kim Jong - il at the National Meeting of Party Propagandists in North Korea .
Ciudades Desiertas ( Empty cities or Deserted Cities ) is a 1982 novel written in Spanish by José Agustín .
Four Children and It is a novel by author Jacqueline Wilson based on the 1902 book Five Children and It by Edith Nesbit .
The Secret Circle is a supernatural , young - adult series of books created by L. J. Smith .
Interlopers is a 2001 science fiction novel by Alan Dean Foster .
We Have Never Been Modern is a 1991 book by Bruno Latour , originally published in French as Nous n'avons jamais été modernes :
Nõiduse õpilane ( English : Sorcerer 's Apprentice / Sorcerer 's Disciple / Student of Witchcraft ) is a novel by Estonian author Karl Ristikivi .
The Metamorphoses ( Latin : Metamorphōseōn librī : `` Books of Transformations '' ) is a Latin narrative poem by the Roman poet Ovid , considered his magnum opus .
`` Stickfighting Days '' is Sierra Leonean writer Olufemi Terry 's second short story and the winner of the 2010 Caine Prize for African Writing .
A Little Raw on Monday Mornings is an adult novel published by popular young adult author Robert Cormier in 1963 .
Post - Scarcity Anarchism is a collection of essays by Murray Bookchin , first published in 1971 by Ramparts Press .
Ravished Armenia ( full title : Ravished Armenia : The Story of Aurora Mardiganian , the Christian Girl , Who Survived the Great Massacres ) is a book written in 1918 by Arshaluys ( Aurora ) Mardiganian about her experiences in the Armenian Genocide .
Gens des nuages is a travel journal written in French by French Nobel laureate J. M. G. Le Clézio and his wife Jémia .
The Meaning of Night is the debut novel by author Michael Cox .
The Looking Glass War ( 1965 ) , by John le Carré , is a spy novel about a British Intelligence agency known as ' The Department ' and its attempts to infiltrate an agent into East Germany .
Pseudomonarchia Daemonum , or Hierarchy of Demons first appears as an Appendix to Johann Weyer 's De praestigiis daemonum ( 1577 ) .
Marooned on Eden ( 1993 ) , is a science fiction novel by Robert L. Forward , collaborating with his wife , Martha Dodson Forward .
The Animal Family is a 1965 children 's novel by American poet and critic Randall Jarrell and illustrated by noted children 's book illustrator Maurice Sendak .
King Leary is a novel by Canadian humorist Paul Quarrington , published in 1987 by Doubleday Canada .
Henry VI , Part 3 ( often written as 3 Henry VI ) is a history play by William Shakespeare believed to have been written in 1591 , and set during the lifetime of King Henry VI of England .
Culture and Society is a book published in 1958 by Welsh progressive writer Raymond Williams , exploring how the notion of culture developed in the West , especially Great Britain , from the eighteenth through the twentieth centuries .
The Christmas Mystery ( Norwegian : Julemysteriet ) is a Norwegian novel for children by Jostein Gaarder .
Dandelion Wine is a 1957 novel by Ray Bradbury , taking place in the summer of 1928 in the fictional town of Green Town , Illinois , based upon Bradbury 's childhood home of Waukegan , Illinois .
`` Miss Brill '' is a short story by Katherine Mansfield ( 1888 - -1923 ) .
The Wanderings of Oisin ( /oʊˈʃiːn/ oh - SHEEN ) is an epic poem published by William Butler Yeats in 1889 in the book The Wanderings of Oisin and Other Poems .
Shikari in Galveston is an alternate history short story written by S. M. Stirling .
American Adulterer is a 2009 fictional novel written by Jed Mercurio focusing on the life of 35th President of the United States John Fitzgerald Kennedy , it mainly talks about his extramarital affairs , political ambitions , various physical ailments and his relationship with his wife Jackie and his children .
R.U.R. is a 1920 science fiction play by the Czech writer Karel Čapek .
Master of Space and Time is a 1984 novel by Rudy Rucker that centers on an inventor , Harry Gerber , who discovers a way to create his own tailor - made universe .
The 35th of May , or Conrad 's Ride to the South Seas ( Der 35 . Mai oder Konrad reitet in die Südsee in German , its original language ) is a novel by Erich Kästner , first published in 1931 .
Morgoth 's Ring ( 1993 ) is the tenth volume of Christopher Tolkien 's 12-volume series The History of Middle - earth in which he analyses the unpublished manuscripts of his father J. R. R. Tolkien .
Celia en el colegio ( `` Celia at the school '' or `` Celia at school '' ) is the second in the series of Celia novels by Elena Fortún , first published in 1932 according to records .
`` Tidal Moon '' is a science fiction short story by Stanley G. Weinbaum and Helen Weinbaum that first appeared in the December 1938 issue of Thrilling Wonder Stories and was reprinted in the collection Interplanetary Odysseys ( 2006 ) .
So You 've Been Publicly Shamed ( 2015 ) is a book by British journalist Jon Ronson about online shaming and its historical antecedents .
Ultimate Daredevil and Elektra is a four - issue comic book mini - series published by Marvel Comics written by Greg Rucka with art by Salvador Larroca .
Host and Guest is an epic poem by the Georgian poet , writer and philosopher Vazha - Pshavela .
The Complete Guide to Middle - earth : from The Hobbit to The Silmarillion is a reference book for the fictional universe of J. R. R. Tolkien 's Middle - earth , compiled and edited by Robert Foster .
The Candy Shop War ( 2007 ) is a children 's fantasy novel by Brandon Mull about magic candy .
The 13 Clocks is a fantasy tale written by James Thurber in 1950 , while he was completing one of his other novels .
The Serpentwar Saga is a series of fantasy novels set in Midkemia by the author Raymond E. Feist .
The Price to Pay is a 2012 autobiography by Joseph Fadelle , an Iraqi man who converted from Islam to Roman Catholicism .
Champions of Mystara was designed by Ann Dupuis and Bruce A. Heard , and published by TSR as a boxed set containing eight vehicle blueprints and four poster maps .
The Devil 's Wind is a historical novel by Manohar Malgonkar that tells the story of Nana Saheb , the heir of the last Peshwa of the Maratha Confederacy , who played a leading role in the Indian Mutiny .
The Goalie 's Anxiety at the Penalty Kick ( German : Die Angst des Tormanns beim Elfmeter ) is a 1970 novel by the Austrian writer Peter Handke .
Evolution and the Theory of Games is a 1982 book by the British evolutionary biologist John Maynard Smith on evolutionary game theory .
The Little White Car , is a novel by British author Dan Rhodes , published under the pen name Danuta de Rhodes in 2004 by Canongate and has been translated into 12 languages .
The Emerald City of Oz is the sixth of L. Frank Baum 's fourteen Land of Oz books .
`` Who 's Afraid of Peer Review ? '' is an article written by Science correspondent John Bohannon that describes his investigation of peer review among fee - charging open access journals .
`` The Doom that Came to Sarnath '' ( 1920 ) is an early short story by H. P. Lovecraft .
The Black Tulip is a historical novel written by Alexandre Dumas , père .
Georg Karck ( 11 June 1911 in Segeberg -- 3 July 1944 , in Normandy ) was a Sturmbannführer ( Major ) in the Waffen - SS who was awarded the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Max Simon ( 6 January 1899 -- 1 February 1961 ) was a German SS - Gruppenführer ( lieutenant General ) und Generalleutnant der Waffen - SS during World War II , who was awarded the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves .
Francis Octavius Grenfell , VC ( 4 September 1880 -- 24 May 1915 ) was an English recipient of the Victoria Cross .
Nico Pelamonia ( born 16 March 1940 ) is an Indonesian actor turned film director who won the Citra Award for Best Director in 1976 for his film Semalam di Malaysia .
Mikhail Gluzman ( born 5 September 1967 , in Kiev , Ukraine ) is a Ukrainian - Australian chess International Master ( IM ) and an experienced chess coach .

Lieutenant - Commander Edgar Christopher Cookson VC DSO ( 13 December 1883 -- 28 September 1915 ) was an English recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .

WISE J035000.32−565830.2 ( designation abbreviated to WISE 0350−5658 ) is a brown dwarf of spectral class Y1 , located in constellation Reticulum , the nearest known star / brown dwarf in this constellation .
Larsen Inlet is an inlet , formerly ice - filled , 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) long in a north -- south direction and 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) wide , between Cape Longing and Cape Sobral along the east coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Mount Persenk ( Bulgarian : връх Персенк , `` Vrah Persenk '' \'vr&h per-'senk\ ) is the rounded , ice - covered peak rising to 1700 m in Lovech Heights on Nordenskjöld Coast in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Mount Campleman is a flat - topped , projecting - type mountain in Antarctica , 1,970 metres ( 6,460 ft ) high , along the north edge of Mackin Table , 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) west of Stout Spur , in the Patuxent Range , Pensacola Mountains .
Shmidt Subglacial Basin is a large subglacial basin situated southward of Knox Coast in East Antarctica .
The Fokker Rocks ( 78 ° 4′S 155 ° 10′W ) are rock outcrops just south of Mount Schlossbach in the Rockefeller Mountains of Edward VII Peninsula , Antarctica .
Guard Glacier ( 71 ° 1′S 62 ° 10′W ) is a broad tributary glacier that drains east along the southern margin of Parmelee Massif to join Murrish Glacier , on the east side of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Grivitsa Ridge ( Bulgarian : Гривишки хребет , `` Grivishki Hrebet '' \'gri - vish - ki ' hre - bet\ ) is the mostly ice - free ridge extending 6.4 km in northwest - southeast direction , 3 km wide and rising to 1100 m ( Batkun Peak ) on Nordenskjöld Coast in Graham Land , Antarctica .
The Chan Rocks ( 72 ° 45′S 160 ° 30′E ) are a group of rocks along an ice bluff situated 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) southeast of Miller Butte in the Outback Nunataks , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Frolov Ridge ( 70 ° 45′S 162 ° 9′E ) is a prominent ridge about 11 nautical miles ( 20 km ) long , trending north -- south , located just west of Arruiz Glacier in the Bowers Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Branscomb Glacier ( 78 ° 32′S 86 ° 05′W ) is an Antarctic glacier , 9.5 km ( 6 mi ) long , flowing west from the north - west side of Vinson Massif ( the highest point in Antarctica ) into Nimitz Glacier , in the Sentinel Range of the Ellsworth Mountains .
Fasettfjellet ( 72 ° 33′S 2 ° 59′W ) is a mountain , 2,425 metres ( 7,960 ft ) high , standing north of Flogstallen in the northeast part of the Borg Massif in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Nichols Snowfield ( 69 ° 25′S 71 ° 5′W ) is a snowfield , 22 nautical miles ( 41 km ) long and 8 nautical miles ( 15 km ) wide , bounded by the Rouen Mountains and Elgar Uplands to the east and Lassus Mountains to the west , in the north part of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Divotino Point ( Bulgarian : нос Дивотино , `` Nos Divotino '' \'nos di-'vo - ti - no\ ) is a sharp , low ice - free point on the southeast coast of Alfatar Peninsula on Robert Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica projecting 200 m into Mitchell Cove .
Kvinge Peninsula ( 71 ° 10′S 61 ° 10′W ) is a snow - covered peninsula at the north side of Palmer Inlet terminating in Cape Bryant , on the east coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
The Monteath Hills ( 72 ° 6′S 166 ° 30′E ) are a group of mountains in the Victory Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica , bounded by Jutland Glacier , Midway Glacier , Pearl Harbor Glacier , and Plata Glacier .
Tilt Rock ( 70 ° 27′S 68 ° 44′W ) is an isolated rock peak , rising to about 670 m , situated 2 nautical miles ( 3.7 km ) inland from the George VI Ice Shelf of George VI Sound and 2 nautical miles ( 3.7 km ) northeast of Block Mountain in eastern Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Inferno Ridge ( 79 ° 26′S 84 ° 13′W ) is a narrow ridge , 8 miles ( 13 km ) long , rising between Schneider Glacier and Rennell Glacier in the Heritage Range , Antarctica .
Predel Point ( Bulgarian : нос Предел , `` Nos Predel '' \'nos pre-'del\ ) is a point on the northwest coast of Fournier Bay in Anvers Island in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica separating the termini of Rhesus Glacier to the north and Thamyris Glacier 4 km to the south .
The Melvold Nunataks ( 72 ° 51′S 74 ° 9′E ) are a group of small nunataks located 14 nautical miles ( 26 km ) west of Mount Harding in the Grove Mountains of Antarctica .
Benin ( /bᵻˈniːn/ bǝ - NEEN or /bᵻˈnɪn/ bǝ - NIN ; French : Bénin ) , officially the Republic of Benin ( French : République du Bénin ) and formerly Dahomey , is a country in West Africa .
Berwick Glacier ( 84 ° 36′S 165 ° 45′E ) is a tributary glacier , 14 nautical miles ( 26 km ) long , flowing southeast between the Marshall Mountains and the Adams Mountains to enter Beardmore Glacier at Willey Point in Antarctica .
Whistle Pass ( 69 ° 47′S 70 ° 25′W ) is a snow pass at about 1,050 m at the head of Sullivan Glacier in north Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Mercator Ice Piedmont ( 68 ° 37′S 65 ° 30′W ) is a gently - sloping ice piedmont at the head of Mobiloil Inlet , formed by the confluence of the Gibbs , Lammers , Cole and Weyerhaeuser Glaciers in eastern Graham Land , Antarctica .
Mount Lanzerotti ( 74 ° 50′S 71 ° 33′W ) is the northernmost of the Sky - Hi Nunataks , rising to about 1,550 metres ( 5,100 ft ) in Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Cape Jeremy is a cape marking the east side of the north entrance to George VI Sound and the west end of a line dividing Graham Land and Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Heezen Glacier ( 72 ° 45′S 61 ° 18′W ) is a glacier flowing northeast from the eastern portion of the Wegener Range and entering Violante Inlet east of Mount Reynolds , on the Black Coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Rush Glacier ( 64 ° 23′S 62 ° 37′W ) is a glacier in Antarctica .
Hjort Massif is a salient mountain rising to about 1,000 metres ( 3,300 ft ) at the northeast end of the Wilson Mountains , on the south side of Hilton Inlet , on the Bowman Coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Hoggestabben Butte ( 72 ° 0′S 3 ° 58′E ) is a prominent butte , 2,410 metres ( 7,900 ft ) high , standing 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) north of Mount Hochlin and being its highest northern outlier , in the Mühlig - Hofmann Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Cape MacKay ( 77 ° 42′S 168 ° 31′E ) is an ice - covered cape which forms the southeastern extremity of Ross Island , Antarctica .
Mount Athelstan ( 70 ° 10′S 69 ° 16′W ) is a prominent , partly ice - covered mountain , 1,615 metres ( 5,300 ft ) high , at the north side of Trench Glacier on a spur which extends east from Douglas Range on the east coast of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Grant Island is an ice - covered island , 37 kilometres ( 20 nmi ) long and 19 kilometres ( 10 nmi ) wide , lying 9 km ( 5 nmi ) east of the smaller Shepard Island off the coast of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Mount Frustum ( 73 ° 23′S 162 ° 55′E ) is a large pyramidal shaped table mountain , 3,100 metres ( 10,200 ft ) high , standing between Mount Fazio and Scarab Peak in the southern part of Tobin Mesa , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Galdhøpiggen is the highest mountain in Norway , Scandinavia and Northern Europe , at 2,469 m ( 8,100 ft ) above sea level .
Giants Cirque ( 67 ° 17′S 67 ° 17′W ) is a large cirque on the west side of the Tyndall Mountains which opens to the southwest to Vallot Glacier , on Arrowsmith Peninsula , Loubet Coast , Antarctica .
Mount Garan ( 67 ° 32′S 98 ° 56′E ) is a mountain marked by a cluster of small peaks , rising 9 nautical miles ( 17 km ) southwest of Mount Strathcona near the head of Denman Glacier in Antarctica .
The Gervaize Rocks are a group of rocks about 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) north - northeast of Cape Ducorps , Trinity Peninsula , Antarctica .
Killer Nunatak ( 71 ° 54′S 160 ° 28′E ) is a granite nunatak , 2,080 metres ( 6,820 ft ) high , near the center of the Emlen Peaks , 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) northwest of Mount Phelan , in the Usarp Mountains of Antarctica .
Mount Gran ( 76 ° 59′S 160 ° 58′E ) is a large flat - topped mountain , 2,235 metres ( 7,330 ft ) high , standing at the north side of Mackay Glacier and immediately west of Gran Glacier in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Laseron Islands are a chain of small ice - capped and rocky islands lying 6 kilometres ( 3 nmi ) east of Cape Denison in Commonwealth Bay , Antarctica .
Kappa Island ( 64 ° 19′S 63 ° 0′W ) is an island , nearly 0.5 nautical miles ( 0.9 km ) long , lying immediately south of Beta Island and close east of the Theta Islands in the Melchior Islands of the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Etar Snowfield ( Bulgarian : Ледник Етър \'led - nik ' e - t&r\ , Lednik Etar ) is a roughly crescent - shaped snowfield on western Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica situated west of Urdoviza , Medven and Berkovitsa Glaciers , and northwest of Verila Glacier .
Mount Gray ( 75 ° 1′S 136 ° 42′W ) is a rounded , ice - worn mountain on the southwest part of the McDonald Heights in coastal Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Kitchen Point is a rocky point at the east end of Tirizis Island off the east coast of Robert Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Mount Harding is the largest mountain in the Grove Mountains of Antarctica , in the south - central part of the range and about 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) west of Gale Escarpment .
Mount Lagally ( 67 ° 9′S 67 ° 6′W ) is a mountain standing 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) south of Vanni Peak in the Dorsey Mountains , on Arrowsmith Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Crohn Massif ( 70 ° 27′S 64 ° 57′E ) is a large , domed massif in Antarctica , 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) west of Mount Kirkby in the Porthos Range , Prince Charles Mountains .
Fourier Island is a small rocky island 100 metres ( 0.05 nmi ) off the coast and 1.4 kilometres ( 0.75 nmi ) east - northeast of Cape Mousse , Antarctica .
The Admiralty Mountains ( alternatively Admiralty Range ) is a large group of high mountains and individually named ranges and ridges in northeastern Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mount Hazlett ( 72 ° 6′S 167 ° 35′E ) is a mountain , 2,080 metres ( 6,820 ft ) high , at the south side of the mouth of Montecchi Glacier where the latter enters Tucker Glacier , in the Victory Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Alph Lake lies at the foot of Ward Valley on the north - west side of Koettlitz Glacier , Scott Coast , Antarctica .
The Homerun Range ( 71 ° 40′S 166 ° 35′E ) is a northwest - trending mountain range , 45 km ( 28 mi ) long and 3 to 11 km ( 2 to 7 mi ) wide , located east of Everett Range at the heads of the Ebbe and Tucker glaciers in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mount Weininger is a large , mainly ice - free mountain in Antarctica , 1,970 m , standing at the north extremity of Mackin Table , to which it is joined by a short ridge , in the Patuxent Range , Pensacola Mountains .
Long Glacier ( 72 ° 30′S 96 ° 43′W ) is a glacier about 8 nautical miles ( 15 km ) long in the southeastern part of Thurston Island , Antarctica .
Vanuatu is not a member of Interpol , along with 11 other countries mainly in Oceania .
The Dent de Crolles hosts one of the most complex and vast cave systems in Europe .
The Shackleton Range is a mountain range in Antarctica .
Renaud Island is an ice - covered island , 40 km ( 25 mi ) long and from 6.4 to 16.1 km ( 4 to 10 mi ) ( average 11.3 km ( 7 mi ) ) wide , lying between the Pitt Islands and Rabot Island in the Biscoe Islands of Antarctica .
Horteriset Dome ( 72 ° 5′S 12 ° 22′E ) is a broad ice covered hill about 13 nautical miles ( 24 km ) west of the southern part of the Weyprecht Mountains in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Metropolitan France ( French : France métropolitaine or la Métropole ) is the part of France located in Europe .
Pliska Ridge ( Vrah Pliska \'vr&h ' pli - ska\ ) is a three - peaked ridge rising to 667 m in eastern Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
The Central Masson Range ( 67 ° 50′S 62 ° 52′E ) is the central segment of the three parts of the Masson Range , Antarctica .
The Inland Forts ( 77 ° 37′S 161 ° 8′E ) are a line of peaks extending between Northwest Mountain and Saint Pauls Mountain , in the Asgard Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Radnevo Peak ( Vrah Radnevo \'vr&h ' rad - ne - vo\ ) is a peak of elevation 481 m forming the southwest extremity of Vidin Heights on Varna Peninsula on Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Jezek Glacier ( 77 ° 59′S 162 ° 13′E ) is a glacier on the southeast side of Platform Spur , flowing northeast into Emmanuel Glacier in the Royal Society Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Hulbe Glacier ( 73 ° 47′S 125 ° 55′W ) is a glacier about 10 nautical miles ( 20 km ) long draining the north side of Siple Island , Antarctica .
Debren Pass ( Bulgarian : проход Дебрен , `` Prohod Debren '' \'pro - hod ' de - bren\ ) is the ice - covered saddle of elevation 2100 m on the east side of Sentinel Range in Ellsworth Mountains , Antarctica separating Mount Jumper from the side ridge descending via Evans Peak .
Kubbestolen Peak ( 71 ° 47′S 8 ° 54′E ) is a bare rock peak , 2,070 metres ( 6,800 ft ) high , at the northwest end of Vinten - Johansen Ridge in the Kurze Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Wildwind Glacier is a substantial mountain glacier in Antarctica , 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) wide , which flows southward into Alatna Valley , draining both the Staten Island Heights and Mount Razorback areas , in the Convoy Range , Victoria Land .
Walkabout Rocks is a prominent rock exposure along the coast at the north - eastern extremity of the Vestfold Hills , about 0.5 nautical miles ( 0.9 km ; 0.6 mi ) south of the Wyatt Earp Islands of Princess Elizabeth Land , Antarctica .
Morennaya Hill ( 66 ° 34′S 93 ° 0′E ) is a hill rising to 40 metres ( 130 ft ) , standing 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) southwest of Mabus Point on the coast of Antarctica .
Case Island is a roughly circular ice - covered island , 22 kilometres ( 12 nmi ) in diameter , lying off the coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Hansen Glacier ( 78 ° 21′S 84 ° 33′W ) is a tributary glacier 10 nautical miles ( 19 km ) long , flowing northeast from Mount Tuck between Veregava Ridge and Doyran Heights to join Dater Glacier west of Dickey Peak , in the Sentinel Range of the Ellsworth Mountains in Antarctica .
Phillips Nunatak ( 84 ° 45′S 62 ° 35′W ) is a nunatak along the edge of a small ice escarpment 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) north of Mount Wanous in the Patuxent Range , Pensacola Mountains , Queen Elizabeth Land , Antarctica .
Goldsmith Glacier is a glacier flowing west - northwest through the Theron Mountains of Antarctica , 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) south of Tailend Nunatak .
Durrance Inlet ( 73 ° 50′S 16 ° 30′W ) is an ice - filled inlet 10 nautical miles ( 19 km ) north of Veststraumen Glacier along the Princess Martha Coast of Antarctica .
Yugoslavia ( Serbo - Croatian , Macedonian , Slovene : Jugoslavija , Југославија ) was a country in Southeast Europe during most of the 20th century .
The Chilean South Pole Expedition ( 2004 - -2005 ) was a Chilean expedition to Antarctica organized by the Chilean Navy , Centro de Estudios Científicos and INACh .
Mercer Ice Stream ( 84 ° 50′S 145 ° 00′W ) , formerly Ice Stream A , flows west to Gould Coast to the south of Whillans Ice Stream , Antarctica .
Holmes Block ( 78 ° 13′S 161 ° 35′E ) is a blocklike bluff , rising to 1,855 metres ( 6,090 ft ) at the west side of Ruecroft Glacier , 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) west of Cooke Bluff , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mulock Glacier in Antarctica is a heavily crevassed glacier which flows into the Ross Ice Shelf 40 km south of the Skelton Glacier in the Ross Dependency , Antarctica .
Jones Valley ( 83 ° 55′S 56 ° 50′W ) is a snow - covered valley between West Prongs and Elliott Ridge in the southern Neptune Range of the Pensacola Mountains in Antarctica .
The Haller Rocks ( 64 ° 4′S 62 ° 6′W ) are a small group of rocks in the eastern part of Bouquet Bay , lying 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) northwest of the southwest end of Liège Island , in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
The Monk Islands ( 60 ° 40′S 45 ° 55′W ) are a group of very small islands and rocks lying 1.5 nautical miles ( 3 km ) south of Meier Point , off the south coast of Coronation Island in the South Orkney Islands off Antarctica .
Hale Glacier ( 72 ° 13′S 100 ° 33′W ) is a glacier about 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) long , located just east of Mount Simpson on Thurston Island , Antarctica , and flowing southwest to the Abbot Ice Shelf in Peacock Sound .
Duseberg Buttress ( 65 ° 10′S 64 ° 6′W ) is a conspicuous rocky cone , 500 metres ( 1,600 ft ) high , standing at the southwest side of Mount Scott on the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Holman Dome ( 66 ° 27′S 98 ° 54′E ) is a dome - shaped nunatak 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) southwest of Watson Bluff , on the east side of David Island , Antarctica .
Burris Nunatak ( 71 ° 47′S 160 ° 27′E ) is a nunatak near the northern extremity of the Emlen Peaks , 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) northwest of Mount Cox , in the Usarp Mountains , a major mountain range situated in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Lind Ridge ( 75 ° 48′S 132 ° 33′W ) is a ridge forming the south wall of Coleman Glacier in the Ames Range of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Linwood Peak ( 77 ° 36′S 147 ° 13′W ) is an isolated peak on Hershey Ridge , standing 14 nautical miles ( 26 km ) west of Mount Ronne in the Ford Ranges of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Hogback Hill ( 77 ° 29′S 163 ° 37′E ) is a rounded mountain , 735 metres ( 2,410 ft ) high , rising just north of Hjorth Hill and 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) west of Cape Bernacchi , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mount Bowles is an ice - covered mountain 822 metres ( 2,697 ft ) high , the summit of Bowles Ridge in the central part of eastern Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Iratais Point ( Nos Iratais \'nos i - ra-'ta - is\ ) is a point forming both the south extremity and the vertex of the V - shaped Desolation Island situated in the entrance to Hero Bay , Livingston Island , Antarctica .
Holdfast Point ( 66 ° 48′S 66 ° 36′W ) is both the northeast side of the entrance to Lallemand Fjord and the northwest side of the entrance to Chepra Cove on Pernik Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica , situated about 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) southwest of Cape Rey .
Sheldon Glacier ( 67 ° 30′S 68 ° 23′W ) is a glacier flowing southeast from Mount Mangin into Ryder Bay , Adelaide Island , Antarctica .
Martin Reef ( 67 ° 34′S 65 ° 31′E ) is a reef awash , lying 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) north of the coast of Antarctica and slightly west of Cape Fletcher .
Jøkulfallet ( 71 ° 51′S 6 ° 42′E ) is a steep ice slope on the north side of Jokulkyrkja Mountain in the Mühlig - Hofmann Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Chernoochene Glacier ( Bulgarian : ледник Черноочене , `` Lednik Chernoochene '' \'led - nik che - rno-'o - che - ne\ ) is the 5 km long and 2 km wide glacier on Oscar II Coast , Graham Land in Antarctica situated in the southeast foothills of Forbidden Plateau south of Jorum Glacier and northeast of Crane Glacier .
Anderson Pyramid ( 70 ° 46′S 159 ° 56′E ) is a distinctive pyramidal peak , the southernmost member of the Bigler Nunataks , in the Usarp Mountains of Antarctica .
Mount Lockhart ( 76 ° 28′S 145 ° 6′W ) is a prominent northerly projection from the main massif of the Fosdick Mountains 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) northeast of Mount Avers , in the Ford Ranges of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Madey Ridge ( 83 ° 28′S 55 ° 50′W ) is a ridge trending northwest from Mount Moffat along the north side of Berquist Ridge in the Neptune Range , Pensacola Mountains , Antarctica .
Dinsmoor Glacier ( 64 ° 22′S 59 ° 59′W ) is a glacier flowing from the south edge of Detroit Plateau on Nordenskjöld Coast , Graham Land in Antarctica .
Mount Heitō ( 69 ° 16′S 39 ° 49′E ) is a flat - topped mountain 495 metres ( 1,620 ft ) high on the southeast end of the Langhovde Hills in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Cape Ryugu ( 67 ° 58′S 44 ° 2′E ) is a rocky cape 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) northeast of Rakuda Rock on the coast of Queen Maud Land in Antarctica .

The Wagendrift Dam is a multi - arch type dam located on the Bushman 's River , upstream of Estcourt , in the KwaZulu - Natal province of South Africa .

Asa Kasher ( Hebrew : אסא כשר‎ , born on June 6 , 1940 ) is an Israeli philosopher and linguist working as a Professor at Tel Aviv University and at Shalem College , Israel .
Issa Makhlouf ( Arabic:عيسى مخلوف ) is a Lebanese writer and poet who lives in Paris where he is currently the News Director at Radio Orient .
Ebenezer Elliott ( 17 March 1781 -- 1 December 1849 ) was an English poet , known as the Corn Law rhymer for his leading the fight to repeal the Corn Laws which were causing hardship and starvation among the poor .
Eldrid Lunden ( born 5 October 1940 ) is a Norwegian poet , and Norway 's first professor in creative writing , at Telemark University College .
Jatindra Nath Duwara ( Assamese : যতীন্দ্ৰনাথ দুৱৰা ; 1892 - 1964 ) was a notable poet of the Jonaki era of Assamese literature .

Thomas Hoepker ( German : Thomas Höpker ; 10 June 1936 in Munich , Germany ) is a German photographer and member of Magnum Photos known for stylish color photo features .
Hope Emily Allen ( 1883 - -1960 ) , an independent medieval scholar , is best known for her research on the 14th - century English mystic Richard Rolle and for her discovery of the Book of Margery Kempe .
René Mioch ( born in Waalwijk , March 6 , 1959 ) is a Dutch journalist and presenter for radio and television .
Charles - Gaspard Delestre - Poirson , known as Delestre - Poirson ( 22 August 1790 , Paris - 19 November 1859 ) was a French playwright and theatre director .

Jean Benoît - Lévy ( 1888 - -1959 ) was a French film director and producer .
Simón de Colonia ( died 1511 ) was a Spanish architect and sculptor , son of architect Juan de Colonia and father of architect and sculptor Francisco de Colonia .
Antonio José `` Kitín '' Muñoz y Valcárcel or Kitín Muñoz ( born 19 November 1958 in Sidi Ifni , Morocco ) is a Spanish navigator , scientist , and sociological explorer .
Olga Benário Prestes ( February 12 , 1908 -- April 23 , 1942 ) was a German - Brazilian communist militant .
Giovanni Antonio Amedeo Plana ( 6 November 1781 -- 20 January 1864 ) was an Italian astronomer and mathematician .
Jean - Baptiste - Édouard Gélineau ( 23 December 1828 -- 2 March 1906 ) was the French physician who first described narcolepsy .
Christian Friedrich Heinrich Wimmer ( October 30 , 1803 -- March 12 , 1868 ) was a German botanist and educator who was a native of Breslau .
Menashe Kadishman ( Hebrew : מנשה קדישמן ; August 21 , 1932 - May 8 , 2015 ) was an Israeli sculptor and painter .
Siméon Denis Poisson ( French : ( si.me.ɔ̃ də.ni pwa.sɔ̃ ) ; 21 June 1781 -- 25 April 1840 ) , was a French mathematician , geometer , and physicist .
Nalapat Narayana Menon ( October 7 , 1887 -- October 31 , 1954 ) was a Malayalam language author from Kerala state , South India .
Alfons Mitgutsch , known as Ali Mitgutsch , born August 21 , 1935 in Munich , Germany , is a German author of picture books and professional advertising Illustrator .
Juan Manuel Sánchez Gordillo ( Spanish : ( ˈxwan maˈnwel ˈsantʃeθ ɣoɾˈðiʎo ) ; born 5 February 1952 ) is a Spanish politician , labour leader and history school teacher .
Louis Constant Wairy ( 1778 - -1845 ) was valet to Napoleon , Emperor of the French .

Vera Molnár ( born 1924 ) is a French media artist of Hungarian origin .
Stanislas de Guaita ( 6 April 1861 , Tarquimpol , Moselle -- 19 December 1897 , Tarquimpol ) was a French poet based in Paris , an expert on esotericism and European mysticism , and an active member of the Rosicrucian Order .
John Frith ( 1503 -- 4 July 1533 ) was an English Protestant priest , writer , and martyr .
Mitch Murray ( born Lionel Michael Stitcher , 30 January 1940 , Hove , Sussex , England ) , is an English songwriter , record producer and author .
Eduard Limonov ( Russian : Эдуа́рд Лимо́нов , real name Eduard Veniaminovich Savenko , Russian : Эдуа́рд Вениами́нович Саве́нко ; born 2 February 1943 ) is a Russian writer and political dissident .
Sir James Pennethorne ( 4 June 1801 -- 1 September 1871 ) was a 19th - century English architect and planner , particularly associated with buildings and parks in central London .
Julie Zenatti , ( born 5 February 1981 ) , is a French singer celebrity .
Alonso de Olmedo y Ormeño ( 1626 - -1682 ) was a Spanish actor , playwright and writer .

Pál Vastagh ( born 23 September 1946 ) is a Hungarian politician and jurist , who served as Minister of Justice between 1994 and 1998 .
Jean Favier ( 2 April 1932 -- 12 August 2014 ) was a French historian , who specialized in Medieval history .
Jean - Louis Forain ( 23 October 1852 -- 11 July 1931 ) was a French Impressionist painter , lithographer , watercolorist and etcher .

Antoine Halley ( 1593 -- 3 June 1675 ) was a French professor and poet .

Sister ( Spanish : Sor ) Tadea de San Joaquín ( c. 1750 - 1827 ) was a Carmelite nun and writer of the Chilean Colonial period who wrote Catholic confessional ballad about the great flood of 1783 .

Martín de Ursúa ( or Urzúa ) y Arizmendi ( February 22 , 1653 -- February 4 , 1715 ) , Count of Lizárraga and of Castillo , was a Spanish Basque conquistador in Central America during the late colonial period of New Spain .

Pierre Allain ( 7 January 1904 -- 19 December 2000 ) was a French alpinist who began climbing in the 1920s .

Charles - Émile Reynaud ( 8 December 1844 -- 9 January 1918 ) was a French inventor , responsible for the first projected animated cartoons .
Baltasar de Mendoza y Sandoval ( 1653 -- 1727 ) was a Spanish bishop who headed the Spanish Inquisition from 1699 to 1704 .

WFYE is an Adult Contemporary formatted broadcast radio station licensed to Glade Spring , Virginia , serving Smyth and Washington counties in Virginia .
WCDE is a Christian Contemporary formatted broadcast radio station licensed to Elkins , West Virginia , serving Metro Elkins , and airing programming from the Air 1 radio network .
CFGP - FM is a Canadian radio station that broadcasts an active rock format operating on the frequency 97.7 FM in Grande Prairie , Alberta .
KEPC ( 89.7 FM ) is a radio station licensed to Colorado Springs , Colorado , USA , the station serves the Colorado college area .
WZEE ( 104.1 MHz FM ) is a radio station licensed to Madison , Wisconsin and serving South Central Wisconsin .
KF - KQ is a Top 40 ( CHR ) formatted simulcast broadcasting on two radio stations , with WWKF licensed to Fulton , Kentucky ( serving Union City , Tennessee ) and WAKQ licensed to Paris , Tennessee .
CKOM is a radio station in Saskatoon , Saskatchewan broadcasting at 650 kHz on the AM band .
KCQQ is an FM radio station licensed to Davenport , Iowa with a classic rock format .

The Mangfall is a left tributary of the River Inn in Upper Bavaria and 58 km long .
The Polenz is the right - hand , smaller headstream of the Lachsbach in the German state of Saxony .
It passes through the reservoir of Sant Ponç ( 25 hm3 ) between Olius and Clariana de Cardener ( Solsonès ) , Cardona , Súria and Manresa ( Bages ) before joining the Llobregat from the left at Castellgalí ( Bages ) .
The Kentucky River is a tributary of the Ohio River , 260 miles ( 418 km ) long , in the U.S. Commonwealth of Kentucky .
The Kechika River , also historically known as Black 's River , is a tributary of the Liard River , located in northern British Columbia , Canada .
Sullivans Creek flows generally south - west , through a small channel within a much larger older gully system in its upper reaches ; and through a series of urban sealed stormwater channels in its middle reaches ; before reaching the grounds of the Australian National University , towards its confluence with the Molonglo River near Acton .
The Tipitapa River ( Río Tipitapa ) is a short river in Nicaragua that connects Lake Managua to Lake Nicaragua .

The Esmeraldas River is a river in northwestern Ecuador that flows into the Pacific Ocean at the city of Esmeraldas .
Malka River ( Russian : Малка ) , also known as Balyksu River ( Russian : Балыксу ) , is a river in Kabardino - Balkaria in Russia , which forms the northwest part of the Terek River basin .
The Klondike River is a tributary of the Yukon River in Canada that gave its name to the Klondike Gold Rush .
The Kenogami River is a river in the James Bay drainage basin in Thunder Bay and Cochrane districts in Northern Ontario , Canada , which flows north from Long Lake near Longlac to empty into the Albany River .
The Roe River runs between Giant Springs and the Missouri River in Great Falls , Montana , United States .
The Gallatin River is a tributary of the Missouri River , approximately 120 mi ( 193 km long ) , in the U.S. states of Wyoming and Montana .
Nedlouc River is a tributary of the south bank of the Leaf River whose waters flow East and throw themselves on the west coast of Ungava Bay .
The Shasta River is a tributary of the Klamath River , approximately 58 miles ( 93 km ) long , in northern California in the United States .
The Duckmaloi River rises on the western slopes of the Great Dividing Range east of Shooters Hill , and flows generally to the north by east , where it forms its confluence with the Fish River near Oberon ; dropping 265 metres ( 869 ft ) over the course of its 27 kilometres ( 17 mi ) length .
The Chutine River , originally named the Clearwater River , is a major right tributary of the Stikine River in northwestern British Columbia , Canada .
The Republican River joins the Smoky Hill River at Junction City , Kansas to form the Kansas River .
Zamantı River is a river in Central Anatolia , Turkey , crossing Kayseri Province in practically its whole course to join Seyhan River further south , of which it is the western , the longest and the most important tributary .
The Drino or Drinos ( Albanian : Drino , Greek : Δρίνος ) is a river in southern Albania and northwestern Greece , tributary of the Vjosë .
Ithaca Creek is a waterway in the Enoggera Creek catchment , in the western suburbs of Brisbane , Queensland , Australia .

Alain Carignon , born on February 23 , 1949 in Vizille ( Isère ) , is a conservative French politician .
Anne of Brittany ( Breton : Anna ; 25 January 1477 -- 9 January 1514 ) was a French queen who reigned as Duchess of Brittany from 1488 until her death .
Jean - Remy de Chestret ( Liège 1739 - Paris 1809 ) was a Burgomaster of Liège in 1784 and 1789 and one of the chiefs of the Liège Revolution and later a member of the French Sénat conservateur .
Séverin Faust ( December 29 , 1872 , Paris -- April 23 , 1945 ) , better known by his pseudonym Camille Mauclair , was a French poet , novelist , biographer , travel writer , and art critic .
Lazare Escarguel ( 1816 - 1893 ) was a French politician and newspaper editor .
Léon Battu was a French dramatist , born 1829 in Paris , where he died on 22 November 1857 .
Jean Desmarets , Sieur de Saint - Sorlin ( 1595 -- 28 October 1676 ) was a French writer and dramatist .
Laurent Ruquier ( born 24 February 1963 in Le Havre ) is a French television and radio host , producer , and satirical comedian .
Oliver Krischer ( born 26 July 1969 in Zülpich , Germany ) is a German Green politician and member of the German Bundestag .
Frédéric Andréi ( born 23 October 1959 ) is a French actor and director .
Karine Berger ( born 11 March 1973 ) is a French politician , member of the French National Assembly representing Hautes - Alpes .
Ferdinand Flocon ( 1 November 1800 -- 15 March 1866 ) was a French journalist and politician who was one of the founding members of the Provisional Government at the start of the French Second Republic in 1848 .
Ercole Baldini ( born 26 January 1933 ) is a retired Italian cyclist .
Michael Jan de Goeje ( August 13 , 1836 -- May 17 , 1909 ) was a Dutch orientalist .
Gesine Meißner ( or Meissner ; born 22 February 1952 in Uelzen ) is a German politician for the Free Democratic Party .
Mélanie Fazi ( born 29 November 1976 ) is a French novelist and translator specialising in fantasy fiction .
Françoise d'Eaubonne ( 12 March 1920 in Paris - 3 August 2005 in Paris ) was a French feminist , who introduced the term ecofeminism ( écologie - féminisme , éco - féminisme or écoféminisme ) in 1974 .
Tim Krabbé ( born 13 April 1943 ) is a Dutch journalist and novelist .
Jean - Paul Pigasse ( born 1939 ) is a Brazzaville - based French journalist and media proprietor .
Thomas - Simon Gueullette ( 2 June 1683 - 2 December 1766 ) was a French lawyer , playwright , scholar and man of letters , who also wrote fairy tales and works on the theatre itself .
Victor Méric is the pseudonym of Henri Coudon ( 10 May 1876 -- 10 October 1933 ) , a French journalist and libertarian author .
Olympe de Gouges ( French pronunciation : ​(olɛ̃p də ɡuʒ ) ; 7 May 1748 -- 3 November 1793 ) , born Marie Gouze , was a French playwright and political activist whose feminist and abolitionist writings reached a large audience .
Barbara Laage ( 30 July 1920 -- 21 May 1988 ) was a French film actress who flourished in the 1950s .
Véronique Augereau ( born 25 May 1957 ) is a French actress who is notably active in dubbing .
Marc Fumaroli ( born 10 June 1932 in Marseille ) , is a French historian and essayist .
Elisabeth Christine of Brunswick - Wolfenbüttel ( 28 August 1691 -- 21 December 1750 ) was Princess of Brunswick - Wolfenbüttel , Holy Roman Empress , German Queen , Queen of Bohemia and Hungary ; and Archduchess of Austria by her marriage to Emperor Charles VI .
Wilhelm Amsinck Burchard - Motz ( born 4 July 1878 in Hamburg , died 13 January 1963 in Hamburg ) was a German lawyer and national - liberal politician .
Samuel Dirksz van Hoogstraten ( 2 August 1627 , Dordrecht -- 19 October 1678 , Dordrecht ) was a Dutch painter of the Golden Age , who was also a poet and author on art theory .
Alexis Kanner ( 2 May 1942 in Bagnères - de - Luchon , France - 13 December 2003 in London , England ) was a French - born English actor , most notable for appearing in the ground - breaking TV series The Prisoner .
Dom Hans van der Laan ( 29 December 1904 -- 19 August 1991 ) was a Dutch Benedictine monk and architect .
Francisque Sarcey ( 8 October 1827 -- 16 May 1899 ) was a French journalist and dramatic critic .
Henri Desgrange ( 31 January 1865 , Paris -- 16 August 1940 ) was a French bicycle racer and sports journalist .
Raphaël Onana , born on 14 July 1919 , was a Free French soldier of Cameroonian origin , naturalised French .
Carl Wirths ( December 10 , 1897 -- June 16 , 1955 in Wuppertal ) was a German politician of the Free Democratic Party ( FDP ) .
Fred Vargas is the pseudonym of the French historian , archaeologist and writer Frédérique Audoin - Rouzeau ( born 7 June 1957 in Paris ) .
Markus Meckel ( b. August 18 , 1952 ) is a German theologian and politician .
Philippe Jullian ( real name : Philippe Simounet ; 11 July 1919 -- 25 September 1977 ) was a French illustrator , art historian , biographer , aesthete , novelist and dandy .
Robert de Boron ( also spelled in the manuscripts `` Bouron '' , `` Beron '' ) was a French poet of the late 12th and early 13th centuries who is most notable as the author of the poems Joseph d'Arimathe and Merlin .
Léa Hélène Seydoux - Fornier de Clausonne ( born 1 July 1985 ) , known as Léa Seydoux , is a French actress .
Marcel Pagnol ( French pronunciation : ​(maʁsɛl paɲɔl ) ; 28 February 1895 -- 18 April 1974 ) was a French novelist , playwright , and filmmaker .
Ulrich von Hutten ( 21 April 1488 -- 29 August 1523 ) was a German scholar , poet , satirist and reformer .
Mac Lesggy ( born Olivier Lesgourges , 1 August 1962 ) is a French agricultural engineer , television presenter and producer .
Bert - Jan Lindeman ( born 16 June 1989 ) is a Dutch professional road bicycle racer who rides for UCI Continental Team Rabobank Development Team .
Maria Matray ( July 14 , 1907 -- October 30 , 1993 ) was a German screenwriter and film actress .
Yves de Bayser ( 1920 - -1999 ) was a French poet , essayist , and translator .
Isaac Leib Peretz ( Polish : Icchok Lejbusz Perec , Hebrew : יצחק־לייבוש פרץ ) ( May 18 , 1852 -- 3 April 1915 ) , also sometimes written Yitskhok Leybush Peretz , best known as I. L. Peretz , was a Yiddish language author and playwright from Poland .
Anneke Brassinga ( born 20 August 1948 in Schaarsbergen , Gelderland ) is a Dutch writer and translator .
Ryoichi Taguchi ( born 1 December 1986 ) is a Japanese professional boxer .
Kuno Fischer , born Ernst Kuno Berthold Fischer ( 23 July 1824 -- 5 July 1907 ) , was a German philosopher , a historian of philosophy and a critic .
Geymond Vital ( 1897 - -1987 ) was a French film , stage and television actor .
Lucien Callamand born Lucien Marie Pascal Eugène Callamand ( April 1 , 1888 in Marseille - December 3 , 1968 in Nice , Alpes - Maritimes ) was one of the earliest French film actors whose career transcended 6 decades of French cinema .
Melanie Oßwald ( born 1 June 1976 in Nuremberg ) is a German politician and a former member of the Bundestag with the CSU .
Jeannette Vermeersch ( born Julie Marie Vermeersch ; 26 November 1910 -- 5 November 2001 ) was a French politician .
Claude - Philibert Barthelot , comte de Rambuteau ( French pronunciation : ​(klod filibɛːʁ baʁtəlo kɔ̃t də ʁɑ̃byto ) ) ( Mâcon , 9 November 1781 -- Château de Rambuteau , 11 April 1869 ) was a French senior official of the first half of the 19th century .
Rémi Laurent ( 12 October 1957 , Suresnes -- 14 November 1989 , Paris ) was a French actor , best known for playing the son Laurent in La Cage aux Folles .
Sylvie Testud ( born 17 January 1971 ) is a French actress , writer and film director , whose film career began in 1991 .
Andrés Oppenheimer ( born in 1951 in Buenos Aires , Argentina ) is the editor and syndicated foreign affairs columnist with The Miami Herald , anchor of `` Oppenheimer Presenta '' on CNN En Español , and author of seven books , several of which have been published in English , Spanish , Portuguese and Japanese .
Guillaume Imbert de Boudeaux ( 1744 - 19 May 1803 ) was a French man of letters .
Léo Malet ( 7 March 1909 -- 3 March 1996 ) was a French crime novelist and surrealist .
Jules Bazile , known as Jules Guesde ( 11 November 1845 -- 28 July 1922 ) was a French socialist journalist and politician .
Marcel Hansenne ( January 24 , 1917 -- March 22 , 2002 ) was a French middle distance runner , who won the bronze medal at the 1948 Summer Olympics in London over 800 m in a time of 1:49.8 min . The race was won by Mal Whitfield .
Hannelore Kraft ( née Külzhammer ; born 12 June 1961 ) is a German politician .
Albert Dess ( born 17 April 1947 in Röckersbühl ) is a German politician and member of the European Parliament for Bavaria with the Christian Social Union in Bavaria , part of the European People 's Party and sits on the European Parliament 's Committee on Agriculture and Rural Development .
Jan van de Velde the Elder ( 1568 , Antwerp -- 1623 , Haarlem ) , was a Dutch calligrapher , writing teacher , and engraver .
Ottmar Schreiner ( 21 February 1946 -- 6 April 2013 ) was a German lawyer and left - wing politician .
Josef Stefan ( Slovene : Jožef Stefan ) ( 24 March 1835 -- 7 January 1893 ) was an ethnic Carinthian Slovene physicist , mathematician , and poet of the Austrian Empire .
Balthazar Baro ( 1596 - -1650 ) was a French poet , playwright and romance - writer .
Alessandro Mercuri is a French - Italian author and director , born in 1973 .
Jacques Weber ( born 23 August 1949 ) is a French actor , director and writer .
Françoise Chandernagor is a French writer , born 15 June 1945 .
Henri Weber ( born 23 June 1944 ) is a French politician and Member of the European Parliament for the north - west of France .
Marguerite Bellanger ( 10 June 1838 - 23 November 1886 ) was a French stage actress and courtesan .
Arnould Galopin ( 1865 , Marbeuf , Eure - 1934 ) was a prolific French writer with more than 50 novels to his credit .
Augustin Daniel Belliard , comte Belliard et de l'Empire ( March 23 , 1769 in Fontenay - le - Comte , Vendée -- January 28 , 1832 in Brussels ) was a French general .

Antoine Emmanuel Ernest Monis ( French pronunciation : ​(ɛʁnɛst mɔni ) ; 23 May 1846 in Châteauneuf - sur - Charente -- 25 May 1929 in Mondouzil ) was a French politician of the Third Republic , deputy of Gironde from 1885 to 1889 and then senator of the same department from 1891 to 1920 .

( Isaac ) Kadmi Cohen ( 1892 - -1944 ) was a French / Jewish writer .

Gérald Laroche ( born 1964 ) is a French actor born in Paris , France .
Jean - Pascal Lacoste ( also known as Jean - Pascal or Jipé ; born 21 June 1978 ) is a French singer , actor and TV host .
Léon Deschamps ( 1864 -- 28 December 1899 ) was a French novelist and poet , most notable as the founder of the La Plume literary review .
Charles Baudouin ( French : ( bodwɛ̃ ) ; 26 July 1893 -- August 25 , 1963 ) was a French - Swiss psychoanalyst .
André Chéradame ( 1871 - -1948 ) was a French journalist and scholar from the École Libre des Sciences Politiques .
