Antje Huber ( 23 May 1924 in Stettin -- 30 September 2015 ) was a German politician who was the Federal Minister for Youth , Family and Health from 1976 to 1982 .
Philippe Katerine ( born Philippe Blanchard ; December 8 , 1968 in Chantonnay , Vendée , France ) is a French singer , who began his career in 1991 .
Jacques de Baroncelli ( 25 June 1881 -- 12 January 1951 ) was a French film director best known for his silent films from 1915 to the late 1930s .
Alexandre Pierre Freslon ( 11 May 1808 -- 26 January 1867 ) was a French Lawyer who became a representative in the Constituent Assembly and Minister of Public Education and Religion in 1848 .
Akkineni Nageswara Rao ( 20 September 1923 -- 22 January 2014 ) , widely known as ANR , was an Indian film actor and producer , known for his works predominantly in Telugu cinema .
André Roussin , ( 22 January 1911 -- 3 November 1987 ) , was a French playwright .
Fritz Henßler ( born April 12 , 1886 in Altensteig ; died December 4 , 1953 in Witten ) was a German Social Democratic politician .
Louis Marie Baptiste Atthalin , Baron Atthalin ( born 22 June 1784 at Colmar , Haut - Rhin - 3 September 1856 ) ) was a French Army officer , politician , painter , watercolorist , and lithographer .
Jeanne Loury or Jane Loury ( 1876 - -1951 ) was a French stage and film actress .
André Marty ( 6 November 1886 -- 23 November 1956 ) was a leading figure in the French Communist Party ( PCF ) for nearly thirty years .
Polaire was the stage name used by French singer and actress Émilie Marie Bouchaud ( 14 May 1874 -- 14 October 1939 ) .
Megan Hauserman ( born November 5 , 1981 ) is an American model and reality television personality , best known for her appearances on Vh1 .
Tropicaliente was a Brazilian soap opera produced and displayed at the time of 18 hours by Rede Globo , ran from May 16 to December 31 , 1994 , totaling 194 chapters .
Durval Guimarães ( born 14 July 1935 ) is a Brazilian former sport shooter who competed in the 1968 Summer Olympics , the 1972 Summer Olympics , the 1976 Summer Olympics , the 1980 Summer Olympics and the 1984 Summer Olympics .
Pablo Javier Robledo ( 23 July 1975 ) is a cross - country skier set to represent Argentina at the 2014 Winter Paralympics .
Saleh Alah - Djaba ( born January 5 , 1950 ) is a track and field sprint athlete who competes internationally for Chad Alah - Djaba represented Chad at the 1972 Summer Olympics in Munich .

Heike Nagel ( née Hustede , born 16 January 1946 ) is a German former swimmer who competed in the 1964 , 1968 and 1972 Summer Olympics .

Garrincha was the most outstanding player of the 1962 FIFA World Cup .
Shamo Quaye ( 22 October 1971 -- 30 November 1997 ) was a football player from Ghana , who was a member of the Men 's National Team that won the bronze medal at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona , Spain .
Anja Nyffeler ( born 25 November 1992 ) is a Swiss competitor in synchronized swimming who competed in the 2011 World Aquatics Championships , 2013 World Aquatics Championships , and 2012 Summer Olympics .
Wu Meijin ( simplified Chinese : 吴美锦 ; traditional Chinese : 吳美錦 ; pinyin : Wú Měijǐn ; born April 25 , 1980 in Ruian , Zhejiang ) is a Chinese weightlifter who competed in the Men 's 56 kilogram weight class at the 2004 Summer Olympics and won the silver medal , lifting 287.5 kilograms in total .
Rupali Akhter ( Bengali : রুপালী আক্তার ) is a Bangladeshi national women 's Kabaddi player who was part of the team that won the bronze medal at the 2010 Asian Games .

Anton Heiden ( born July 4 , 1960 in Barendrecht ) is a former water polo player from the Netherlands Heiden participated once with the Dutch national water polo team at the Olympics , finishing in sixth position at the 1984 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles .
Aleksandr Kolotov ( born 4 March 1964 ) is a Russian former water polo player who competed in the 1988 Summer Olympics and in the 1992 Summer Olympics .
Jasna Kolar - Merdan ( born October 19 , 1956 in Mostar ) is a former Yugoslav handball player who competed in the 1980 Summer Olympics , in the 1984 Summer Olympics and in the 1992 Summer Olympics .
Dinko Petrov ( Bulgarian : Динко Петров ) ( born 10 March 1935 ) is a Bulgarian former wrestler who competed in the 1956 Summer Olympics , in the 1960 Summer Olympics , and in the 1964 Summer Olympics .
Toby Kane ( born 30 December 1986 ) is an Australian Paralympian who won a bronze medal in the men 's super G Standing at the 2006 Winter Paralympics in Torino and a bronze medal in the men 's super G standing in his third Winter Paralympics at 2014 Winter Paralympics in Sochi .
Delfo Cabrera Gómez ( April 2 , 1919 -- August 2 , 1981 ) was an Argentine athlete , winner of the marathon race at the 1948 Summer Olympics in one of the most dramatic finishes in athletics history .
Shahnaz Parvin Maleka ( Bengali : শাহনাজ পারভীন মালেকা ) is a Bangladeshi national women Kabaddi player who was part of the team that won the bronze medal at the 2010 Asian Games .
Libor Capalini ( born January 30 , 1973 ) is a modern pentathlete from the Czech Republic who won the bronze medal in the Modern Pentathlon at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens , Greece .

Graham Crouch ( born 11 January 1948 ) is an Australian former middle - distance runner who competed in the 1976 Summer Olympics .
Nduka Odizor ( born 9 August 1958 ) is a former tennis player from Nigeria , who represented his native country at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul , where he was defeated in the first round by American lucky loser Robert Seguso .
Daouda Karaboué ( born 11 December 1975 in Abidjan , Côte d'Ivoire ) is a French handball player , he won the gold medal at the 2008 Summer Olympics , the 2009 World Championships and the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Mino De Rossi ( born 21 May 1931 ) was a road bicycle and track cyclist from Italy , who won the gold medal in the men 's 4.000 m team pursuit at the 1952 Summer Olympics , alongside Marino Morettini , Loris Campana and Guido Messina .
Bill Adcocks ( born 11 November 1941 in Coventry ) is a British former long - distance runner who competed in the 1968 Summer Olympics .

Duje Bonačić ( born April 10 , 1929 ) is a retired Croatian rower who competed in the 1952 Summer Olympics for Yugoslavia .
Cameron Hammond ( born 20 September 1989 in Moree , New South Wales ) is an Aboriginal professional boxer who represented Australia at the 2010 Commonwealth Games in New Delhi , India and 2012 Summer Olympics in the welterweight division .
José Couto ( born 27 February 1978 ) is a breaststroke swimmer from Portugal , who represented his home country at the 1996 Summer Olympics , the 2000 Summer Olympics and at the 2004 Summer Olympics .
Ainhoa Ibarra Astellara ( born 27 October 1968 in Guernica ) is a Spanish former alpine skier who competed in the 1988 Winter Olympics , in the 1992 Winter Olympics , in the 1994 Winter Olympics , and in the 1998 Winter Olympics .

Roy Askevold ( 1 July 1935 -- 30 March 2005 ) was a Norwegian amateur boxer who competed in the 1960 Summer Olympics .
Marie - Ève Drolet ( born February 3 , 1982 ) is a Canadian short track speed skater who competed in the 2002 Winter Olympics where she won a bronze in the relay event .

Thomas Greiner ( born 3 May 1963 ) is a retired German rower who won a gold medal in the coxless fours at the 1988 Summer Olympics .

Adkar Maruti ( born 15 February 1950 ) is an Indian former wrestler who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Igor Gočanin ( July 24 , 1966 ) is a Yugoslav water polo player . He was part of the Yugoslavia team which won the Gold medal in water polo in the 1988 Summer Olympics .

Charles Palmer - Tomkinson was a competitor in the 1964 Winter Olympics in the Giant Slalom and Downhill events .

Fred Everiss ( born 1882 in West Bromwich ) was secretary - manager of the English football club West Bromwich Albion and also served the club as assistant secretary and later as a director .
Ingeborg Arvola ( born 7 July 1974 in Honningsvåg ) is a Norwegian novelist and children 's writer .
Johannes Mathesius ( June 24 , 1504 in Rochlitz -- October 7 , 1565 ) , also called Johann Mathesius or John Mathesius , was a German minister and a Lutheran reformer .

Zarqa Nawaz ( Born 1968 in Liverpool , England ) is a British - Canadian freelance writer , journalist , broadcaster , and filmmaker of Pakistani origin .

Stu West ( born 24 December 1964 , Lincolnshire , England ) is the current bassist in the English punk band The Damned .
Stephen van Haestregt ( born 12 September 1974 in Westdorpe ) is a Dutch drummer , best known as the drummer of the Dutch symphonic metal band Within Temptation until his departure in 2010 .
Sosipatra of Ephesus ( Greek : Σωσιπάτρα ) was a Neoplatonist philosopher and mystic who lived in the first half of the 4th century CE . The story of her life is told in Eunapius ' Lives of the Sophists .
Henning Christiansen ( May 28 , 1932 , Copenhagen -- December 10 , 2008 ) was a Danish composer and an active member of the Fluxus - movement .
Ansgar Beckermann ( born 29 June 1945 in Hamburg ) is a German philosopher who deals primarily with philosophy of mind and epistemology .
Frederik Paludan - Müller ( 7 February 1809 -- 27 December 1876 ) was a Danish poet , the third son of Jens Paludan - Müller and born in Kerteminde , on the island of Funen .

Woldemar Hau ( Russian : Владимир Иванович Гау. 16 February 1816 , Tallinn - 23 March 1895 , Saint Petersburg ) was a Baltic German portrait painter who worked in the Biedermeier style .

János Pásztor ( 1881 , Gyoma - 1945 , Budapest ) was a renowned Hungarian academic sculptor in the first decades of the 20th century .
Giovanni Garzoni ( 1419 - -1506 ) was an Italian humanist and physician from Bologna , where he was professor of medicine and teacher of rhetoric .
William Rickarby Miller ( May 20 , 1818 Staindrop - July 1893 New York City ) was an American painter , of the Hudson River School .
Duchess Marie Gabrielle in Bavaria ( German : Marie Gabrielle Mathilde Isabelle Therese Antoinette Sabine Herzogin in Bayern ) was born 9 October 1878 in Tegernsee in the Kingdom of Bavaria and died 24 October 1912 in Sorrento in the Kingdom of Italy ) .
Richard Mudge ( * 1718 in Bideford ; † April 1763 in Bedworth ) was an English clergyman and composer of the late baroque period .
Béla Balázs ( Hungarian : ( ˈbeːlɒ ˈbɒlaːʒ ) ; 4 August 1884 , Szeged -- 17 May 1949 , Budapest ) , born Herbert Bauer , was a Hungarian - Jewish film critic , aesthete , writer and poet .

Hugo Zöller ( 12 January 1852 -- 1933 in Munich ) was a German explorer and journalist .
Feletheus and his wife were captured , and executed in Ravenna in 487 .
Otto Rubensohn ( 24 November 1867 , Kassel -- 9 August 1964 , Höchenschwand ) was a German - Jewish classical archaeologist .
Lima Barreto was born in Rio de Janeiro in 1881 , to João Henriques de Lima Barreto and Amália Augusta .
Petrus Jacobus Kipp ( Utrecht , 5 March 1808 -- Delft , 3 February 1864 ) was a Dutch apothecary , chemist and instrument maker .
Martino Bassi ( 1542 - -1591 ) was an Italian architect active in the Renaissance period , mainly in Milan .
Giovanni Poleni ( b. Venice , around 1683 ; d. Padua , Nov. , 1761 ) was a Marquess , physicist , mathematician and antiquarian .

Konstantinos Volanakis ( Greek : Κωνσταντίνος Βολανάκης ; 1837 , Heraklion - 29 June 1907 , Piraeus ) was a Greek painter who became known as the `` father of Greek seascape painting '' .

Milan Sachs ( 28 November 1884 -- 4 August 1968 ) was a Czech - Croatian opera conductor and composer , who was long associated with the Zagreb Opera in Croatia , where he conducted some important local premieres , including Wagner 's Parsifal , and Janáček 's Jenůfa ( 1920 ) .
Karlen Abramov ( Armenian : Կառլեն Աբրամով , born 9 May 1987 in Tashkent , Uzbek SSR - 2008 ) was an Uzbekistani ethnically Jewish - Armenian professional football striker .

Jan Duiker ( also Johannes Duiker ) ( The Hague , 1 March 1890 -- Amsterdam , 23 February 1935 ) was a Dutch architect .
James Tilly Matthews ( 1770 -- 10 January 1815 ) was a London tea broker , originally from Wales and of Huguenot descent , who was committed to Bethlem ( colloquially Bedlam ) psychiatric hospital in 1797 .
Arthur Oldham died in Villejuif in 2003 , aged 76 .
Mirdza Ķempe ( later Naikovska ) ( 9 February ( O.S. 27 January ) 1907 , Liepāja - 12 April 1974 , Riga ) was a noted Latvian poet , translator and tutor .
Polibio Fumagalli ( October 26 , 1830 in Inzago -- June 21 , 1900 in Milan ) was an Italian composer , organist , and pianist .
Félix Fénéon ( 22 June 1861 , Turin , Italy -- 29 February 1944 , Châtenay - Malabry ) was a Parisian anarchist and art critic during the late 19th century .

Marcelle Pradot died in Neuilly - sur - Seine in 1982 , two and a half years after L'Herbier .
Carl Heinrich Auspitz ( September 2 , 1835 , in Nikolsburg , Moravia -- 22 May , 1886 , in Vienna ) was a Jewish Austrian dermatologist .

William F. Poe ( July 22 , 1931 -- May 1 , 2014 ) was the mayor of Tampa , Florida from 1974 to 1979 .
Antonio Dardani ( 1677 - -1735 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , mainly in his native Bologna ..
Gaetano Zompini ( 25 September 1700 -- 20 May 1778 ) was an Italian printmaker and engraver , known for his prints depicting workers from the lower classes in Venice .
Ross Hagen died of prostate cancer at his home in Brentwood , Los Angeles , on May 7 , 2011 , at the age of 72 .
Reinhold Johan von Fersen ( 1646 , Tallinn -- 1716 , Stockholm ) was the governor of Västerbotten County from 1688 to 1692 and of Halland County from 1705 to 1710 .

Lucas Osiander the Elder ( 16 December 1534 , Nuremberg - 17 September 1604 , Stuttgart ) was a German pastor of the Evangelischen Landeskirche in Württemberg .
François - Pierre Blin or Pierre - François Blin , was born in Rennes on the 8th of June 1756 , and died on the 4th of November 1834 in Chantenay - sur - Loire .

Marie Delcourt ( Ixelles , 18 November 1891 -- Liège , 11 February 1979 ) was a Belgian classical philologist .
Edward Lawry Norton ( 28 July 1898 , Rockland , Maine--28 January 1983 , Chatham , New Jersey ) was an accomplished Bell Labs engineer and scientist famous for developing the concept of the Norton equivalent circuit .
Consalvo Carelli ( March 29 , 1818 in Naples -- December 2 , 1900 in Naples , Italy ) was an Italian landscape painter and painter of the School of Posillipo .
Jan van Balen ( 21 July 1611 , Antwerp -- 14 March 1654 ) was a Flemish painter known for his Baroque paintings of history and allegorical subjects .

Édouard Batiste was a French composer and organist born in Paris on 28 March 1820 , and studied at the Imperial Conservatoire as a teenager , winning prizes in solfège , harmony and accompaniment , counterpoint and fugue , and organ .
Heinrich Bütefisch ( 24 February 1894 , Hanover -- 5 September 1969 , Essen ) was a German chemist , manager at IG Farben , and Nazi war criminal .
Tom Dragna ( 1889 - -1977 ) was a Sicilian - American bootlegger and mobster who became a member of the Los Angeles crime family .
Caspar Joseph Brambach ( 14 July 1833 -- 20 June 1902 ) was a 19th - century German musician , pedagogue , composer whose reputation extended beyond Germany to America , and a renowned conductor of the leading choirs in Bonn .

Dante Gianello ( Chiesa in Valmalenco , Italy , 26 March 1912 -- Privas , France , 14 November 1992 ) was a professional road bicycle racer .
Gerald Dreyer ( 22 September 1929 -- 5 September 1985 ) was a boxer from Pretoria , South Africa , who competed in the Lightweight division during his career as an amateur .
François - Rupert Carabin ( 17 March 1862 , Saverne , Bas - Rhin - 1932 , Strasbourg ) was a French cabinetmaker , photographer and sculptor .
Laurent Merchiers ( 9 June 1904 -- 5 February 1986 ) was a Belgian liberal politician , lawyer , and a Professor at the University of Ghent .
Johann Friedrich Eduard Sobolewski ( born Königsberg ( Królewiec ) , October 1 , 1804 or 1808 - died St. Louis , May 17 , 1872 ) was a Polish - American violinist , composer , and conductor .

Isaac Bargrave ( 1586 -- January 1643 ) was an English royalist churchman , Dean of Canterbury from 1625 to 1643 .
Rudy Kousbroek died aged 80 in Leiden .
Ernesto Nazareth was born in Rio de Janeiro , one of five children .
Henrik Gabriel Porthan ( 1739 in Viitasaari -- 1804 in Turku ) was a scholar sometimes known as The Father of Finnish History .
Giuseppe Simonelli ( Naples , c.1650 - -1710 ) was an Italian painter , active in a late - Baroque style .
Paul Bairoch ( 24 July 1930 , Antwerp -- 12 February 1999 , Geneva ) was one of the great post - war economic historians who specialised in global economic history , urban history and historical demography .
Lorser Feitelson ( 1898 , Savannah , GA -- 1978 , Los Angeles , CA ) was born in Savannah , Georgia , but was raised in New York City , where his family relocated shortly after his birth .
Jérémie Pauzié ( 1716 -- 1779 in Geneva ) was a Swiss - French diamond jeweler , artist and memoirist , best known for his work for the Russian Imperial court and his masterpiece , the Imperial Crown of Russia , that was commissioned for the 1762 coronation of Empress Catherine the Great .
Haidee Wright ( 13 January 1867 -- 29 January 1943 ) as Ada Wright was a London born English character actress .
Magnus Gottfried Lichtwer ( 30 January 1719 , in Wurzen -- 7 July 1783 , in Halberstadt ) was a German fabulist .
Victor Meirelles de Lima ( 18 August 1832 , Florianópolis - 22 February 1903 , Rio de Janeiro ) was a Brazilian painter who is best known for his works relating to his nation 's culture and history .

Klári Tolnay ( born Rózsi Tolnay ) was born on 17 July 1914 in Budapest , as the daughter of István Tolnay and Eleonóra Siess .

Jiří Kodet ( 6 December 1937 in Prague - 25 June 2005 in Prague ) was a Czech actor .
The Gunnister Man is the remains of a man found by two Shetlanders in a peat bog not far from the junction of the A970 road in Gunnister , Shetland , Scotland .
Giovanni Guerra ( 1544 - -1618 ) was an Italian draughtsman and painter from Modena who worked in Rome , where he probably arrived in 1562 , though he was not documented until 1583 , when he frescoed three friezes of allegorical figures in the Palazzetto Cenci , a modest project for a patron who was not very prestigious .
Arturo Ambrogi ( 1874 -- 1936 in San Salvador , El Salvador ) was a writer and journalist , considered one of the pioneers of Salvadoran literature , along with Francisco Gavidia and Alberto Masferrer .
Acosta ( birth name : José Julián Acosta Calbo ) was born in San Juan , Puerto Rico .
William Bell Wait ( 1839 - -1916 ) was a teacher in the New York Institute for the Education of the Blind who invented New York Point , a system of writing for the blind that enjoyed wide use in the United States before the Braille system was universally adopted there .

Johann Gottlob von Kurr ( 15 January 1798 , Sulzbach an der Murr -- 9 May 1870 , Stuttgart ) was a German pharmacist and naturalist , making contributions in the fields of botany and mineralogy .

John Bennet Lawes was born at Rothamsted in modern - day Harpenden near St Albans , Hertfordshire on 28 December 1814 , the only son of John Bennet Lawes , owner of the Rothamsted estate and lord of the manor of Rothamsted .
Benjamin Whichcote ( 1609 - -1683 ) was a British Establishment and Puritan divine , Provost of King 's College , Cambridge , and leader of the Cambridge Platonists .
Pope Sixtus I ( 42 -- 125 ) was the Bishop of Rome from c. 115 to his death c. 124 .
Anders Gustaf Ekeberg ( Stockholm , Sweden , 16 January 1767 -- Uppsala , Sweden , 11 February 1813 ) was a Swedish chemist who discovered tantalum in 1802 .
Bernhard Hirzel ( 12 August 1807 -- 6 June 1847 in Paris ) was a Swiss theologian and Orientalist .
Alfredo Oriani ( 22 August 1852 in Faenza -- 18 October 1909 in Casola Valsenio ) was an Italian author , writer and social critic .
Werner Zoege von Manteuffel ( 13 July 1857 , in Määri , Estonia -- 14 March 1926 , in Tallinn , Estonia ) was a Baltic German medical surgeon .
Dorothea Susanne of Simmern ( 15 November 1544 , Simmern -- 8 April 1592 , Weimar ) was a princess of the Electorate of the Palatinate and by marriage Duchess of Saxe - Weimar .
Fulvio Croce , ( June 6 , 1901 - April 28 , 1977 ) was an Italian lawyer , President of the Turin Bar Association , who was killed by the terrorist association Red Brigades .
Walter Livingston ( November 27 , 1740 Clermont Manor , Clermont , Columbia County , New York - May 14 , 1797 New York City ) was an American merchant , lawyer and politician .
Otto Friedrich Ferdinand von Görschen ( April 12 , 1824 in Neuruppin -- June 8 , 1875 in Eberswalde ) was a Royal Prussian lieutenant colonel and highly decorated war hero of the 19th century .
Vladimir Varlaj ( 1895 - -1962 ) was a Croatian artist , a member of the Group of Four during the Zagreb Spring Salon of the 1920s , and a founder of the Independent Group of Artists .
Vasco Santana ( full name : Vasco António Rodrigues Santana ; 28 January 1898 in Lisbon -- 13 June 1958 ) was a Portuguese actor , one of the most renowned of the classical era of Portuguese cinema .
Emanuele Appiani ( c. 1380 -- February 15 , 1457 ) was Prince of Piombino during the Appiani dynasty in the Renaissance .
Christian Friedrich Henrici ( January 14 , 1700 -- May 10 , 1764 ) , writing under the pen name Picander , was a German poet and librettist for many of the cantatas which Johann Sebastian Bach composed in Leipzig .
Dimo Todorovski ( Macedonian Slavic : Димо Тодоровски ) , ( 1910 , Thessaloniki - 1983 , Skopje ) , was a prominent Macedonian artist and a first generation Macedonian sculptor .
Maria Rowohlt ( born as Maria Pierenkämper ; 5 June 1910 in Bochum -- 11 April 2005 in Hamburg ) was a German actress .
Mieczysław Zygfryd Słowikowski ( Jazgarzew , near Warsaw , 1896 - -1989 , London ) , also known as `` Rygor - Słowikowski , '' was a Polish Army officer whose intelligence work in North Africa facilitated Allied preparations for the 1942 Operation Torch landings .
Gavrilo Vitković ( 28 January 1829 , in Buda , Austrian Empire -- 25 July 1902 , in Negotin , Kingdom of Serbia ) was an engineer , historian , professor and collector of old manuscripts .
Giuseppe Casciaro ( March 9 , 1861 in Ortelle , Province of Lecce , Region of Apulia -- October 25 , 1941 in Naples ) was an Italian painter , active mainly in Naples .
Frida Leider was born at Berlin , where she studied singing while working in a bank .
Adam Elsheimer ( 18 March 1578 -- 11 December 1610 ) was a German artist working in Rome who died at only thirty - two , but was very influential in the early 17th century in the field of Baroque paintings .
Renata Fronzi died at the age of 82 of multiple organ dysfunction syndrome , which was brought on by diabetes , on April 15 , 2008 , at the Hospital Municipal Lourenço Jorge in the Barra da Tijuca neighborhood of western Rio de Janeiro .
Francesco Merli was born Francesco Cova in Corsico ( Milan ) , son of Luigi and Emilia Cova .
Shapland Hugh Swinny ( 30 January 1857 , Dublin -- 31 August 1923 , London ) was an Irish economist and Comtean positivist .
Alois Friedrich Rogenhofer ( 22 December 1831 , Vienna -- 15 January 1897 , Vienna ) was an Austrian entomologist .

Immanuel Munk ( 30 May 1852 , Posen -- 1 August 1903 , Berlin ) was a German physiologist .
Sigmund Neuberger , or Sigmund Newburger , was born on 25 February 1871 in Munich , Germany and died on 9 May 1911 in Edinburgh , Scotland .
Mikołaj Rudnicki - ( born 6 December 1881 in Sokołów Podlaski - died 28 June 1978 in Puszczykowo ) was a Polish linguist .
Arie de Vroet ( Dutch pronunciation : ( ˈaːri də ˈvrut ) ) ( born November 9 , 1918 , Oud - Beijerland - died September 9 , 1999 , Woudenberg ) was a Dutch footballer who was active as a left winger .
Claudi Lorenzale i Sugrañes ( December 8 , 1814 , Barcelona - March 31 , 1889 , Barcelona ) was a Catalonian painter , associated with the German Nazarene movement and local efforts to recover the history of the Catalan region .
Otti Berger ( * October 4 , 1898 in Zmajevac / Baranja , Hungary ; † 1944/45 in Auschwitz concentration camp ) was a textile artist and weaver and a member of the Bauhaus .
Jovan Žižić ( Serbian : Јован Жижић ) ( 1874 , Drobnjak -- January 20 , 1941 Pljevlja ) was one of the key commanders of the Montenegrin Army in the period before and after the First World War .
Lucía Sánchez Saornil ( Madrid . December 13 , 1895 -- Valencia . June 2 , 1970 ) , was a Spanish poet , militant anarchist and feminist .
René Vannes ( 1888 Lille , France--1956 Brussels ) was a Belgian musicologist and author of a standard history of lutenists , which is also used as a standard reference work on violin bow makes and archetiers .
Siegfried Breuer ( 24 June 1906 , Vienna -- 1 February 1954 , Weende , Göttingen ) was an Austrian stage and film actor and occasional film director and screenwriter .
Élie Reclus ( French : ( ʁəkly ) ; 16 June 1827 , Sainte - Foy - la - Grande -- 11 February 1904 , Brussels ) was a French ethnographer who studied what were then called primitive cultures , and an anarchist .
Émile - Louis Burnouf ( 26 August 1821 , in Valognes -- January 1907 , in Paris ) was a leading nineteenth - century Orientalist and racialist whose ideas influenced the development of theosophy and Aryanism .
Martin of Cochem ( born at Cochem on the Mosel , 13 December 1630 or 1634 ; died in the convent at Waghäusel , 10 September 1712 ) was a German Capuchin theologian , preacher , and ascetic writer .

Saint Balthild of Ascania ( /ˈbɔːltɪld/ ; Old English : Bealdhild , ' bold sword ' or ' bold spear ; around 626 -- January 30 , 680 ) , also called Bathilda , Baudour , or Bauthieult , was the wife and queen of Clovis II , the king of Burgundy and Neustria ( 639 - -658 ) .
Princess Margaret of Denmark ( Margrethe Françoise Louise Marie Helene ; 17 September 1895 , Bernstorff Palace -- 18 September 1992 , Copenhagen , Denmark ) was a princess of Denmark and Iceland by birth and a princess of Bourbon - Parma as the wife of Prince René of Bourbon - Parma
Nicesipolis or Nicasipolis of Pherae ( Greek : Νικησίπολις ) , was a Thessalian woman , native of the city Pherae , wife or concubine of king Philip II of Macedon and mother of Thessalonica of Macedon .
Zaynab bint Jahsh ( Arabic : زينب بنت جحش‎ ) ( c. 590 -- 641 ) was a cousin and wife of Muhammad and therefore a Mother of the Believers .
Kosala Devi was Empress consort of the Magadha Empire as the first wife of Emperor Bimbisara ( 558 - -491 BC ) .
Eva Marie Veigel ( also Eva Maria Violette , with variants Eva Maria and Ava - Maria ) ( February 29 , 1724 , Vienna - October 16 , 1822 , London ) was a dancer and the wife of actor David Garrick .
Dimitra Liani ( Greek : Δήμητρα Λιάνη ; born 30 April 1955 ) is the third wife of former Greek Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou .
Arlene Klasky ( born May 26 , 1949 ) is an American animator , graphic designer , producer and co - founder of Klasky - Csupo with Gábor Csupó .
Etta Place ( born circa 1878 , date of death unknown ) was a companion of the American outlaws Butch Cassidy ( real name Robert LeRoy Parker ) and the Sundance Kid ( Harry Alonzo Longabaugh ) , both members of the outlaw gang known as the Wild Bunch .
Tan Yuling ( 1920 -- 14 August 1942 ) , born Tatara Yuling , was a concubine of China 's last emperor Puyi .
Alcibiades was married to Hipparete , the daughter of Hipponicus , a wealthy Athenian .
Joan Fiona Dickson OBE , or Fiona Dickson ( best known as Fiona Castle ) ( born 1940 on the Wirral Peninsula , Cheshire ) is a retired British dancer who is most notable for her marriage to the TV entertainer Roy Castle .
Danielle Mitterrand ( born Danielle Émilienne Isabelle Gouze ; 29 October 1924 -- 22 November 2011 ) was the wife of French President François Mitterrand , and president of the foundation France Libertés Fondation Danielle Mitterrand .
Atractaspis coalescens , or the black burrowing asp , is a species of venomous snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Xanthonia is a genus of leaf beetles found in eastern Asia and North and Central America .
Hibiscadelphus distans ( Kauai hau kuahiwi ) is an extremely rare species of flowering plant in the mallow family , Malvaceae , that is endemic to the island of Kauaʻi in Hawaii .
Microthrissa is a genus of sprats in the herring family , Clupeidae , which is endemic to Africa .
Rubus pedatus is an Asian and North American species of raspberry known under the common names Five - leaved bramble , Strawberryleaf Raspberry and Creeping Raspberry .
Eutreta diana is a species in the family Tephritidae , known as fruit flies in North America and picture wing flies in Europe .
Limacina rangii is a species of swimming sea snail in the family Limacinidae , which belong to the group commonly known as sea butterflies ( Thecosomata ) .
Restrepia trichoglossa , commonly called the Hairy - tongued Restrepia , is a species of orchid found from Mexico ( Chiapas ) to Peru .
Homoephloeus licheneus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Homoephloeus .
Cryptanthus bivittatus , ( commonly known as Earth Star , along with Cryptanthus zonatus zebrinus ) is a small , terrestrial species of plant in the Bromeliaceae family .
Candidatus Atelocyanobacterium thalassa , previously cyanobacterium UCYN - A , is a species of non - photosynthetic nitrogen - fixing marine cyanobacteria that lacks the oxygen - producing photosystem II complex of the photosynthetic apparatus , the Carboxysome , enzymes of the Calvin and tricarboxylic acid cycles , as well as several enzymes involved in amino acid synthesis .
Sympetrum is a genus of small to medium - sized skimmer dragonflies , known as darters in the UK and as meadowhawks in the North America .
Hapalomantis minima is a species of praying mantis in the genus Hapalomantis .
Cirripectes fuscoguttatus , the Spotted blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the Pacific ocean .
Hemieleotris is a genus of small sleeper gobies native to Central America and Colombia , where they are only found in freshwater habitats .
Seseli is a genus of herbaceous perennial plants .
Khadia beswickii is a species of plant in the Aizoaceae family .
Phymaspermum is a genus of African plants in the chamomile tribe within the daisy family .
Drosanthus is a genus of tephritid or fruit fly in the family Tephritidae .
Macrobrachium japonicum is a species of freshwater shrimp found in Asia that was first described in 1849 .
Phillips ' small - eared shrew ( Cryptotis phillipsii ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae found in Mexico .
Epanterias is a dubious genus of theropod dinosaur from the Kimmeridgian - Tithonian - age Upper Jurassic upper Morrison Formation of Garden Park , Colorado .
Prionosciadium lilacinum is a plant species native to the Mexican States of Jalisco and Nayarit .
Hemiphractus bubalus , or the Ecuador horned treefrog , is a species of frog in the Hemiphractidae family .
Geissanthus is a genus of flowering plants in the family Primulaceae .
Dermomurex pauperculus , common name the little aspella , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Penicillium confertum is an anamorph fungus species of the genus of Penicillium .
Stenosigma is a small neotropical genus of potter wasps .
Asterogyne is a genus of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family native to Central America and northern South America , with three of the five known species endemic to Venezuela .
Trachelipus razzautii is a species of woodlouse in the genus Trachelipus belonging to the family Trachelipodidae that can be found in northern Italy , Slovenia , the Greek island of Lesbos and European Turkey .
Apocynaceae is a family of flowering plants that includes trees , shrubs , herbs , stem succulents , and vines , commonly called the dogbane family , after the American plant known as dogbane , Apocynum cannabinum .
Bujurquina is a genus of cichlid fish endemic to South America .
Rickettsia is a genus of nonmotile , Gram - negative , nonspore - forming , highly pleomorphic bacteria that can present as cocci ( 0.1 μm in diameter ) , rods ( 1 - -4 μm long ) , or thread - like ( 10 μm long ) .
Penstemon rostriflorus is a species of penstemon known by the common names beaked penstemon , Bridge penstemon , or Bridges ' penstemon .
The single species , Aciculopoda mapesi , was named by Rodney Feldmann and Carrie Schweitzer in honour of Royal Mapes , a paleontologist who discovered the type specimen .
Hylatomus was a genus of birds in the Picidae family that is now considered a synonym of Dryocopus .
Pectiniidae is a family of stony corals , commonly known as chalice corals .
Wainuia clarki is a species of air - breathing predatory land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Rhytididae .
Parrishia is an extinct genus of sphenosuchian crocodylomorph that is considered a nomen dubium because of the lack of diagnostic features associated with it .
Lilaeopsis masonii is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common names mudflat quillplant and Mason 's lilaeopsis .
Scortum barcoo is a species of fish in the family Terapontidae known by the common names Barcoo grunter and jade perch .
Ungaliophis continentalis , or the Chiapan boa , is a species of snake in the Tropidophiidae family .
Due to the widespread distribution of the Dana duckbill eel , as well as its deep - water nature and the subsequent perceived lack of threats , the IUCN redlist currently lists the species as Least Concern .
Streptomyces turgidiscabies is a streptomycete bacterium species , causing scab in potatoes .
Mitrospingus is a genus of bird formerly in the family Thraupidae .
Choristoneura zapulata , the zapulata moth , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Zetoceras is an extinct ammonoid cephalopod genus from the suborder Phylloceratina that lived during the Early and Middle Jurassic in what is now Europe , and is included in the ( family ) Phylloceratidae .
Deplanchea is a genus of about eight species of tropical rainforest trees , constituting part of the plant family Bignoniaceae .
The Cretan meadow foxtail ( Alopecurus creticus ) is a species of foxtail grass .
Pristimantis lichenoides ( rana camuflada in Spanish ) is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Oberea trigonalis is a species of longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Breuning in 1950 .
Syncarpha is a genus of herbaceous flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Mesogobius batrachocephalus , the knout goby or toad goby , is one of the species of gobiid fish native to the Black Sea and the Sea of Azov basins .
It was first listed as Maritrema sp . II in 1988 , then described as the only species of a new genus , Floridatrema heardi , in 1994 , and eventually reassigned in 2003 to Maritrema as Maritrema heardi .
Drosera monticola is a perennial carnivorous plant species in the genus Drosera , the sundews .
Eburia albolineata is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that is endemic to Venezuela .
Hypalastoroides is a neotropical genus of potter wasps with a few nearctic and andean species .
Cirsium palustre , the marsh thistle or European swamp thistle , is a herbaceous biennial ( or often perennial ) species of the genus Cirsium .
Demanietta is a genus of freshwater crabs found in Indochinese Peninsula of Southeast Asia .
Orthomiella is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The members ( species ) of this genus are found in the Indomalaya ecozone and the Palearctic ecozone ( Yunnan ) .
Meiacanthus luteus , the Yellow fangbelly , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific ocean , around northern Australia .
Cnemaspis indraneildasii is a species of gecko endemic to India .
Ocnus planci is a species of sea cucumber in the family Cucumariidae .
Passiflora picturata is a species of Passion flower in the Passifloraceae family .
Petrolisthes eriomerus is a species of marine porcelain crab found in the eastern Pacific Ocean .
Woodwardia fimbriata , known by the common name giant chain fern , is a fern species in the family Blechnaceae , in the eupolypods II clade of the order Polypodiales , in the class Polypodiopsida .
Hadrosaurids ( Greek : ἁδρός , hadrós , `` stout , thick '' ) , or duck - billed dinosaurs , are members of the ornithischian family Hadrosauridae .
Pluteus nevadensis is a species of fungus in the agaric family Pluteaceae .
Cyathea caudata is a species of tree fern native to the islands of Luzon and Mindanao in the Philippines , where it grows in montane forest .
Neominois ridingsii , Riding 's Satyr , is a species of butterfly in the Nymphalidae family .
Lorosuchus is an extinct genus of sebecid mesoeucrocodylian known from Tucumán Province of north - western Argentina .
Proisocrinus ruberrimus is a species of crinoid that is in the monotypic genus Proisocrinus .
Acineta barkeri is a species of orchid found from Mexico to Guatemala .
Paullinia is a genus of flowering shrubs , small trees and lianas in the soapberry family , Sapindaceae , native to tropical South America , Central America and the Caribbean .
Sarcophilus is a genus of carnivorous marsupial best known for its only living member , the Tasmanian devil .
Rhodochorton is a genus of filamentous red alga adapted to low light levels .
Oxystele sinensis , common name the pink - lipped topshell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Laccaria laccata , commonly known as the deceiver , or waxy laccaria , is a white - spored species of small edible mushroom found throughout North America and Europe .
Charitometridae is a family of crinoids or feather stars in the phylum Echinodermata .
Coreopsis gladiata ( coastalplain tickseed ) is a North American species of perennial tickseeds in the sunflower family .
Rabidosa is a genus of spiders described by Roewer ( 1960 ) .
The Transbaikal zokor ( Myospalax psilurus ) is a species of rodents in the family Spalacidae .
Atrociraptor ( meaning `` savage robber '' ) is a genus of dromaeosaurid theropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous ( Maastrichtian stage ) of Alberta , Canada .
Notropis dorsalis , common name bigmouth shiner , is one of the 324 fish species found in Tennessee .
Nepheronia , commonly called vagrants , is a genus of butterflies of the subfamily of Pierinae endemic to Africa .
The Euphaeidae are a family of damselflies in the order Odonata sometimes called Epallaginidae .
Pterocelastrus is a genus of flowering plant in the family Celastraceae .
Piperia cooperi is an uncommon species of orchid known by the common names Cooper 's rein orchid and chaparral rein orchid .
Chrysallida fenestrata is an ectoparasitic species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
The superfamily Cavolinioidea is the most speciose group of sea butterflies .
Heliopsis parvifolia is a North American species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae , known by the common name Mountain oxeye .
Kayentachelys ( `` Kayenta shell '' ) is an extinct genus of stem - turtle from the Early Jurassic Kayenta Formation of northern Arizona .
The Caspian stellate tadpole - goby ( Benthophilus leobergius ) , also known as the starry goby , is a species of gobiid fish endemic to the Caspian Sea basin .
Lestrimelitta limao is a neotropical eusocial bee species found in Brazil and Panama and is part of the Apidae family .
Neoliotomus is a genus of North American mammal from the Paleocene .
Scaphella gouldiana , commonly known as the banded volute is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Chrysomyxa himalensis , ( also called spruce needle rust ) is a species of rust fungi in the Coleosporiaceae family that can be found on Rhododendron and Picea species in the Himalayan region of southern Asia and was introduced in the United States .
Stipa turkestanica is a species of grass in the Poaceae family , endemic to India and Russian central and western Asia .
Solenosmilia variabilis is a species of colonial coral in the family Caryophylliidae .
Helianthus giganteus ( giant sunflower or tall sunflower ) , is a species of Helianthus native to the eastern United States and eastern and central Canada , from Newfoundland west to Alberta south to Minnesota , Mississippi , and South Carolina .
Neobisium maritimum is a species of pseudoscorpions in the Neobisiidae family , and are the only ones in Neobisium genus .
Agnocoris reclairei is a species of bugs from the Miridae family .
Hylaeus sanguinipictus is a bee species endemic to Western Australia .
The genus Savageoceras is a barrandeoceratid first known from the Middle Silurian of Illinois consisting of rapidly enlarging , depressed cyrtocones with a trapazoidal section ; ventral side wider and flatter than dorsal ; sides converging on dorsum .
Uloborus gilvus is a spider species found in Italy and Greece .
Parajubaea torallyi , commonly known as the Palma De Pasobaya or Bolivian Mountain Coconut , is a species of evergreen flowering plant of genus Parajubaea , in the Arecaceae family .
Glandularia gooddingii is a species of flowering plant in the verbena family known by the common name southwestern mock vervain .
Scyrotis granosa is a species of moth of the Cecidosidae family .
Weejasperaspididae ( `` Shields of Wee Jasper '' ) is a family of three extinct acanthothoracid placoderm species indigenous to the Early Devonian of Victoria and New South Wales , Australia .
Xanthocyparis ( synonym Callitropsis ) is a genus of cypresses in the family Cupressaceae , comprising one species native to North America and one native to Vietnam in southeast Asia .
Hemimyzon megalopseos is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Hemimyzon .
Oecomys paricola , also known as the Brazilian oecomys , Brazilian arboreal rice rat , or South Amazonian arboreal rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Oecomys of family Cricetidae .
Hakea cucullata , commonly known as hood - leaved hakea or scallop hakea , is a species of shrub in the family Proteaceae and is endemic to the south - west of Western Australia .
Ellobium aurismidae , common name Midas 's Ear Shell , is a species of medium - sized , air - breathing , saltmarsh snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Ellobiidae .
Uaru fernandezyepezi is a species of cichlid native to South America where it is found in rivers of the Orinoco River basin .
Tomeurus gracilis is a species of poeciliid fish native to South America .
Tenthredinidae is the largest family of sawflies , with well over 7500 species worldwide .
Neocrepidodera transversa is a species of flea beetle from Chrysomelidae family that can be found in everywhere in Europe except for Andorra , Finland , Greece , Latvia , Monaco , Norway , San Marino , Vatican City , and various European islands .
Nelson 's small - eared shrew ( Cryptotis nelsoni ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Toxoptera citricida ( syn . Toxoptera citricidus ) is a species of aphid known by the common names brown citrus aphid , black citrus aphid , and oriental citrus aphid .
Acaena magellanica , commonly called buzzy burr or greater burnet ( cadillo in Spanish ) , is a species of flowering plant whose range includes southern South America and many subantarctic islands .
Dregus glebalis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Dregus .
Orthetrum nitidinerve , also known as Orthetrum baeticum is a freshwater Mediterranean dragonfly species .
Dendrelaphis nigroserratus ( common name : sawtooth - necked bronzeback ) is a species of snake belonging to the bronzebacks ( Dendrelaphis ) .
Ceratops ( meaning `` horn face '' ) is a dubious genus of herbivorous ceratopsian dinosaur which lived during the Late Cretaceous .
Plaxiphora australis is a very small species of chiton in the family Mopaliidae .
Bathyclarias is a genus of airbreathing catfish endemic to Lake Malawi in Africa .
Liatris cokeri , also known as Coker 's gayfeather and sandhills blazing star , is a plant species in the aster family Asteraceae and genus Liatris .
Melodorum leichhardtii or Zig - zag vine , is a plant species of rainforest vines native to eastern Australia .
The Large Aden gerbil ( Gerbillus poecilops ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Stanhopea warszewicziana is a species of orchid found from Costa Rica to western Panama .
Sporogonites was a genus of Lower Devonian land plant with branching axes .
Andrena , commonly called the mining bee , is the largest genus in the family Andrenidae , and is nearly worldwide in distribution , with the notable exceptions of Oceania and South America .
Herpestides is an extinct genus of terrestrial carnivore that was endemic to North Africa and Southern Europe during the Early Miocene subepoch ( 22.4 - -20 mya ) and existed for approximately 2.4 million years .
Sisyrinchium is a large genus of annual to perennial plants of the iris family , native to the New World , whose species are known as blue - eyed grasses .
Dongusaurus is an extinct genus of therocephalian therapsid .
Moitessieriidae is a family of small freshwater snails , aquatic gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Truncatelloidea .
Dorycera syriaca is a species of Ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Dorycera of the family Tephritidae .
Hildenbrandia is a genus of thalloid red alga comprising 26 species .
Plegiocidaris is an extinct genus of echinoid that lived from the Triassic to the Early Cretaceous .
Basilissopsis regina is a species of extremely small deep water sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Seguenziidae .
Zenaspis is an extinct genus of jawless fish which existed during the early Devonian period .
Pteronemacheilus lucidorsum is a species of stone loach endemic to the Irrawaddy Basin , Myanmar .
Major 's pine vole ( Microtus majori ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae found in Caucasus region and its vicinities ( Russia , Georgia , Azerbaijan , Armenia , Turkey , Iran ) .
Carex abrupta is a species of sedge known by the common name abrupt - beaked sedge or abruptbeak sedge .
Brachinus baeticus is a species of ground beetle from the Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Spain .
Acer taurocursum is an extinct maple species in the family Sapindaceae described from a single fossil samara found in Late Eocene akebed sediments exposed in the state of Nevada , US .
Apostichopus is a genus of sea cucumber .
Anisolepis is a small genus of polychrotid lizards .
Formica pacifica is an ant species occupying the Pacific coast of the United States and British Columbia , Canada .
Ectocarpus is a genus of filamentous brown alga ( Heterokontophyta ) that is a model organism for the genomics of multicellularity .
Speleonectes atlantida is a species of eyeless crustacean in the order Nectiopoda .
Aglaia lepiorrhachis is a species of plant in the family Meliaceae .
Centrolene acanthidiocephalum ( common name Santander giant glass frog ) is a species of frog in the Centrolenidae family .
It contains only one species , Pterothrixidia rufella , which is found in France , Spain , Switzerland , Italy , the Balkan Peninsula , Ukraine , Russia , Kazakhstan , Turkey and Iran .
Honckenya peploides , the sea sandwort ( UK ) or seaside sandplant ( Canada ) , is the only species in the genus Honckenya of the flowering plant family Caryophyllaceae .
Cyclopalpia violescens is a species of snout moth in the genus Cyclopalpia .
Nephrotoma quadrifaria is a species of true cranefly found in most of Europe , but absent from the Iberian peninsula .
Kotlassia is an extinct genus of Reptiliomorpha .
Alicellidae is a family of amphipod crustaceans , which live as scavengers in the deep sea ( at depths of 706 - -8,480 metres or 2,316 - -27,822 feet ) , often in association with hydrothermal vents .
Liocarcinus marmoreus , sometimes known as the marbled swimming crab , is a species of crab found in the northern Atlantic Ocean and North Sea .
Dorycera hybrida is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Dorycera of the family Ulidiidae found in France , Ukraine , Greece , and Turkey .
Sophora saxicola is a species of flowering plant in the pea family , Fabaceae , that is endemic to Jamaica .
Melicope quadrangularis ( also called four angle melicope or four - angled pelea ) is a species of plant in the citrus family , Rutaceae .
The Green 's Gem , Libellago greeni , is a species of damselfly in the family Chlorocyphidae .
Agathiceras anceps is a species of Agathiceras , named by Gemmellaro in 1887 .
The Colletidae are a family of bees , and are often referred to collectively as plasterer bees or polyester bees , due to the method of smoothing the walls of their nest cells with secretions applied with their mouthparts ; these secretions dry into a cellophane - like lining .
Leuchtenbergia principis ( agave cactus or prism cactus ) , the sole species of the genus Leuchtenbergia , is a species of cactus .
Thaumeledone gunteri is a species of small , benthic , deep - sea octopus found in the bathyal zone in the Southern Ocean near South Georgia .
Oxypetalum coeruleum is a species of flowering plant , native to South America from southern Brazil to Uruguay .
Pittsfordipterus is a genus of prehistoric eurypterid from the Silurian period in North America .
Ligusticum huteri is a species of flowering plant in the Apiaceae family , endemic to the Serra de Tramuntana on Majorca , Spain .
Abies spectabilis ( East Himalayan fir ) is a conifer species in the family Pinaceae and the genus firs .
Cycas orixensis is an endemic species found in the Indian state of Odisha .
Farfantepenaeus duorarum is a species of marine penaeid shrimp found around Bermuda , along the east coast of the United States and in the Gulf of Mexico .
Cosmochelys is an extinct genus of sea turtle from the Eocene of Africa .
Taxus sumatrana is an evergreen shrub and one of the eight species of the yew .
Pygaeus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived from the early to middle Eocene of Italy .
Gambian pouched rats have become an invasive species on Grassy Key in the Florida Keys , after a private breeder allowed the animals to escape .
Poa sandvicensis is a rare species of grass known by the common name Hawaiian bluegrass .
Monodilepas monilifera is a species of small sea snail or limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Lamprima adolphinae is a species of stag beetle in the Lucanidae family that can be found on New Guinea and Papua .
Russula albidula is a species of mushroom in the Russula genus .
Pogonomyrmex is a genus of harvester ants , occurring primarily in the deserts of North , Central , and South America , with a single endemic species from Haiti .
Phyllophaga nebulosa is a species of june beetle endemic to Jones Lake State Park in North Carolina .
The Red River mudpuppy ( Necturus maculosus louisianensis ) , also called Louisiana waterdog , is a subspecies of mudpuppy .
Psychocidaridae is a family of sea urchins in the order Cidaroida .
Calmonia is an extinct genus of trilobite .
Dicotylichthys punctulatus also known as the Three - bar porcupinefish is a species of porcupinefish endemic to Australia , where it is found in reef environments down to 50 m ( 160 ft ) deep .
Hydrangea paniculata ( panicled hydrangea ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Hydrangaceae native to southern and eastern China , Korea , Japan and Russia ( Sakhalin ) .
Partubiola blancha is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Skeneidae , .
Anoectochilus sandvicensis ( also called Hawaii Jewel - orchid ) is a species of plant in the Orchidaceae family .
Plumeria clusioides is a species of the genus Plumeria in the family Apocynaceae .
Pachyiulus speciosus is a species of millipede from Julidae family that is endemic to Greece .
Dryadocoris apicalis is a species of shield bugs belonging to the family Pentatomidae .
Carabus obsoletus carpathicus is a subspecies of beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in Czech Republic , Moldova , Romania , and Ukraine .
The Stuttering frog is a large species of frog that inhabits temperate and sub - tropical rainforest and wet sclerophyll forest in Australia .
The Lamiales are an order in the asterid group of dicotyledonous flowering plants .
Oligosoma is a genus of small to medium - sized skinks ( family Scincidae ) found only in New Zealand as well as Norfolk and Lord Howe islands .
Xiphactinus ( from Latin and Greek for `` sword - ray '' ) is an extinct genus of large ( 4.5 to 6 m ( 15 to 20 feet ) long ) predatory marine bony fish that lived during the Late Cretaceous .
Auroraceratops , meaning `` dawn horned face '' , is a genus of basal neoceratopsian dinosaur , from the Early Cretaceous ( Aptian age ) of north central China and South Korea .
Prionosciadium saraviki , common name saraviki , is a plant species in the genus Prionosciadium , in the carrot family , Apiaceae .
Physalaemus is a large genus of leptodactylid frogs .
Mycobacterium lacus is a species of bacteria in the Mycobacterium family known to be a causative agent in immunocompetent individuals .
Antispila voraginella is a species of moth of the Heliozelidae family .
Eurotrochilus is an extinct genus of primitive hummingbird .
Aronia melanocarpa , called the black chokeberry , is a North American species of shrubs in the rose family .
Geranium is a genus of 422 species of flowering annual , biennial , and perennial plants that are commonly known as the cranesbills .
Valgus hemipterus is a smallish species of scarab beetle ( family Scarabaeidae ) found in the Northern Hemisphere .
Neoscopelus is a genus of blackchins .
Crassostrea ariakensis , the Suminoe oyster , is a species of true oyster which inhabits intertidal hard grounds and substrate , as well as muddy creeks of warm estuaries throughout the western Pacific .
Paradoxoglanis is a genus of electric catfishes native to Africa where all of the known species are endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Oreomunnea mexicana is a species of plant in the family Juglandaceae , which grows in the tropical rain forests of Mexico , Guatemala , Nicaragua , Costa Rica , and Panama at altitudes from 1 - -1.7 km . Common names include Guayabo amarillo and Remiendo .
Ageneiosus polystictus is a species of driftwood catfish of the family Auchenipteridae .
Argentipallium is a genus of flowering plants in the family Asteraceae .
Bocainella minima is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Bocainella .
Kyitchaungia is a genus of adapiform primate that lived in Asia during the Eocene .
Cheilanthes intertexta , reclassified as Myriopteris intertexta , is a species of lip fern known by the common name coastal lip fern .
Moquinia is a genus of flowering plants in the Moquinia tribe within the sunflower family .
Satyrium coriifolium is a species of orchid endemic to southwestern and southern Cape Province .
Oxystylis is a monotypic genus of flowering plants currently considered a part of the cleome family containing the single species Oxystylis lutea , which is known by the common name spiny caper .
Mangifera odorata ( also called kwini , kuwini mango , Saipan mango , or fragrant mango ) is a species of plant in the family Anacardiaceae .
Paraclinus altivelis , the Topgallant blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny endemic to the Gulf of California where it can be found in the vicinity of reefs at depths of from 7.6 to 30 metres ( 25 to 98 ft ) .
The Plagiorchiida are a large order of flatworms ( synonym is Echinostomida ) .
Clavisybra strandiella is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Clavisybra .
Thriambeutis hemicausta is a species of moth of the family Heliodinidae .
Lycaste macrophylla is a species of terrestrial orchid native to Costa Rica , Nicaragua , Panama , Colombia , Ecuador , Venezuela , Peru and Bolivia .
Cumanotus is a genus of sea slugs , aeolid nudibranchs , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Flabellinidae .
Fangfangia spinocleithralis is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Indonesia where it is found in the peat swamp forests of Kalimantan Tengah , Borneo .
Amolops kangtingensis ( common name : Kangting sucker frog ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family that is endemic to Kangding County in western Sichuan , China .
Hoplocorypha acuta is a species of praying mantis found on Madagascar and in Tanzania .
Procambarus clarkii is a freshwater crayfish species , native to the Southeastern United States , but found also on other continents , where it is often an invasive pest .
Moodna ostrinella , the darker moodna moth , is a species of snout moth in the genus Moodna .
Eucalyptus yarraensis , commonly known as Yarra gum , is a tree species that is endemic to Victoria , Australia .
Georgenthalia is an extinct genus of dissorophoid temnospondyl from the Lower Permian .
Apebusu rubriventris is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Apebusu .
Nectandra krugii , Krug 's sweetwood , is a species of plant in the Lauraceae family .
Ribes montigenum is a species of currant known by the common names mountain gooseberry , alpine prickly currant , western prickly gooseberry , and gooseberry currant .
Oreolalax major ( common lazy toad or large toothed toad ) is a species of amphibian in the Megophryidae family .
Goniobranchus albomaculatus is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Chromodorididae .
Lagenida is an order of benthic foraminiferal protists in which the tests ( shells ) are monolamellar , with walls composed of optically and ultra - structurally radiate calcite , with the crystallographic c - axes perpendicular to the surface .
Balitora annamitica is a species of hill - stream loach from the Mekong River Basin in Cambodia , Thailand , and Laos , and possibly Vietnam .
Chorizanthe is a genus of plants in the buckwheat family known generally as spineflowers .
Paramecium caudatum is a species of unicellular organisms belonging to the genus Paramecium of the phylum Ciliophora .
Brachyhypopomus walteri is a species of electric knifefish .
Heteropoda davidbowie is a species of huntsman spider of the Heteropoda genus .
Carex praticola is a species of sedge known by the common name meadow sedge .
Leptoceratopsidae is an extinct family of neoceratopsian dinosaurs from Asia and North America .
It is endemic to New Caledonia and the only species of the genus Hooglandia .
Ankylomyrma is a genus of large arboreal ants in the subfamily Agroecomyrmecinae .
Mitra papalis , common name the Papal / Pontifical Mitre , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mitridae , the miters .
Mimocoedomea fusca is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimocoedomea .
Oryzias carnaticus or the spotted ricefish are a freshwater -- brackish fish species native to the India , Bangladesh , Sri Lanka , and Myanmar .
Equus stenonis or the Stenon zebra , was a Pleistocene species of zebra , now extinct , that inhabited North America , Europe , North Africa and Asia .
Collenia is genus of fossil cyanobacteria that form a particular type of stromatolites .
Mertensophryne uzunguensis ( common name : Uzungwe toad or Udzungwa toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Ripogonum ( sometimes Rhipogonum ) is a genus of flowering plants confined to eastern Australia , New Zealand , and New Guinea .
Euphorbia palustris ( marsh spurge or marsh euphorbia ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Euphorbiaceae , native to marshland throughout much of mainland Europe and western Asia .
Aechmea aciculosa is an epiphytic species in the genus Aechmea .
Euconulus alderi is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Euconulidae , the hive snails .
Hesperolinon serpentinum ( now Hesperolinon sharsmithae ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the flax family known by the common name Napa dwarf flax , or Napa western flax .
Lactuca biennis is a North American species of wild lettuce known by the common names tall blue lettuce and blue wood lettuce .
Parastrapotherium is an extinct genus of South American land mammal that existed from the Late Oligocene ( Deseadan SALMA ) to the Early Miocene ( Colhuehuapian SALMA ) 28.1 to 23.03 million years ago .
Shewanella is the sole genus included in the Shewanellaceae family of marine bacteria , some species within it were formerly classed as Alteromonas .
Epilobium septentrionale , with the common names Humboldt County fuchsia and northern willowherb , is a species of willowherb .
Werauhia balanophora is a bromeliad species in the genus Werauhia .
Labeobarbus rocadasi is a species of cyprinid fish that occurs in the Nyong River in Cameroon and in the Quanza and Lucalla rivers in Angola .
It was described by Amsel , in 1961 , and contains the species Amechedia pagmanella .
Penicillium oxalicum is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from rhizosphere soil of pearl millet .
Cupeyalia subterranea is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cupeyalia .
Ocotea foetens , commonly called til , tilo , stinkwood , or rain tree of Hierro island , is a species of tree in the Lauraceae family .
Racinaea kessleri is a species in the genus Racinaea .
Loxolexis is an Afrotropical genus of skippers in the family Hesperiidae .
Aetobatus poeyi is an extinct species of eagle ray that lived during the Miocene .
The Middendorff 's grasshopper warbler ( Locustella ochotensis ) is a species of Old World warbler in the Locustellidae family .
Pavonia lasiopetala is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common names that include Texas swamp - mallow , Wright pavonia , and rock rose .
Sthenaster emmae is a species of deep sea corallivores ( preys on deep - sea corals ) .
The Colpodea are a class of ciliates , of about 200 species common in freshwater and soil habitats .
Uruyiella is an extinct genus of laidleriid temnospondyl from Permian or Triassic deposits of Buena Vista Formation of Uruguay .
Nama aretioides is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name ground nama .
Ageratina concordiana is a species of flowering shrub in the sunflower family , native to the State of Sinaloa in northwestern Mexico .
Nirodia belphegor is a butterfly species in the family Lycaenidae and the monotypic genus Nirodia .
Baeocrara is a genus of featherwing beetles named because of the intricate structure of their flight wings , which have a long fringe of hairs on their borders .
Aphonopelma smithi is a relatively skittish species , and can be disturbed easily .
Salinella salve is a dubious species of very simple animal that may not exist , but which some have named as the sole member of the phylum Monoblastozoa .
Ribes thacherianum , with the common name Santa Cruz gooseberry , or Santa Cruz Island gooseberry , is a rare North American species of currant found only on one island off the coast of California .
Zosterogrammidae is an extinct family of millipedes containing three genera , each with a single species .
Haplophyton ( cockroach plant ) is a plant genus in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1844 .
Limonia acidissima is the only species within the monotypic genus Limonia .
Pogogyne serpylloides is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common names thymeleaf mesamint and thymeleaf beardstyle .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Ascofascicula talaroluteoides .
Paratlepolemoides spiniscapus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paratlepolemoides .
Streptomyces kanamyceticus is a bacterial species in the genus Streptomyces .
The material was not described until 2011 , when the new species Spinops sternbergorum was erected .
Antrodia serialiformis is a species of polypore fungus in the family Fomitopsidaceae .
The sole species is Nesocodon mauritianus , formerly known as Wahlenbergia mauritiana , which is endemic to the island of Mauritius .
Agoseris glauca is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common names pale agoseris , prairie agoseris , and short - beaked agoseris .
Rhacophorus turpes ( common name : Htingnan flying frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family endemic to northern Myanmar .
Pseudapomecyna klugii is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudapomecyna .
Ectima is a brush - footed butterfly genus found in South America .
Eutropis andamanensis is a species of skink found in the Andaman Islands of India .
Colchicum baytopiorum is a plant species native to western Turkey and to the Greek Island of Rhodes ( although possibly extinct there ) .
Haliotid herpesvirus 1 is the only known species in the genus Haliotivirus .
Triops cancriformis , or tadpole shrimp , is a species of tadpole shrimp found in Europe to the Middle East and India .
Iris lazica ( Lazistan iris ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Iridaceae , native to the Black Sea Coast of Turkey and southern Georgia , and also cultivated as an ornamental plant in temperate regions .
Echinosphaerites is a genus of rhombiferan echinoderm ( a cystoid ) that lived in the Early and Middle Ordovician of North America and Europe ( Bockelie , 1981 ) .
The Anaeroplasmatales are an order of mollicute bacteria .
Trigonocyttara clandestina is a moth in the Psychidae family , and the only species in the genus Trigonocyttara .
Ephemeridae is a family of mayflies with about 150 described species found throughout the world except Australia and Oceania .
Berberis vulgaris ( European barberry ) is the alternate host species of the wheat rust fungus ( Puccinia graminis ) , a grass - infecting rust fungus that is a serious fungal disease of wheat and related grains .
Chromidotilapiini is a tribe of small cichlids from tropical West and Middle Africa .
Mount Lefo brush - furred mouse ( Lophuromys eisentrauti ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Heteroderinae is a subfamily of roundworms .
Juncus acuminatus is a species of rush known by the common names tapertip rush , tufted rush and sharp - fruited rush .
Caudellia colorella is a species of snout moth in the genus Caudellia .
Krithodeophyton is a genus of lower Devonian plant with branching axes .
Mordellistena amamiensis is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , which is in the Mordellistena genus .
Pododesmus rudis , or the false jingle shell , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Anomiidae .
Megacephala oleadorsa is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Sumlin in 1992 , and is endemic to Australia .
Fabiola quinqueferella is a species of Oecophoridae moth in the genus Fabiola .
Chlorurus perspicillatus , known commonly as the Spectacled Parrotfish , is a species of marine fish in the family Scaridae .
Pandanus boninensis is an Asian species of plant that is endemic to and common in the Distylium - Schima dry forests and Raphiolepsis - Livistona dry forests of the Ogasawara Islands , Japan .
Agalinis skinneriana is a species of flowering plant in the broomrape family known by the common names Skinner 's gerardia , Skinner 's false foxglove and pale false foxglove .
Thoracocharax is a genus of freshwater hatchetfishes found in the Amazon , Orinoco and Paraná basins in South America .
Coryphomys is an extinct genus of rats , known from sub - fossils found on Timor .
Teramulus kieneri , the Keiner 's silverside or vily , is a species of silverside endemic to Madagascar where it is found in rivers .
Xanthium spinosum is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by many common names , including spiny cocklebur , prickly burweed and Bathurst burr .
Ipheion uniflorum is a species of flowering plant , related to the onions , so is placed in the allium subfamily ( Allioideae ) of the Amaryllidaceae .
† Daphnobela minutissima is an extinct species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc with a brown shell measuring approximately 2.5 mm in length .
Lithornis is a genus of extinct paleognathous birds .
Chalybion is a genus of blue mud dauber wasps in the family Sphecidae .
Ytu artemis is a species of myxophagan beetle in the genus Ytu .
Goodyera are a wide - ranging genus of orchid , one of approximately 800 described Orchidaceae genera within that large and diverse family .
Erythronium taylorii is a rare species of flowering plant in the lily family known by the common names Pilot Ridge fawn lily , Taylor 's fawnlily , and Yosemite fawn lily .
Chiayusuchus is an extinct genus of stomatosuchid crocodylomorph .
Goniacodon is an extinct genus from the Paleocene of North America .
Ustilaginomycetes is the class of true smut fungi .
Agathis borneensis , also known as borneo kauri , is a species of conifer in the Araucariaceae family .
Hadogenes is a genus of large African scorpions ( including the worlds longest , Hadogenes troglodytes ) found from South Africa up to Tanzania .
Boehm 's bush squirrel ( Paraxerus boehmi ) is a species of rodents in the family Sciuridae found in Burundi , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Kenya , Rwanda , South Sudan , Tanzania , Uganda , and Zambia .
Abacetus poeciloides is a species of ground beetle , in the subfamily Pterostichinae .
Gyarancita rondoni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Gyarancita .
It contains only one species , Ranohira silvestris , which is found in Madagascar .
Pontederia is a genus of tristylous aquatic plants , members of which are commonly known as pickerel weeds .
Eupoa prima is a species of jumping spider from Vietnam .
Boschniakia is a small genus of three species of parasitic plant in the broomrape family .
Gymnosoma filiola is a Nearctic species of fly in the family Tachinidae .
Hemiculter is a genus of cyprinid fish , consisting of eight species native to fresh water of eastern Asia ( Siberia to Vietnam ) .
Odontomantis planiceps , common names grass mantis and Asian ant mantis ( due to ant mimicry when young ) , is a species of praying mantis .
Asteroceras stellare , the True Star Ammonite , is an extinct species of cephalopod belonging to the Ammonite subclass and to the family Arietitidae .
Actinostachys is a small genus of small ferns originally included in the genus Schizaea .
Lanmaoa fragrans is a rare species of bolete fungus in the family Boletaceae found in Europe .
Acuticryphops is a genus of trilobite that lived during the late Frasnian , particularly between the Lower and Upper Kellwasser horizons .
Trimeresurus gumprechti ( Gumprecht 's green pitviper ) is a species of venomous pitviper endemic to Asia .
Amaranthus fimbriatus is a species of glabrous flowering plant .
Chrysopsis highlandsensis , called the Highlands goldenaster , is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family .
Carex festucacea or fescue sedge is a species of sedge that lives in eastern North America .
Avitabatrachus uliana is the single species in the extinct genus Avitabatrachus , a genus of prehistoric frogs that lived in the Middle Cretaceous .
Eogyrinidae is an extinct family of large , long - bodied tetrapods that lived in the rivers of the Late Carboniferous period .
Ansonia endauensis is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae found in the Endau - Rompin National Park in southern peninsular Malaysia .
Goniothalamus thwaitesii is a species of small tree in the Annonaceae family .
The Hysteriales are an order of fungi in the class Dothideomycetes , subclass Pleosporomycetidae .
Danaoceras is the ancestral genus of the Polyelasmoceratidae and is possibly derived from either Oonoceras or Oocerina of the Oncoceratidae based on similarities of the siphuncle
Saxatilomys is a genus of murid rodent native to central Laos and Vietnam , containing the sole species Saxatilomys paulinae ( commonly known as Pauline 's limestone rat ) .
Hypleurochilus pseudoaequipinnis is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Atlantic ocean .
Chorizanthe ventricosa , common name Priest Valley spineflower , is a plant species endemic to a small region in the Coastal Ranges of west - central California .
Cirriformia tentaculata , is a species of marine polychaete worm in the family Cirratulidae .
Aphanisma is a monotypic genus which contains the sole species Aphanisma blitoides , a rare annual plant known by the common names San Diego coastalcreeper or simply aphanisma .
Eriogonum umbellatum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name sulphurflower buckwheat , or simply sulphur flower .
Buddleja americana is the most widespread of all the Buddleja species native to the Americas , its range extending south from Tamaulipas , Mexico , through Central America and much of the West Indies into South America , reaching eastward to Venezuela , westward as far as the Galapagos , and south to Bolivia .
Endomychidae , or handsome fungus beetles , is a family of beetles with representatives found in all ecozones .
Tilopteridales is an order of brown algae ( class Phaeophyceae ) with isomorphic alternation of generations .
Oxyporus similis is a species of fungus in the Schizoporaceae family .
Phungia rufa is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , which is in the genus Phungia .
Quadrastichus erythrinae Kim , 2004 , ( quadra = four , stichus = line , erythrinae = of erythrina ) is a small parasitoid wasp belonging to the family Eulophidae , but also a secondary phytophage by way of inducing galls on the leaves , stems , petioles and young shoots of various Erythrina species .
Kryptopterus piperatus is a species of Asian glass catfish from northern Sumatra .
Greeneyes are deep - sea aulopiform marine fishes in the small family Chlorophthalmidae .
Apetahia is a genus of plants native to various islands of French Polynesia in the South Pacific .
Buddleja tibetica was a species sunk as Buddleja crispa by Leeuwenberg in 1979 , and treated as such in the subsequent Flora of China ; however , the plant remains widely known by its former epithet in horticulture .
Sagina procumbens is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common names procumbent pearlwort , birdeye pearlwort and matted pearlwort .
Dasypsyllus is a widespread genus of fleas .
Manilkara pleeana ( zapote de costa ) is a species of plant in the Sapotaceae family .
Vallonia parvula or trumpet vallonia is a species of small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Valloniidae .
Lagarostrobos franklinii is a species of conifer native to the wet southwestern corner of Tasmania , Australia .
Astragalus cimae is a species of milkvetch known by the common name Cima milkvetch .
Grammatostomias flagellibarba , is a species of barbeled dragonfish .
Squalius keadicus , is a species of fresh - water fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Salvia mohavensis ( Mojave sage ) is a species of sage endemic to the Mojave Desert .
Agonum belleri , sometimes called Beller 's ground beetle , is a species of ground beetle in the Platyninae subfamily .
Cirsium pulcherrimum , called Wyoming thistle , is a North American species of plants in the thistle tribe within the sunflower family .
Raphitoma is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Raphitomidae .
Dissothrix is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae .
Macropetalichthys is a genus of placoderm fish , named by Norwood and Owen in 1846 ; the name `` Macropetalichthys '' means `` armour - plated fish '' .
Sclerotheca is a genus of plants native to various islands in the South Pacific .
Palaemonetes paludosus , the eastern grass shrimp , is a species of freshwater shrimp from the Eastern United States .
Pseudolithoxus nicoi is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela where it is found in the upper Negro and Casiquiare canal basins .
Dendropsophus labialis is a species of frog in the Hylidae family , known commonly as the Green Dotted Treefrog .
Penicillium citrinum is an anamorph , mesophilic fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which produces tanzawaic acid A - D , ACC , Mevastatin , Quinocitrinine A , Quinocitrinine B , and nephrotoxic citrinin .
Euonymus hamiltonianus is a species of flowering plant in the family Celastraceae known by the common names Hamilton 's spindletree , Himalayan spindle and Hamilton 's spindle .
It consists of only one species Mannina hagnoleuca , which can be found in Mexico .
Turbinidae , the turban snails , are a family of small to large marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Trochoidea .
Heisteria pallida is a plant species in the genus Heisteria found in Brazil .
Bursera stenophylla is a Mexican species of trees in the Frankincense Family in the soapwood order .
Sinopoda forcipata is a species of spider in the family Sparassidae .
Diaporthales is an order of sac fungi .
The Paralithodes californiensis , also known as the spiny king crab and the California king crab , is a species of king crab .
Ptychophorae is a suborder of rhizostome jellyfish , identified in 2013 by Gershwin and Davie .
Menippidae is a family of crabs of the order Decapoda .
Tachina lurida is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that can be found everywhere in Europe , except for Albania , Belarus , Estonia , Ireland , Liechtenstein , Lithuania , Luxembourg , Monaco , San Marino , Scandinavia , Slovenia , Vatican City , and various European islands .
Procetichthys kreffti is a species of flabby whalefish found at depths of around 2,200 metres ( 7,200 ft ) in the Atlantic Ocean .
Box jellyfish ( class Cubozoa ) are cnidarian invertebrates distinguished by their cube - shaped medusae .
Hieracium parryi is a North American plant species in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Lycium fremontii is a species of flowering plant in the nightshade family , Solanaceae , that is native to northwestern Mexico and the southernmost mountains and deserts of California and Arizona in the United States .
Conchaspis capensis is a species of scale insect from South Africa found on Metalasia muricata and Phylica species .
Barbus mimus ( Ewaso Nyiro barb ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Schoenoplectus etuberculatus , Canby 's bulrush , is a plant species native to the United States .
The Selangor pygmy flying squirrel ( Petaurillus kinlochii ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Dimorphostylis echinata is a species of crustacean from the Diastylidae family .
