Viverra leakeyi , also known as Leakey 's civet or the giant civet , is an extinct species of civet .
Puccinellia nuttalliana is a species of grass known by the common name Nuttall 's alkaligrass .
Megalechis picta , the Tail bar armored catfish , Tail bar hoplo or Spotted Hoplo , is a species of catfish of the family Callichthyidae .
Emblemaria hyltoni , the Filament blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found around Belize and Honduras , in the western Atlantic ocean .
Alaria americana is a species of a trematode in a family Diplostomatidae .
Eriogonum thomasii is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Thomas ' buckwheat .
Palaeoapterodytes ictus is an extinct species of penguin from the late Oligocene or early Miocene of Argentina , the only member of its genus .
Lactarius flexuosus is a species of fungus in the Russulaceae family of mushrooms .
Plectritis congesta is a species of flowering plant in the honeysuckle family known by several common names , including shortspur seablush and rosy plectritis .
Sorbus scopulina is a species of rowan that is native to western North America , primarily in the Rocky Mountains .
Mesciniodes subinfractalis is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Mesciniodes .
Moschowhaitsia is an extinct genus of theriodont .
Difflugia is the largest genus of Arcellinida , one of several groups of Tubulinea within the eukaryote supergroup Amoebozoa .
Quercus xalapensis , or xalapa oak , is a species of oak in the red oak group ( Quercus section Lobatae ) .
The Usambara eagle - owl , also called the nduk eagle - owl or Vosseier 's eagle - owl , ( Bubo vosseleri ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Gobionellus is a genus of gobies native to fresh , marine and brackish waters along the Atlantic and Pacific coasts of the Americas .
Megacephala castelnaui is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Sloane in 1906 , and is endemic to Australia .
Euryxanthops chiltoni is a species of crab found in the New Zealand Exclusive Economic Zone .
Fissurella barbouri is a species of small sea snail or true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Kadua cookiana ( formerly Hedyotis cookiana ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common names ' awiwi and Cook 's bluet .
Ammannia baccifera , also known as the monarch redstem or blistering ammannia is a species in the family Lythraceae .
Pterostichus morio is a species of ground beetles in the subfamily Pterostichinae .
Rhynchonelloidella smithi is a species of extinct , small - sized brachiopod , a marine rhynchonellate lampshell in the family Rhynchonellidae .
The fan mussel , Atrina fragilis , is a species of large saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Pinnidae , the pen shells .
Lagerstroemia speciosa ( giant crape - myrtle , Queen 's crape - myrtle , banabá plant for Philippines , or Pride of India ) is a species of Lagerstroemia native to tropical southern Asia .
Tritomegas bicolor , the pied shield bug , is a species of shield bug found in Europe .
Gomphus septima ( Septima 's clubtail ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Gomphidae .
Mimonemophas quadrifasciatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimonemophas .
Pseudovanilla is a genus of orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) belonging to the subfamily Vanilloideae .
Tor tor , commonly known as the tor mahseer or tor barb , is a species of cyprinid fish found in fast - flowing rivers and streams with rocky bottoms in Bangladesh , Bhutan , India , Nepal , and Pakistan .
Latrodectus hesperus , the western black widow spider or western widow , is a venomous spider species found in western regions of North America .
Prionobutis is a genus of sleeper gobies native to Borneo and Papua New Guinea .
Pseudis paradoxa , known as the paradoxical frog or shrinking frog , is a species of hylid frog from South America .
Cymbium cymbium , commonly known as the false elephant 's snout volute , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Motandra is a genus of plant in the Apocynaceae family native to tropical Africa .
Streptoglossa is a genus of Australian plants in the inula tribe within the daisy family .
Gongora aromatica is a species of orchid found in Colombia , Costa Rica , Ecuador , Mexico , Nicaragua , Panama and Peru .
Nicolasia is a genus of African flowering plants in the spikenard tribe within the daisy family .
Agyneta metropolis is a species of sheet weaver found in Kenya .
Leptobrotula breviventralis is a species of cusk - eel found in the Indian Ocean off the coast of Africa and in the Pacific Ocean around the Hawaiian Islands .
Phacelia humilis , with the common name low phacelia , is a species of phacelia .
Hoplobatrachus tigerinus , the Indus Valley bullfrog or Indian bullfrog , popular name Asian bullfrog , Asean bullfrog or Asia bullfrog , is a large species of frog found in Myanmar , Bangladesh , India , Pakistan , Afghanistan , and Nepal .
Suncus is a genus of shrews in the family Soricidae .
Zabrus robustus is a species of ground beetle in the Pelor subgenus that is endemic to Greece .
Euchilichthys dybowskii is a species of upside - down catfish native to Cameroon , Central African Republic and the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it is found in the Dja and Ubangi Rivers and rivers of the eastern Congo Basin .
Niveoscincus is a genus of skinks ( family Scincidae ) , commonly called snow skinks or cool - skinks and residing mainly in Tasmania or Victoria , Australia .
Phallus duplicatus ( common name , netted stinkhorn or wood witch ) is a species of fungus in the stinkhorn family .
Leptotyphlops distanti is a species of snake in the family Leptotyphlopidae .
Angraecum bancoense is a species of comet orchid that can be found in Cameroon , the Central African Republic , the Republic of the Congo , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Equatorial Guinea , Gabon , Ghana , Guinea , Liberia , Nigeria , Rwanda , São Tomé and Principe and Sierra Leone .
Saurillodon was a genus of prehistoric lizard of the Late Jurassic Morrison Formation of Western North America .
Buddleja longifolia is a species now restricted to remnants of montane forest in Loja , Ecuador , and northern Peru at altitudes of 2100 -- 2600 m. The species was first described and named by Kunth in 1818 .
Mertensia ciliata is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names tall fringed bluebells , mountain bluebells , and streamside bluebells .
The Bopyridae are a family of isopod crustaceans in the suborder Cymothoida .
Gambusia is a large genus of fish in family Poeciliidae ( order Cyprinodontiformes ) .
Carabus obsoletus fossulifer is a subspecies of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that might be extinct throughout Europe .
Varanus rainerguentheri , commonly known as Rainer Günther 's monitor , is a species of lizard , which is a member of the mangrove monitor species - complex .
Genicanthus lamarck , commonly called Blackstriped Angelfish or Lamarck 's Angelfish among various vernacular names , is a species of marine fish in the family Pomacanthidae .
Carinoclodia anancyloides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Carinoclodia .
Aralia stipulata is a species native to China .
Horaglanis is a genus of airbreathing catfishes endemic to India .
Nidara is a genus of moths belonging to the subfamily Drepaninae from Madagascar .
Ptiliinae is the largest subfamily of feather - winged beetles ( family Ptilidae ) .
Subulites is a genus of fossil sea snails , mud - dwelling marine gastropod mollusks known from the early - middle Ordovician , apparently allied with the Caenogastropoda .
Erigeron nanus is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name dwarf fleabane .
Xylosma flexuosa , commonly known as brushholly or coronilla , is a species of flowering plant in the willow family , Salicaceae , that is native to southern North America and northern South America .
Austrolittorina antipodum ( Philippi , 1847 ) , known as the Banded periwinkle is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Littorinidae , the winkles or periwinkles , found in New Zealand .
Phillyrea latifolia , commonly known as green olive tree or mock privet , is a species of tree in the family Oleaceae .
Planococcus citri , commonly known as the citrus mealybug , is a species of mealybugs native to Asia .
Caprella linearis is a species of skeleton shrimp in the genus Caprella .
Phylogenetic and chemotaxonomic analyses have shown that the strain ATCC 19623 from the species Zoogloea ramigera belongs not to this species but to a new species Crabtreella saccharophila .
Calliostoma javanicum , common name the chocolate - lined top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Catostylidae is a family of small jellyfish .
Cryptoblabes adoceta , the sorghum head moth , is a species of snout moth in the genus Cryptoblabes .
Stenaelurillus darwini is a jumping spider species found in Tanzania .
Lates longispinis , also known as the Rudolf lates or Turkana perch , is a species of latid fish that is endemic to Lake Turkana ( formerly known as Lake Rudolf ) in Kenya and Ethiopia .
Achatinella valida is an extinct species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Achatinellidae .
Haworthia fasciata is a species of succulent plant from the Eastern Cape Province , South Africa .
Macropraonetha pterolophioides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Macropraonetha .
The Bracted Dendrobium ( Dendrobium bracteosum ) is a species of orchid .
Synodontis waterloti is a species of upside - down catfish native to waters of western Africa .
Gobiops is an extinct genus of temnospondyl from the Jurassic of Mongolia , China , and possibly Kyrgyzstan .
Haplochromis dentex is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria , but has not been seen since 1987 .
Parapsycharium is a genus of moth in the Somabrachyidae family containing only one species Parapsycharium paarlense , which is known from South Africa .
Dendrelaphis caudolineatus is a common species of colubrid snake known commonly as the striped bronzeback or bronze tree snake .
Lupinus littoralis is a species of lupine known by the common name seashore lupine .
Arius jella ( blackfin sea catfish ) is a species of fish .
Adenocaulon is a small genus of flowering plants in the daisy family known generally as trailplants .
Melanochromis simulans is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it occurs in the Masinje Rocks and at Cape Ngombo .
Hydrophis inornatus , commonly known as the plain sea snake , is a species of venomous sea snake in the family Elapidae .
Haplochromis thuragnathus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria in Africa .
Pinctada margaritifera , commonly known as the Black - Lip Pearl Oyster , is a species of pearl oyster , a saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Pteriidae .
Chicoreus virgineus , common name the virgin murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Allium constrictum , the Grand Coulee Onion , is a plant species endemic to the US State of Washington .
Opisthacanthus africanus is a species of African scorpion .
Potamogeton crispus , the curled pondweed or curly - leaf pondweed , is a species of aquatic plant native to Eurasia but an introduced species and often a noxious weed in North America .
Pappophorum vaginatum is a species of grass known by the common name whiplash pappusgrass .
Pseudogenes ornaticeps is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudogenes .
Drosera marchantii is an erect perennial tuberous species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera .
The order Ostreoida includes the true oysters .
Chaetosphaerella is a genus of fungi within the Chaetosphaerellaceae family .
Tropheops novemfasciatus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it prefers sheltered bays with rocks and vegetation , usually within 4 metres ( 13 ft ) of the surface .
Hymenocallis occidentalis is a plant species native to the southern United States .
Scincella palnica is a species of skink .
The Tamaulipas pygmy owl ( Glaucidium sanchezi ) is a species of owl in the Strigidae family .
Xyrichtys is a genus of wrasses native to the Atlantic , Indian and Pacific Oceans , where they are found in sandy - bottomed habitats .
Ctenosauriscus is an extinct genus of sail - backed poposauroid archosaur from Early Triassic deposits of Lower Saxony in northern Germany .
Clepsis dumicolana is a moth species of the family Tortricidae .
Atyidae is a family of shrimp , present in all tropical and most temperate waters of the world .
Kwangsisaurus is an extinct genus of a basal pistosauroid known from the Early or Middle Triassic ( Olenekian or Anisian age ) of Guangxi , southern China .
Pachydermata ( from two Greek words παχύς pachys , `` thick '' and δερμα derma , `` skin '' , meaning ' thick skin ' ) is an obsolete order of mammals described by Gottlieb Storr , Georges Cuvier and others , at one time recognized by many systematists .
Cotinis orientalis is a species of the Cotinis scarab genus .
One genus , Prolagus , is recognised within the family , which was previously considered a subfamily of Ochotonidae , as Prolaginae .
Crassispira is a genus of small predatory sea snails with narrow , high - spired shells , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pseudomelatomidae .
Timon princeps is a species of Timon which belongs to the family of Lacertidae , the wall lizards .
Convolvulus althaeoides is a species of morning glory known by the common names mallow bindweed and mallow - leaved bindweed .
Schizosaccharomyces is a genus of fission yeasts .
Elaeocarpus amoenus is a species of flowering plant in the Elaeocarpaceae family used as a medicinal plant .
Labrisomus bucciferus , the Puffcheek blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the western Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea .
Agyneta natalensis is a species of sheet weaver found in South Africa .
Diplura fasciata is a species of funnel - web tarantulas belonging to the subfamily Diplurinae .
Trifolium wormskioldii is a species of clover native to the western half of North America from Alaska , through California , to Mexico .
Junonia hierta , the yellow pansy , is a species of nymphalid butterfly found in the Palaeotropics .
Phyllostegia mollis , the Waianae Range phyllostegia , is a species of flowering plant in the mint family , Lamiaceae , that is endemic to Hawaiʻi .
Hamatastus simillimus is a species of longhorn beetle in the Cerambycidae family .
Technomyrmex horni is a species of Dolichoderine ant which is a widespread species that can be found in many Indo - Australian , Oriental , and Palaearctic regions .
Phlegethontia is an extinct genus of lepospondyl amphibian from the Carboniferous and Permian periods of Europe and North America .
Aloe aculeata ( common names include ngopanie , sekope , red hot poker aloe ) is an Aloe species that is native to the Limpopo valley and Mpumalanga in South Africa along with southern and central Zimbabwe and Mozambique .
Nes longus , the Orangespotted goby , is a species of goby native to the tropical Atlantic coast of the Americas where it prefers silty bottoms around reefs .
The Ankober serin ( Crithagra ankoberensis ) is a species of finch in the Fringillidae family .
Podocarpus drouynianus is a species of podocarp native to the relatively high rainfall southwestern corner of Western Australia , where it is known by the name Wild Plum , although it is not a true plum .
Nitidella nitida , common name : the glossy dove shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae , the dove snails .
Salix sitchensis is a species of willow known by the common name Sitka willow .
Schinus polygama , the Hardee peppertree or Chilean pepper tree , is a species of plant in the Anacardiaceae family which is native to Argentina and Chile and naturalized in California .
The family Thermodesulfobiaceae according to the LPSN is located within the order Thermoanaerobacterales and class Clostridia .
Phalaenopsis pulcherrima is a species of orchid found from Hainan Island to western Malesia .
The Papuan mountain pigeon ( Gymnophaps albertisii ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Heterostraci ( `` Different scales '' ) is an extinct subclass of pteraspidomorph jawless vertebrate that lived primarily in marine and estuary environments .
Eremosyne pectinata , the sole species in the genus Eremosyne , is an annual herb endemic to the south coast of Western Australia .
Uria is a genus of seabirds in the auk family known in Britain as guillemots , in most of North America as murres , and in Newfoundland and Labrador as turr .
Agriolimacidae is a family of small and medium - sized land slugs , or shell - less snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks .
It contains only one species , Calleremites subornata , which is found in China and India ( Sikkim ) .
Myrsine fosbergii , the Koolau Range colicwood , is a species of plant in the Primulaceae family .
Sorbus cashmiriana ( Kashmir rowan ) , is a species of flowering plant in the family Rosaceae , native to the western Himalayas , including Kashmir .
Quercus alba is sometimes confused with the swamp white oak , a closely related species , and the bur oak .
The Madagascan mannikin ( Lonchura nana ) is a common species of estrildid finch native to Madagascar .
Diaphanos is a genus of butterflies in the Nymphalidae family .
Polypogon monspeliensis , commonly known as annual beard - grass or annual rabbitsfoot grass , is a species of grass .
Douvilleiceras is a genus of ammonites from the Cretaceous .
Ficus coronata , commonly known as the sandpaper fig or creek sandpaper fig , is a species of fig tree , native to Australia .
Colaspidea oblonga is a species of beetle in the Chrysomelidae family that can be found on Balearic Islands and Crete .
Odontamblyopus rebecca is a species of eel goby native to marine and brackish waters of Vietnam .
Erinaceusyllis , previously known as Sphaerosyllis ( Claparède , 1863 ) , is a genus belonging to the phylum Annelida , a group known as the segmented worms .
Isocarpha oppositifolia , the Rio Grande pearlhead , is a New World species of plants in the sunflower family .
Bermudamysis speluncola is a species of crustacean in the family Mysidae , endemic to Bermuda , and the only species in the genus Bermudamysis .
Solidago ludoviciana , the Louisiana goldenrod , is a North American plant species in the sunflower family native to Louisiana , Texas and Arkansas .
Apedolepis is a genus of prehistoric jawless fish which lived during the Ordovician period .
Fungi of the order Chytridiales , like other members of its division , may either have a monocentric thallus or a polycentric rhizomycelium .
Rhantus tigris is a species of water beetle in the Dytiscidae family .
The Tanna fruit dove ( Ptilinopus tannensis ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Marah fabaceus , the California manroot or bigroot , is the most common of the manroot species native to California .
Penstemon alluviorum , known by the common name lowland beardtongue , is a species of flowering plant in the veronica family .
Rickia wasmannii is a species of the widely distributed entomoparasitic order of fungi Laboulbeniales .
Saussurea americana is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name American saw - wort .
The Andean goose is a grazing species , eating grasses .
The Texas garter snake ( Thamnophis sirtalis annectens ) is a subspecies of the common garter snake ( T. sirtalis ) endemic to the United States .
Primula pulverulenta , the mealy cowslip , is a species of flowering plant in the family Primulaceae , native to damp habitats in China .
Delphinium polycladon is a species of larkspur known by the common name mountain marsh larkspur .
Amaranthus hybridus , commonly called green amaranth , slim amaranth , smooth amaranth , smooth pigweed , or red amaranth , is a species of annual flowering plant .
Odaxothrissa , the fangtooth pellonulines , is a genus of fresh - water fish in the herring family , Clupeidae .
Calliobasis bilix , common name the balanced top shell , is a species of extremely small deep water sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Seguenziidae .
Nectophryne ( African tree toads ) is a small genus of true toads with only two species .
Acromis spinifex is a species of tortoise beetle from South America .
Callistege is a genus of moths in the Erebidae family .
The Metagoniolithoideae are a monogeneric subfamily of genucilate Corallinaceaen Coralline alga .
Notylia sagittifera is a species of orchid that occurs from Colombia , Venezuela , the Guianas and northeastern Brazil .
Scaphander otagoensis is a species of sea snail , a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Scaphandridae , the canoe bubbles .
Zygoballus remotus is a species of jumping spider which occurs in Guatemala .
Nostoc pruniforme ( Mare 's eggs ) are a species of cyanobacterium .
Meroptera abditiva is a species of snout moth in the genus Meroptera .
Ephedra intermedia , with the Chinese common name of Zhong Ma Huang , is a species of Ephedra that is native to Siberia , Central Asia , Iran , Afghanistan , Pakistan , the western Himalayas , Tibet , Mongolia , and China .
Stilpnophyllum grandifolium is a species of tree in the Rubiaceae family .
Buddleja coriacea is a variable species endemic to the high Andes from the Cordillera Blanca in Peru to Lake Titicaca in Bolivia .
Stegops is an extinct genus of euskelian temnospondyl from the Late Carboniferous of the eastern United States .
Sordaria macrospora is a species of microscopic fungus .
Laothoe austanti , the Maghreb poplar hawkmoth , is a species of moth of the Sphingidae family .
Crataegus coccinioides is a species of hawthorn known by the common names Kansas hawthorn and large - flowered cockspurthorn .
Panagaeus fasciatus is a species of ground beetle in the Panagaeinae subfamily that can be found in the US and Canada .
Graecoanatolica conica is a species of freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Ceratosuchus is an extinct genus of alligatorine crocodylian from latest Paleocene rocks of Colorado 's Piceance Basin and earliest Eocene rocks of Wyoming 's Bighorn Basin in North America , a slice of time known as the Clarkforkian North American Land Mammal Age .
Rimicola is a genus of clingfishes found along the coasts of the eastern Pacific Ocean .
Callionymus marquesensis is a species of dragonet native to the Pacific Ocean around the Marquesan Islands .
Collared wrigglers are perciform fishes in the family Xenisthmidae .
Thersistrombus thersites , common name : the Thersite Conch , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Haemaphysalis concinna is a common rodent tick species that originally predominantly occurred in Russia and Eastern Europe , but is also known from Japan , China , Germany and France .
Streptomyces lavendulae is a species of bacteria from the genus Streptomyces .
Woolly aphids ( subfamily : Eriosomatinae ) are sucking insects that live on plant fluids and produce a filamentous waxy white covering which resembles cotton or wool .
Diploon is a genus of plant in the Sapotaceae family described as a genus in 1946 .
Aromobates mayorgai ( common name : Mayorga rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Oncidium amictum is a species of orchid endemic to southeastern Brazil .
Harpalus saxicola is a species of ground beetle native to Palaearctic and Near East .
Lioptilodes tribonia is a species of moth in the genus Lioptilodes , known from Chile and Peru .
Typhis sejunctus , common name the frilly typhis , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Dillwynella texana is an extinct species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Skeneidae .
Hancockiidae is a family of sea slugs , nudibranchs , marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Tritonioidea .
Sisyrinchium funereum is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the iris family known by the common names Funeral Mountain blue - eyed grass and Death Valley blue - eyed - grass .
Clarkichthys bilineatus , the Flagtail wormfish , is a species of wormfish native to the Pacific coast of the Americas from Mexico to Colombia as well as the Galapagos Islands .
Cerradomys langguthi is a species of rodent from South America in the genus Cerradomys .
Cupressus stephensonii is a species of conifer known as the Cuyamaca cypress , and endemic to California .
Persoonia asperula , commonly known as mountain geebung , is a species in the family Proteaceae .
Garberia is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the aster family , Asteraceae , containing the single species Garberia heterophylla .
Witaaspis was an extinct genus of osteostraci fish that lived in the Wenlock and Ludlow stages of the Silurian period .
Vandiemenia ratkowskiana is the only species of liverwort in the genus Vandiemenia .
Protonemacheilus longipectoralis is a species of hillstream loach that is endemic to China .
Phomopsis longicolla is a species of ascomycota fungi in the Diaporthaceae family .
Memecylon tirunelvelicum is a plant species endemic to the Tinurelveli Hills in Tamil Nadu , India .
Laganosuchus is an extinct genus of stomatosuchid crocodyliform .
Zaireichthys camerunensis is a species of loach catfish found in Cameroon and Guinea in the Niger River basin .
Neritilia manoeli is a species of minute freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Neritiliidae .
Gamochaeta coarctata , gray everlasting , is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
The leopard tree iguana , Liolaemus leopardinus , is a species of lizard in the Iguanidae family .
Leptolalax heteropus ( Malaysian Asian toad or variable litter frog ) is a frog species in the family Megophryidae .
Eupackardia calleta , commonly known as the Calleta silkmoth , is a species of moth in the Saturniidae family .
Paramphistomum is a genus of parasitic flat worm belonging to the digenetic trematodes .
Tachina corylana is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to Latvia .
Ixodonerium is a genus of flowering plants in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1933 .
Megalobulimus popelairianus , synonym Strophocheilus popelairianus , is a species of tropical air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Strophocheilidae .
Euglossa jacquelynae is a Euglossine bee species found in Central Brazil .
Cheilanthes newberryi is a species of lip fern known by the common name Newberry 's lip fern .
Dendroplex is a genus of bird in the woodcreeper subfamily ( Dendrocolaptinae ) .
Pleurobranchella is a genus of sea slugs , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pleurobranchaeidae .
Linckia guildingi , also called the common comet star , Guilding 's sea star or the green Linckia , is a species of sea star found in the shallow waters of the tropical Pacific Ocean , Indian Ocean , Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea .
Protylopus is an extinct genus of camel that lived during middle to late Eocene some 45 - 40 million years ago in North America .
Phylloporus pelletieri , commonly known as the golden - gilled bolete , is a species of fungus in the Boletaceae family .
The Fülleborn 's longclaw ( Macronyx fuellebornii ) , also spelled Fuelleborn 's longclaw is a species of bird in the Motacillidae family .
Hirthia littorina is a species of tropical freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Paludomidae .
Dusicyon avus is an extinct species in the genus Dusicyon .
Conus princeps , common name the prince cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Gastrodiscoides is genus of zoonotic fluke under the class Trematoda .
Amsinckia menziesii is a species of plant in the Boraginaceae family , the borage or forget - me - not family .
Tusciziphius is an extinct genus of ziphiidae cetacean .
Solidago riddellii , Riddell 's goldenrod , is a North American plant species in the genus Solidago of the sunflower family .
Limatulichthys , is a genus of the family Loricariidae of catfish .
Arctium is a genus of biennial plants commonly known as burdock , family Asteraceae .
Tarsonemidae is a family of mites , also called thread - footed mites or white mites .
Pisidium moitessierianum is a species of minute freshwater clam .
Phyllomacromia bispina is a species of dragonfly in the family Corduliidae .
Mannophryne collaris ( common name : collared poison frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
The Samwell Cave cricket is an undescribed species of insect in the family Rhaphidophoridae , which is endemic to California .
Conasprella stearnsii , common name Stearn 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
The Javan munia ( Lonchura leucogastroides ) is a species of estrildid finch found in Southern Sumatra , Java , Bali and Lombok , Indonesia .
Prunus campanulata is a species of cherry native to Japan , Vietnam , and China ( including Taiwan ) , widely grown as an ornamental tree , and a symbol of Nago , Okinawa in the Ryukyu Islands of Japan .
Dalea mollis is a species of flowering plant in the legume family which is known by the common name hairy prairie clover .
Penthus tenebrioides is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Penthus .
Schoenolirion , rush - lily or sunnybell , is a genus of three recognized species of flowering plants , all endemic to the southeastern United States .
Suillia hispanica is a European species of Heleomyzidae .
The only species is Dendrosicyos socotranus , the cucumber tree .
Histiodraco velifer is a species of barbeled plunderfish native to the marine waters around Antarctica where it is found at depths of from 210 to 667 metres ( 689 to 2,188 ft ) .
Chrysina gloriosa is a species of scarab whose common names are glorious beetle and glorious scarab .
Chione cancellata , is a species of medium - sized saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Veneridae , the venus clams .
Petersius conserialis is a species of fish in the Alestidae family , and the sole member of the genus Petersius .
The Sicydiinae are a small subfamily ( about 118 species ) of freshwater gobies , with only nine genera .
Heterotheca canescens , hoary goldenaster , is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family .
Peltanthera is a genus of flowering plants containing a single species , P. floribunda .
Tetropismenus hirtus is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Tetropismenus of the family Ulidiidae .
Oecanthus is a genus of cricket in subfamily Oecanthinae , the tree crickets .
Latabryna arnaudi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Latabryna .
Flower of the Andes ( Chuquiraga jussieui ) is a species of flowering plant in the Asteraceae family .
Penicillium marinum is a species of the genus of Penicillium which produces patulin and roquefortine C.
Condorraptor ( meaning robber or snatcher from Cerro Condor ) is a genus of megalosauroid theropod dinosaur .
Chaperina fusca ( common names : brown thorny frog , spiny - heeled froglet , saffron - bellied frog ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Elassoma evergladei , or the Everglades pygmy sunfish , is a species of fish from the genus Elassoma ( the pygmy sunfishes ) that is endemic to North America .
Brachycentridae is a family of insect in the order Trichoptera .
Gongpoquansaurus ( meaning `` Gongpoquan reptile '' ) is an extinct genus of basal hadrosauroid dinosaur that was not formally named until 2014 , while the name was a nomen nudum for many years previously .
Calymene niagarensis is a species of trilobite belonging to the genus Calymene .
Tetronarce tremens also known as the Chilean torpedo is a species of fish in the Torpedinidae family .
Eurycleidus is an extinct genus of large - bodied rhomaleosaurid known from the Early Jurassic period ( most likely earliest Hettangian stage ) of the United Kingdom .
Neocaphys purpuralis is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Neocaphys .
Angelica californica is a species of angelica known as California angelica .
The Diprotodontidae are an extinct family of large marsupials , endemic to what would be Australia , during the Oligocene through Pleistocene periods from 28.4 million to 11,000 years ago .
Compsocus is a genus within the Psocoptera order of insects .
Masdevallia bulbophyllopsis is a species of orchid endemic to southwestern Ecuador .
Streptomyces heliomycini is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil . Streptomyces heliomycini produces heliomycin .
Phalium flammiferum , the Striped Bonnet , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cassidae , the helmet snails and bonnet snails .
Albuca fastigiata is a plant species in the genus Albuca native to the Cape Provinces of South Africa , where it is used in ethnomedicine .
Acianthera is a genus of orchids native to the tropical parts of the Western Hemisphere , especially Brazil .
Limax dacampi ( by other authors Limax dacampoi ) is a species of air - breathing land slug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Limacidae , the keelback slugs .
Parapoynx stagnalis , the rice case bearer or rice caseworm , is a species of moth in the Crambidae family .
Acrosticta wytsmani is a species of ulidiidae , or picture - winged fly , in the genus Acrosticta of the family Ulidiidae .
Ameerega is a genus of poison dart frogs in the family Dendrobatidae .
Eoplatax is an extinct genus of prehistoric spadefish that lived during the Lutetian of Monte Bolca .
Nelumbo nucifera , also known as Indian lotus , sacred lotus , bean of India , or simply lotus , is one of two species of aquatic plant in the family Nelumbonaceae .
Magnolia delavayi is a species of flowering plant in the genus Magnolia native to southern China , occurring in Guizhou , Sichuan and Yunnan at 1,500 - 2,800 m altitude .
Ottelia acuminata , is a plant species endemic to Southern China .
Tomichia natalensis is a species of very small freshwater snails which have a gill and an operculum , gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Pomatiopsidae .
Orthocarpus bracteosus is a species of flowering plant in the broomrape family known by the common name rosy owl's - clover .
Sphaeralcea rusbyi is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common names Rusby 's globemallow and Rusby 's desert - mallow .
Macroplacus is an extinct genus of placodont reptiles .
Slopalinida is a Stramenopila order .
Acremodonta crassicosta is a species of minute , deep - water sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc or micromollusk in the family Ataphridae , the false top snails or false top shells .
Mimoblennius cas is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian ocean , around Comoros .
Lactuca perennis , common names : mountain lettuce , blue lettuce or perennial lettuce , is a perennial herbaceous plant species belonging to the genus Lactuca of the daisy family .
Emucarididae is an extinct family of soft - shelled trilobite - like arthropods ( nektaspids ) from the Lower Cambrian of South Australia and South China .
Caryodaphnopsis cogolloi is a species of plant in the Lauraceae family endemic to Colombia .
Latia neritoides is a species of small freshwater snail or limpet , an aquatic gastropod mollusc in the family Latiidae .
Kudekanye suidafrika is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Kudekanye .
Lunella granulata , common name the granulated moon turban , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Araneus sericinus is an orb - weaver spider species found in Portugal and Spain
The Darling Downs hopping mouse ( Notomys mordax ) is an extinct species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Glover 's pika ( Ochotona gloveri ) is a species of mammal in the family Ochotonidae .
Ollaphon is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Fasciolariidae , the spindle snails , the tulip snails and their allies .
Iris virginica , with the common name Virginia iris , is a perennial species of flowering plant , native to eastern North America .
Olearia glutinosa , commonly known as the Sticky Daisy - bush , is a species of plant in the Asteraceae family .
Phausis reticulata , commonly referred to as the `` blue ghost '' is a species of firefly found in the eastern and central United States .
Eleutherodactylus ruthae ( common name : Ruth 's robber frog ) is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family .
Solariella nuda , common name the naked solarelle , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Solariellidae .
Cupressus nevadensis , now reclassified as ' Hesperocyparis nevadensis , with the common name Paiute cypress , is a species of cypress tree native to a small area in Sierra Nevada of California , in the western United States .
Thermococcus kodakarensis is a species of thermophilic archaea .
Bomarea chimborazensis is a species of flowering plant in the family Alstroemeriaceae .
Scaphiophryne marmorata is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family commonly known as the green burrowing frog and the marbled rain frog .
Triticum compactum erinaceum , also called California Club Wheat or Mayview wheat , is an extinct subspecies of the hexaploid club wheat Triticum compactum .
Chigutisauridae is an extinct family of large temnospondyl amphibians .
Lepidopleurus inquinatus is a species of chiton in the family Leptochitonidae .
Oncidium lentiginosum is a species of orchid occurring from Colombia to northern Venezuela .
The sole species is Nechamandra alternifolia .
Medlicottiidae is a family of ammonoid cephalopods belonging to the Prolecanitida , known from the Upper Carboniferous ( Pennsylvanian ) to the Early Triassic .
Musculium lacustre is a species of small freshwater clam , an aquatic bivalve mollusc in the family Sphaeriidae , the fingernail clams and pea clams .
Lupinus obtusilobus is a species of lupine known by the common name bluntlobe lupine .
Heterochrosis oligochrodes is a species of snout moth in the genus Heterochrosis .
Ogilvia pulverealis is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Ogilvia .
Lophosceles is a small genus from the fly family Muscidae .
Dioscoreales ( yam order ) is a botanical name for an order of monocotyledon flowering plants in modern classification systems , such as the Angiosperm Phylogeny Group and the Angiosperm Phylogeny Web .
Hydrolea ovata is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names ovate false fiddleleaf and blue waterleaf .
Glyceria leptostachya is a species of mannagrass known by the common names davy mannagrass and narrow mannagrass .
Luzonichthys is a genus of marine fish in family Serranidae .
Ericameria cooperi ( Cooper 's goldenbush ) is a North American species of shrubs that grows in the desert regions of southern Nevada , southern and eastern California , and Baja California .
Julia exquisita is a species of very small sea snail with a shell comprising two separate hinged pieces or valves .
Only one species is described , Condorchelys antiqua .
Ischadium recurvum , known as the `` hooked mussel '' or `` bent mussel , '' is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Mytilidae .
Andreaea gainii is a species of moss that lives in western Antarctica and on the South Shetland Islands .
Diastocera trifasciata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Diastocera .
Pygopristis denticulata is a species of serrasalmidae .
Eremiaphila persica is a species of praying mantis found in Turkey , Iran , and Azerbaijan .
Austromorium is an Australian genus of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Rhynchohyalus natalensis , the Glasshead barreleye , is a species of barreleye found in oceans around the world at depths from 247 to 549 metres ( 810 to 1,801 ft ) .
Lycodon cardamomensis , also known as the Cardamom Mountains wolf snake , is a species of non - venomous colubrid snake found in south - western Cambodia and south - eastern Thailand .
Metatrophis margaretae is a species of plant in the family Urticaceae .
Penicillium waksmanii is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from the alga Sargassum ringgoldianum . Penicillium waksmanii produces pyrenocine A , pyrenocine C , pyrenocine D and pyrenocine E
Rhinella achalensis is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae that is endemic to northern Argentina ( Córdoba and San Luis provinces ) .
Malus ioensis , or the prairie crabapple , is a species of crabapple tree native to the United States .
Oligoneuron is a small genus of flowering plants in the sunflower family ( Asteraceae ) .
Dicyemida , or Rhombozoa , is a phylum of tiny parasites that live in the renal appendages of cephalopods .
Achroia is a genus of small moths of the snout moth family ( Pyralidae ) .
Yunganglong is an extinct genus of basal hadrosauroid dinosaur known from the early Late Cretaceous lower Zhumapu Formation of Zuoyun County , Shanxi Province of northeastern China .
Panax notoginseng is a species of the genus Panax , and it is most commonly referred to in English as notoginseng .
Harpalus anxius is a species of phytophagous and xerophilous ground beetle that is native to Palearctic ( including Europe ) and the Near East .
Kurixalus verrucosus ( Boulenger 's bushfrog , small rough - armed tree frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family found in Myanmar , Thailand , China , and Vietnam .
The Lophiocarpaceae are a family of flowering plants comprising mostly succulent subshrubs and herbaceous species native to tropical to southern sub - Saharan Africa to western India .
Argyrotaenia pinatubana , the pine tube moth , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
It contains the single species Hypasura hoenei , which is found in China ( Hunan ) .
Coreopsis leavenworthii ( Leavenworth 's Tickseed ) is an annual or short lived perennail plant species in the sunflower family .
Lepidorrhachis is a monotypic genus of flowering plant in the palm family restricted to Lord Howe Island .
Purpura persica , common name : the Persian purpura , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Betta pulchra is a species of gourami endemid that is found in Johor , Malaysia .
Cerithium echinatum is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cerithiidae .
Squalius torgalensis is a species of freshwater fish in the family Cyprinidae , growing to 12 cm ( 4.7 in ) SL .
Streptococcus orisratti is a species of oral Streptococcus bacteria first isolated from Sprague--
Dolicholagus longirostris , the Longsnout blacksmelt , is a species of deep - sea smelt found circumglobally in deep waters of the tropics and sub - tropics .
Persea borbonia is a species of plant in the Lauraceae family , with several common names including redbay , tisswood , scrubbay , shorebay , and swampbay .
The Eucharitidae are a family of parasitic wasps known as eucharitid wasps .
Trillium chloropetalum is a California species of spring - flowering perennial plants .
Sphodromantis aurea is a species of praying mantis found in Liberia and Ghana .
Astragalus anserinus , also called the Goose Creek milkvetch , is a member of the genus Astragalus that is listed as a candidate species under the Endangered Species Act .
Phantomosaurus is an extinct genus of Ichthyosaur , which existed during the late Anisian period .
Thescelosauridae is a clade or family of small ornithischians which have previously been generally allied to hypsilophodontids .
Melisomimas metallica is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Melisomimas .
Mesotheriidae ( `` Middle Beasts '' ) is an extinct family of notoungulate mammals known from the Eocene through the Pleistocene of South America .
Royoporus badius , commonly known as the black - footed polypore or black - leg , is a species of fungus in the family Polyporaceae .
Machlotica chrysodeta is a species of sedge moths in the genus Machlotica .
Solanum chilliasense is a species of nightshade that is endemic to Ecuador .
Chthamalus stellatus , common name Poli 's stellate barnacle , is a species of acorn barnacle common on rocky shores in South West England , Ireland , and Southern Europe .
Fritillaria drenovskii is a rare European species of plants in the lily family , native to the Thrace region of northeastern Greece , as well as Blagoevgrad Province in southwestern Bulgaria .
Myxillina is a suborder of poecilosclerid sponges .
Stagmomantis californica , common name California mantis , is a species of praying mantis in the genus Stagmomantis native to the Western United States .
Gobiobotia is a genus of cyprinid fish that is found in eastern Asia .
Slender salamander is the name often given to Plethodontid ( lungless ) salamanders of the genus Batrachoseps .
The red - tailed pipe snake , red cylinder snake , or common pipe snake , Cylindrophis ruffus is a snake species found in Southeast Asia .
Aspitates ochrearia , the yellow belle , is a species of moth in the Geometridae family .
Acridoxena is the only genus in the subfamily Acridoxeninae .
The genus , Archaeoindris , translates to `` ancient indri - like lemur '' , even though it probably became extinct recently , around 350 BC . Archaeoindris was first described by Herbert F. Standing in 1909 based on subfossil fragmentary jaws , although Charles Lamberton later discovered a complete skull .
Inosaurus is the name given to a dubious genus of dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous .
Lepromoris gibba is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Lepromoris .
Musa velutina , the hairy banana or pink banana , is a species of seeded banana .
Chaetoderma elegans is a species of glisten worm , a kind of shell - less , worm - like mollusk in the family Chaetodermidae .
It contains only one species , Ogmocoma pharmacista , which is found on Rodriguez Island in Mauritius .
Euvola papyracea , or the paper scallop , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Pectinidae .
Polistes biglumis is a species of social wasp within Polistes , the most common genus of paper wasp .
Pyrus pyrifolia is a species of pear tree native to East Asia .
Pycnopsis brachyptera is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pycnopsis .
Hydrophyllum capitatum , is a species of waterleaf known by the common name ballhead waterleaf .
Tachypleus is a genus of southeast and east Asian horseshoe crabs in the family Limulidae .
Pseudosynanceia melanostigma , the Blackfin stonefish , is a species of stonefish native to the western Indian Ocean where it occurs in areas with muddy bottoms .
Protecovasaurus is a genus of archosaurian reptile from the Late Triassic of the southwestern United States .
The Hydroptilidae are a large family of caddisflies ( Trichoptera ) with a worldwide distribution .
Syrphus torvus is a common species of hoverfly found in Europe , Asia and North America .
Oncopsis flavicollis is a species of leafhoppers belonging to the family Cicadellidae subfamily Macropsinae .
It consists of only one species , Paraterpna harrisoni , which is found in Australia ( New South Wales ) .
Pueraria montana is a species of plant in the botanical family Fabaceae .
The Indian scops owl ( Otus bakkamoena ) is a resident species of owl found in the southern regions of Asia from eastern Arabia through the Indian Subcontinent , except the far north , east across much of Southeast Asia to Indonesia .
Dorstenia hirta is an herbaceous species of the plant family Moraceae which is native to eastern Brazil .
Gnetum africanum ( eru or African Jointfir ) is a vine gymnosperm species found natively throughout tropical Africa .
Cloeon dipterum is a species of mayfly with a Holarctic distribution .
Stylinodon is an extinct genus of taeniodont mammal , and is the best known , and last genus of taeniodonts , lived some 45 million years ago during middle Eocene in North America .
Hadrosteidae is a family of arthrodire placoderms from the Late Devonian .
Erigeron decumbens is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Willamette fleabane .
Guyotemaimetsha is an extinct genus of wasp which existed in France during the Cretaceous period .
Gmelina fasciculiflora , known as the northern white beech is a species of trees endemic in the Queensland tropical rain forests , Australia , of the mint ( Lamiaceae ) plant family .
Glyptothorax kudremukhensis is a species of catfish in family Sisoridae and was described by K.C. Gopi in 2007 .
Vernonia blodgettii ( Florida ironweed , Blodgett 's ironweed ) is a species of perennial plant from Asteraceae family that is native to Florida and the Bahamas .
Gaillardia pulchella ( firewheel , Indian blanket , Indian blanketflower , Indian paintbrush , or sundance ) , is a North American species of short - lived perennial or annual flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Dymasia is a monotypic genus of butterflies from southern USA to Central America in the family Nymphalidae that contains the species Tiny Checkerspot or Dyman Checkerspot ( Dymasia dymas ) .
Chathamiidae is a family of case making caddisflies more commonly known as the marine caddisflies .
Jamoytius kerwoodi was a species of primitive , eel - like jawless fish that lived in the Silurian period .
Calathea loeseneri is a species of plant belonging to the Marantaceae family .
It contains only one known species , Prasium majus , first described for modern science in 1753 .
Holbrookia maculata , commonly known as the lesser earless lizard , is a species of phrynosomatid lizard endemic to the southwestern and central United States and northern Mexico .
It contains only one species , the Spruce Needleminer Moth ( Taniva albolineana ) .
Ploima is an order of rotifers , microscopic invertebrates found in marine and freshwater habitats .
Silvabestius is an extinct genus of marsupial dating to the Early Miocene .
Rhododendron indicum is an Azalea Rhododendron species native to Japan ( S & W Honshu , Shikoku , Kyushu , Yakushima ) .
Magnolia campbellii , Campbell 's magnolia , is a species of Magnolia that grows in sheltered valleys in the Himalaya from eastern Nepal , Sikkim and Assam , India , east to southwestern China ( southern Xizang , Yunnan , southern Sichuan ) and south to northern Myanmar .
Trochulus hispidus , previously known as Trichia hispida , common name , the `` hairy snail '' , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Russula illota is an inedible species of mushroom in the genus Russula .
Winika is a monotypic genus of epiphytic orchids that is endemic to New Zealand .
Margarites salmoneus , common name the salmon margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Margaritidae .
Neomegamphopidae is a family of amphipods , comprising the two genera Maragopsis and Neomegamphopus .
Inocybe lacera ( commonly known as the torn tibrecap ) is a poisonous species of mushroom in the genus Inocybe .
Pseudobagrus brevianalis is a species of bagrid catfish endemic to Taiwan .
Yongjinglong is an extinct genus of herbivorous derived titanosaur sauropod dinosaur known from the Early Cretaceous of Lanzhou - Minhe Basin of Gansu Province , China .
Necrolemur ( `` dead lemur '' ) is an extinct genus of primate .
The Lomariopsidaceae is a family of ferns with a largely tropical distribution .
Kalmia microphylla , known as alpine laurel , bog laurel , swamp - laurel , western bog - laurel or western laurel , is a species of Kalmia belonging to the Ericaceae family .
Gaura neomexicana is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name New Mexico beeblossom .
Abelmoschus is a genus of about fifteen species of flowering plants in the mallow family , Malvaceae , native to tropical Africa , Asia and northern Australia .
Botucaraitherium is an extinct genus of prozostrodontian cynodont from the Late Triassic of Brazil .
Lasiognathus waltoni is a species of wolftrap angler known from the eastern central Pacific Ocean .
Melicope mucronulata is a species of plant in the citrus family , Rutaceae .
Emuellidae are a small family of trilobites , a group of extinct marine arthropods , that lived during the late Lower Cambrian ( late Botomian ) of the East Gondwana supercontinent , in what are today South - Australia and Antarctica .
Liomesaspis is an extinct genus of xiphosuran , related to the modern horseshoe crab .
Archboldomys , the shrew - mice , are a genus of rodents in the family Muridae .
Geosmithia putterillii is a species of fungi of the genus Geosmithia , which was named by Australian mycologist John Pitt in 1979 , is widely distributed and contains 10 species .
Rana pueyoi is an extinct species of large frog from Early Miocene of Spain .
Aizoaceae or Ficoidaceae ( the fig - marigold family or ice plant family ) is a family of dicotyledonous flowering plants containing 135 genera and about 1900 species .
Graphis alboscripta commonly known as White Script Lichen is a species of epiphytic lichen that is endemic to the west coast of Scotland .
Erigeron sparsifolius is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Bracted Utah fleabane ..
The Isostictidae are a small family of medium - sized to large damselflies restricted to Australia , New Caledonia , and New Guinea .
Vitula edmandsii , the American wax moth , dried - fruit moth or dried fruit moth , is a species of snout moth in the genus Vitula .
Aspidotis carlotta - halliae is a species of perennial fern known by the common names tufted lacefern and Carlotta Hall 's lace fern .
Acer grandidentatum ( bigtooth maple ) is a species of maple native to interior western North America , occurring in scattered populations from western Montana in the United States south to Coahuila in northern Mexico .
Neritilia is a genus of freshwater snails which live near the sea coast in submarine caves .
Heterorrhina elegans is a species of Scarab beetle found in India and Sri Lanka that belongs to the flower chafer subfamily .
Malapterurus minjiriya is a species of electric catfish native to Burkina Faso , Ethiopia , Ghana , Mali , Nigeria and Togo .
†Carelia paradoxa was a species of small , air - breathing , land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Amastridae and superfamily Cochlicopoidea .
Hymenocallis pumila is a species of spider lily native to the States of Jalisco and Colima in western Mexico .
Castianeira is a genus of spiders present in Eurasia , Africa , and the Americas .
The Hesperentomidae are a family of hexapods in the order Protura .
Chamaecyparis formosensis ( Formosan cypress , Taiwan cypress ; Chinese : 紅檜/红桧 hong kuai ) is a species of Chamaecyparis , endemic to Taiwan , where it grows in the central mountains at moderate to high altitudes of 1000 - -2900 m. It is threatened by habitat loss and over - cutting for its valuable timber .
Agropyron cristatum ( crested wheat grass , crested wheatgrass , fairway crested wheat grass ) is a species in the Poaceae family .
The Costa Rican pygmy owl ( Glaucidium costaricanum ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Carabus rustemi is a species of black coloured ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Kazakhstan .
Erliansaurus is a genus of therizinosauroid theropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous of China .
Massyla corrugata , common name the corrugated nutmeg , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cancellariidae , the nutmeg snails .
Collinsia parryi is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name Parry 's blue eyed Mary .
Laricobius osakensis is a species of Derodontid beetle native to Japan .
Morchella meiliensis is a species of fungus in the Morchellaceae family native to China .
Helianthella quinquenervis , fivenerve helianthella , is a North American plant species in the sunflower family .
Biceratopsidae is an extinct family of redlichiid trilobites , with species of small to average size .
Lessingia hololeuca is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name woollyhead lessingia .
Urostylididae is a family of true bugs and is considered a basal or `` primitive '' family within the stink - bug lineage .
Apatornis is a genus of prehistoric birds endemic to North America during the late Cretaceous .
Trioza is a sap - sucking bug genus in the family Triozidae .
Metachanda astrapias is a species of moth in the family Oecophoridae .
Patella vulgata , common name the common limpet or common European limpet is an edible species of sea snail with gills , a typical true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Patellidae .
Mycoplasma capricolum is a species of Mycoplasma bacteria .
Hasora , the awls , are a genus of skipper butterflies . The contained species are found in the Indomalayan ecozone and the Australasian ecozone
Acanthomyrmex concavus is a species of ant that belongs to the Acanthomyrmex genus .
Verminephrobacter is a genus of Gram negative bacteria that colonize the nephridia of earthworms within the family Lumbricidae .
Desmatophoca is an extinct genus of pinniped .
Pseudocarpidium is a genus of flowering plants in the family Lamiaceae first described in 1906 .
Zostera capensis is a species of eelgrass growing along the shores of the Atlantic and Indian Oceans in Kenya , Tanzania , Mozambique , Madagascar , Angola and the Cape Provinces and KwaZulu - Natal in South Africa .
Rhynchopsitta phillipsi is an extinct species of thick - billed parrot .
Carallia euryoides is a species of plant in the Rhizophoraceae family that is endemic to Peninsular Malaysia .
Monopylocystis visvesvarai is a species of amoebae , placed in the monotypic genus Monopylocystis , and belonging to the group Heterolobosea .
Tulipa saxatilis is a Greek and Turkish species of plants in the genus of tulips in the ( lily family ) .
Minuartia yukonensis , the Yukon sandwort or Yukon stitchwort , is a plant species native to Yukon and Northwest Territories of Canada , as well as Alaska , and The Russian Far East .
Lutodrilus multivesiculatus is a species of invertebrate in the Lutodrilidae family .
Alicia sansibarensis ( commonly known tuberculate night anemone ) is a sea anemone species in the genus Alicia which can be found in Indo - Pacific Ocean .
Taunayia bifasciata is a species of three - barbeled catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Upper Paraíba do Sul and Tietê River basins .
Nardia is a genus of liverwort in the family Solenostomataceae .
The Japanese wagtail ( Motacilla grandis ) is a species of bird in the pipit and wagtail family Motacillidae .
Cattleya tigrina is a bifoliate species of Cattleya orchid .
Didymictis is an extinct genus of carnivorous mammals known from the late Paleocene and early Eocene ( Tiffanian - Gardnerbuttean NALMA ) of North America .
Astrantia carniolica , the carnic masterwort or red masterwort , is a species of flowering plant in the family Apiaceae .
The Serra Cantareira saddleback toad , Brachycephalus nodoterga , is a species of frog in the Brachycephalidae family .
Cherax snowden is a species of crayfish from West Papua in Indonesia ( Oinsok River Drainage , Sawiat District , Chendravasikh and Kepala Burung Peninsulas ) .
Selaginella cinerascens is a species of spikemoss known by the common names mesa spikemoss , gray spikemoss , and ashy spikemoss .
Amblygobius semicinctus , the Halfbarred goby , is a species of goby from Gobiidae family .
Mongolocampe zhaoningi is a species of Hymenoptera from the Tetracampidae family .
Dichograptus ( meaning two - branched writing or double - line marks ) is an extinct genus of graptolite from the Ordovician .
Neoscorpis lithophilus , the Stone - bream , is a species of sea chub native to the Indian Ocean coast of Africa where it can be found along rocky coasts from Mozambique to South Africa .
Disa cornuta is a species of orchid found from Zimbabwe to South Africa .
Herwigia kreffti , Krefft 's smooth - head , is a species of bathylaconid fish found at depths of 1,000 to 3,200 metres ( 3,300 to 10,500 ft ) in the oceans .
Allium glomeratum is a Central Asian species of onion native to Xinjiang , Kyrgyzstan , Tajikistan , and Kazakhstan .
Sandalodus is an extinct genus of cartilaginous fish from the Carboniferous period .
Mentzelia affinis is a species of flowering plants in the family Loasaceae known by the common name yellowcomet .
Coladenia agni is a species of spread - winged skipper butterflies .
Dorstenia aristeguietae is a species of herb in the plant family Moraceae which is native to Venezuela .
Helvella elastica , commonly known as the flexible Helvella , or the elastic saddle , is a species of fungi in the Helvellaceae family , Pezizales order .
Trachycarpus oreophilus ( also known as Thai mountain fan palm ) is a species in the genus Trachycarpus .
Guzmania nicaraguensis is a species in the genus Guzmania .
Cynanchum utahense is a species of flowering plant in the Cynanchum genus of the dogbane family , known by the common names Utah swallow - wort and Utah vine milkweed .
Elasmotena insulana is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Elasmotena .
Nodipecten nodosus , or the lion 's paw scallop , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Pectinidae .
The Dehradun stream frog , Amolops chakrataensis , is a species of frog found in India .
The Ceylon caecilian or common yellow - banded caecilian , Ichthyophis glutinosus ( sometimes mistakenly spelled Ichthyophis gluinosus ) is a species of caecilian in the family Ichthyophiidae endemic to Sri Lanka .
Polypodium calirhiza is a species of fern in the polypody family .
Polygonum shastense is a species of flowering plant in the knotweed family known by the common name Shasta knotweed .
Harponixus pubescens is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Harponixus .
The Bursidae , common name `` frog snails '' or `` frog shells '' , are a rather small taxonomic family of large sea snails , marine gastropod predatory snails in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Gilia inconspicua is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name shy gilia .
The Sinoceratidae is a family of orthoceroids , named for the genus Sinoceras , both by Shimizu and Obata 1935 , and equivalent to the Michelinoceratinae Flower , 1945 .
Teuscheria is a genus of orchids native to southern Mexico , Central America and northern South America .
Callionymus planus is a species of dragonet native to the shallow Pacific waters off of southern Japan .
Podocarpus nivalis ( mountain or snow totara ) is a species of conifer in the Podocarpaceae family .
Cereus hildmannianus is a species of cactus from southern South America .
Globularia cordifolia ( heart - leaved globe daisy ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Planataginaceae , native to the mountains of central and southern Europe , and western Turkey .
Boreopelta is an extinct genus of rhytidosteid temnospondyl from the early Triassic period ( Olenekian stage ) of Yakutsk Region , central Siberia , Russia .
Sydonia apomecynoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Sydonia .
Parnassia caroliniana is a species of flowering plant in the Celastraceae known by the common name Carolina grass of Parnassus .
Chrysolina viridana is a species of beetle from a Chrysomelidae family .
Choeradodis columbica , common name Columbian shield mantis , is a species of praying mantis native to Colombia .
Parepectasoides boliviana is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parepectasoides .
Sagittaria natans is a species of flowering plant in the water plantain family .
Diuris sulphurea ( Tiger Orchid or Hornet Orchid ) is a species of orchid which is endemic to Australia .
Ptychagnostus atavus is a species of agnostid trilobite .
The scarlet marsh hawk , ( Aethriamanta brevipennis ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Lytechinus is a genus of sea urchin .
Heliconius heurippa is a butterfly of the genus Heliconius that is believed by some scientists to be a separate species from -- but a hybrid of -- the species Heliconius cydno and Heliconius melpomene , making H. heurippa an example of hybrid speciation .
It contains only one species , Spinitibia hodgesi , which is found in North America , where it has been recorded from Alabama , Arkansas , Florida , Georgia , Indiana , Kansas , Louisiana , Mississippi , Oklahoma , South Carolina , Tennessee and Virginia .
Anax speratus , the orange emperor , is a species of dragonfly in the family Aeshnidae .
The genus Fagopyrum is in the flowering plant family Polygonaceae .
Sineoamphisbaena is an extinct genus of squamate of uncertain phylogenetic placement .
Brassia macrostachya is a species of orchid native to Venezuela and Guyana .
Pedopenna ( meaning `` foot feather '' ) is a genus of small , feathered , maniraptoran dinosaur from the Daohugou Beds in China .
It contains only one species , Barca bicolor , which is found in Tibet and Yunnan .
Lewisia nevadensis is a species of flowering plant in the purslane family known by the common name Nevada lewisia .
Ontonychophora is an extinct order of onychophoran consisting of organisms with simple lobobods that lack terminal feet .
Luteimonas lutimaris is a species of yellow - pigmented , Gram - negative , strictly aerobic bacterium .
Agaritha iolaia is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Agaritha .
Chaptalia albicans , the white sunbonnet , is a plant species native to Mexico , Central America and the West Indies .
Penicillium diversum is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which produces austinol , isoaustin and diversonol .
Morchella anatolica is a species of ascomycete fungus in the family Morchellaceae that was described as new to science in 2010 .
The Afghan leopard gecko ( Eublepharis macularius afghanicus ) is one of the five subspecies of the common leopard gecko , a small to midsized lizard belonging to the family Gekkonidae .
The family Echimyidae contains the Neotropical spiny rats and their fossil relatives .
Opsariichthys pachycephalus is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Opsariichthys endemic to Taiwan .
The Grubbiaceae are a family of flowering plants endemic to the Cape floristic region of South Africa .
Astronidium ligulatum is a species of plant in the Melastomataceae family endemic to French Polynesia .
Acmaeodera is a genus of beetles in the family Buprestidae , a group of metallic wood - boring beetles favored by insect collectors .
Arsirrhyncha fibriculata is a moth in the Xyloryctidae family , and the only species in the genus Arsirrhyncha .
Habronattus coecatus is a species of jumping spiders from a Salticidae family , that can be found in Mexico , the United States , and Bermuda .
Streptococcus agalactiae is the species designation for streptococci belonging to group B of the Lancefield classification .
The Sri Lanka sabretail , ( Megalogomphus ceylonicus ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Gomphidae .
Hoplerythrinus is a genus of trahiras found in Central and South America .
Thelesperma is a genus of North American and South American plants in the cosmos tribe within the sunflower family .
Adiantum gertrudis is a threatened species of ferns in the Vittarioideae subfamily of the Pteridaceae that occurs in central South America .
Eucharis amazonica is a species of flowering plant in the family Amaryllidaceae , native to Peru .
Ugamia is a genus of flowering plants in the chamomile tribe within the sunflower family .
Lactarius rubrilacteus is a species of mushroom of the genus Lactarius .
Mentzelia goodrichii is a rare species of flowering plant in the family Loasaceae known by the common name Goodrich 's blazingstar .
Megasecoptera is a paleozoic insect order .
Suillus nueschii is a rare species of mushroom in the genus Suillus .
Nanyangosaurus is a genus of herbivorous ornithischian dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous .
Cochleoceps is a genus of clingfishes endemic to the waters around Australia .
Trichostema simulatum is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Siskiyou bluecurls .
Recilia trispinosus is a species of bug from the Cicadellidae family that is endemic to India .
Ctenocheirodon pristis is a species of characin native to South America that can grow up to 3.4 cm long ( only 3.3 for males ) .
The Lustrous Black Catasetum ( Catasetum atratum ) is a species of orchid found in Brazil .
Froelichia ( snakecotton ) is a genus of plant in family Amaranthaceae .
Nymphargus garciae is a species of frog in the Centrolenidae family , formerly placed in Cochranella .
Xanthocercis zambesiaca ( Mashatu tree or Nyala tree ) is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family .
The Venezuelan red howler ( Alouatta seniculus ) is a South American species of howler monkey , a type of New World monkey , found in the western Amazon Basin in Venezuela , Colombia , Ecuador , Peru and Brazil .
Promachoteuthis sloani is a species of squid from the northern Atlantic Ocean .
Remya kauaiensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family , known by the common name of Kauai remya .
Phacelia orogenes is an uncommon species of phacelia known by the common name mountain phacelia .
Phormium is a genus of two plant species in the Xanthorrhoeaceae family .
Leuconopsis obsoleta is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Ellobiidae .
Tabernaemontana palustris is a tropical flowering plant species in the family Apocynaceae .
Lissodiadema is the only genus in the family Lissodiadematidae .
Gracilidris is a genus of dolichoderine ants with nocturnal behaviour ; thought to have gone extinct 15 - 20 million years ago , they have been found in Paraguay , Brazil , and Argentina and were described in 2006 .
Mimopolyocha obscurella is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Mimopolyocha .
Symphyotrichum lentum ( formerly Aster lentus ) is a species of aster known by the common name Suisun Marsh aster .
Cleyera is a plant genus consisting of 18 species of tender , extremely evergreen shrubs to small trees , mostly native to Mexico and Central America , and one from Eastern Asia .
Plectranthias sheni is a species of marine fish belonging to the family Serranidae .
Microcleididae is an extinct family of basal plesiosauroid plesiosaurs from the Early Jurassic ( middle Sinemurian to late Toarcian stages ) of France , Germany , Portugal and the United Kingdom .
Artocarpus is a genus of approximately 60 trees and shrubs of Southeast Asian and Pacific origin , belonging to the mulberry family , Moraceae .
Pseudobutyrivibrio xylanivorans is a species of butyrate - producing bacteria from the rumen .
Chorthippus is a large genus of acridid grasshoppers with around 190 described species .
Hypancistrus contradens is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela where it occurs in the Orinoco River .
Gossypium thurberi , also known as Arizona wild cotton , Thurber 's cotton , or Desert Cotton , is a wild species of cotton .
Caiman venezuelensis is an extinct species of caiman that lived in South America during the Pleistocene .
Lipariscus nanus , the pygmy snailfish , is a species of snailfish native to the northern Pacific Ocean where it occurs in deep waters down to 910 metres ( 2,990 ft ) .
Eubostrychoceras is a genus of helically wound , corkscew form , heteromorph ammonite which lived during the Upper Cretaceous ( M Turonian - Campanian ) .
The Kawaihae hibiscadelphus ( Hibiscadelphus bombycinus ) was a species of flowering plant in the Malvaceae family .
Manacus is a genus of passerine birds in the manakin family which are found in the forests of tropical mainland Central and South America , and on Trinidad and Tobago .
Lutzomyia adiketis is an extinct species of sandfly in the moth fly subfamily Phlebotominae .
Hypleurochilus aequipinnis , the Oyster blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Atlantic ocean .
†Archinacellidae is an extinct family of paleozoic molluscs of uncertain position ( Gastropoda or Monoplacophora ) .
Physoschistura chulabhornae is a species of loach , a freshwater fish in the family Nemacheilidae .
Pittosporum eriocarpum is a plant species in the Pittosporaceae family endemic to India .
Philoponella vicina is a species of spider that does not use venom ( characteristic of Uloboridae ) , but instead wraps its prey in hundreds of metres of spider silk to crush it to death .
Oeceoclades latifolia is a terrestrial orchid species in the genus Oeceoclades that is endemic to São Tomé Island .
Vaccinium virgatum ( commonly known as rabbit - eye blueberry , smallflower blueberry or southern black blueberry ) is a species of blueberry native to the Southeastern United States , from North Carolina south to Florida and west to Texas .
Saloca diceros is a species of spider that can be found in such European countries as Austria , Belgium , Czech Republic , Denmark , France , Germany , Great Britain , Hungary , Ireland , Italy , Poland , Romania , Slovakia , Slovenia , Spain , Sweden , Switzerland , and the Netherlands .
Indosuchus is a genus of abelisaurid dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous Period ( 70 to 66 million years ago -- the Maastrichtian ) , a theropod related to Abelisaurus .
Psychotria grandiflora ( largeflower wild coffee , large - flowered balsamo , kopiko ) is a species of plant in the Rubiaceae family endemic to the island of Kauai in the Hawaiian Islands .
Livistona decora is a species of palm endemic to the sclerophyll woodlands of Queensland , Australia .
Celosia trigyna is a plant species commonly known as woolflower for its curious flowers .
Calliostoma occidentale , common name the boreal topsnail , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Rhaphidophora is a genus in the family Araceae , occurring from tropical Africa eastwards through Malesia and Australasia to the Western Pacific .
Gnaphosa porrecta is a ground spider species found in Norway .
Equisetum telmateia ( great horsetail or northern giant horsetail ) is a species of Equisetum ( horsetail ) with an unusual distribution , with one subspecies native to Europe , western Asia and northwest Africa , and a second subspecies native to western North America .
Penicillium flavisclerotiatum is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from soil of the Stellenbosch mountain in Fynbos in South Africa .
Tremacebus harringtoni is an extinct species of New World monkey from the Miocene .
Hechtia mooreana is a species in the genus Hechtia , endemic to Mexico .
Oxalis priceae , the tufted yellow woodsorrel , is a species of flowering plant in the woodsorrel family .
Conus sennottorum , common name Sennett 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Xiaosaurus ( `` dawn lizard '' , /ʃaʊˈsɔrəs/ ) , is a genus of small herbivorous dinosaur from the middle Jurassic , approximately 169 to 163 mya .
Petroscirtes xestus , the xestus sabretooth blenny , xestus fangblenny , or the bearded sabretooth blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian ocean .
It consists of only one species , Cleptophasia scissa , which is found in Brazil , French Guiana and Venezuela .
Microchrysa flavicornis , the green gem , is a European species of soldier fly .
Puncturella pseudanaloga is a minute species of deepwater keyhole limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc or micromollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
Phylloceratidae is the predominant family of the Phylloceratina with some 15 or more genera found in rocks ranging from the Lower Jurassic to the Upper Cretaceous .
Sciurotamias is a genus of rodent in the family Sciuridae , found in China .
Dodecocerus poirieri is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Dodecocerus .
Amaurospiza is a genus of birds .
Mesoleptus hibernica is a species of parasitic wasp that was discovered by Dr. Chris Williams , in County Mayo , when he was waiting for marsh flies to hatch in jam jars on his desk .
Lagis koreni , commonly known as the trumpet worm , is a species of marine polychaete worm found in European waters .
Cleomella obtusifolia is a species of flowering plant in the cleome family known by the common name Mojave stinkweed .
Istiblennius pox , the scarface rockskipper , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian ocean .
It contains only one known species , Cylindropsis parvifolia , native to central Africa ( Nigeria , Cabinda , Gabon , Central African Republic , Republic of Congo , Democratic Republic of the Congo ) .
Tephrosia spinosa is a flowering plant species in the genus Tephrosia native from India , Sri Lanka , Malaysia and Indonesia .
Parenchelyurus hyena is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Pacific ocean , around Papua New Guinea .
Anemone virginiana is an upright growing herbaceous plant species in the genus Anemone and family Ranunculaceae .
Levinseniella deblocki , new species ( Trematoda : Digenea : Microphallidae ) from salt marshes along the eastern Gulf of Mexico with notes on its functional morphology and life history ( abstract only ) .
Neoconis is a genus of lacewing .
Mycobacterium shimoidei is a slowly growing non - pigmented species of mycobacteria .
