Allium rhizomatum is a species of plant native to southern Arizona ( Cochise and Santa Cruz Counties ) , southern New Mexico ( Catron , Grant , Hidalgo , Socorro , Sierra and Eddy Counties ) and western Texas ( Brewster and Jeff Davis Counties ) in the United States , and Chihuahua in Mexico .
Protomicrocotylidae is a family of monogenean parasites in the order Mazocraeidea .
Melicope obovata ( also called Makawao melicope or obovate melicope ) was a species of plant in the Rutaceae family .
The Vipos tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys viperinus ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenomyidae .
Neotricula is a genus freshwater snails which have a gill and an operculum , gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Pomatiopsidae .
Cicindela oregona , also called the Western Tiger Beetle , is a species of ground beetles native to North America .
Dendrobium yeageri ( Yeager 's Dendrobium ) is a species of the family Orchidaceae endemic to the Philippines named in honor of Dr. Clark Harvey Yeager .
Quasipaa delacouri ( common names : Doi Chang Asian frog , Tonkin Asian frog ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
The West Mexican chachalaca ( Ortalis poliocephala ) is a species of bird in the Cracidae family .
Hadropithecus is a medium - sized , extinct genus of lemur , or strepsirrhine primate , from Madagascar that includes a single species , Hadropithecus stenognathus .
Masdevallia agaster is a species of epiphytic orchid endemic to southern Ecuador .
Conasprella arcuata , common name the arched cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Myomyscus is a genus of rodent .
Pamphorichthys is a genus of poeciliids native to the Amazon , Paraguay , São Francisco and Itapicuru basins in South America .
Pityphyllum is a genus of orchids comprising 7 known species native to Venezuela , Bolivia , Peru , Ecuador and Colombia .
Ebinania is a genus of fatheads .
Eryngium armatum is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name coastal eryngo .
Potentilla morefieldii is a species of cinquefoil known by the common name Morefield 's cinquefoil .
Peltosaurus is an extinct genus of anguid lizard from North America that lived from the Eocene to the Oligocene .
Gomphus clavatus , commonly known pig 's ears or violet chanterelle , as is an edible species of fungus in the genus Gomphus , family Gomphaceae native to Eurasia and North America .
Muraenolepis is a genus of eel cods .
Lavandula dentata is a species of flowering plant in the Lamiaceae family , native to the Mediterranean , the Atlantic islands and the Arabian peninsula .
Littoraria angulifera or the mangrove periwinkle is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Littorinidae , the winkles .
Teucrium chamaedrys , the wall germander , is a species of ornamental plant native to Mediterranean region of Europe and North Africa , and to the Middle East as far east as Iran .
Cnidium is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , native to Eurasia , Africa and North America .
Strioderes peruanus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Strioderes .
Erigeron cervinus is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names Siskiyou fleabane and Siskiyou fleabane daisy .
Sweepers are small , tropical marine ( occasionally brackish ) perciform fish of the family Pempheridae .
Jatropha cathartica is a species of flowering plant in the spurge family , Euphorbiaceae , that is native to Texas in the United States and Coahuila , Nuevo León and Tamaulipas in northeastern Mexico .
Papuadessus pakdjoko is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Papuadessus .
Prosoproctus pataecus is a species of velvetfish native to the South China Sea where it occurs at depths of from 69 to 82 metres ( 226 to 269 ft ) .
Trigoniulus corallinus , sometimes called the rusty millipede , is a species of millipede native to the area around Thailand and Myanmar .
Dipterocarpus elongatus is a species of tree in the family Dipterocarpaceae found in Indonesia ( Kalimantan and Sumatra ) , Malaysia ( peninsular Malaysia , Sarawak ) and Singapore .
Henosepilachna guttatopustulata , the Large Leaf - eating Ladybird , is a species of ladybird endemic to parts of Australasia , specifically New South Wales , Queensland , the Bismarck Archipelago , New Guinea , New Hebrides and Solomon Islands .
Parecyroschema cristipenne is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parecyroschema .
Corythornis is a genus of small insectivorous African water kingfishers .
Palmoliparis beckeri , the gloved snailfish , is a species of snailfish found around the northern Kuril Islands in the northwestern Pacific Ocean .
Turnera ulmifolia , the ramgoat dashalong or yellow alder , is a species of plant of family Passifloraceae , native to Mexico and the West Indies .
The Northern Colletes ( Colletes floralis ) is a species of bee within the genus Colletes .
Liolaemus constanzae , commonly known as Constanza 's tree iguana , is a species of iguanid lizard endemic to South America .
Aplysia morio , the Atlantic black sea hare or sooty sea hare , is a species of sea slug , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Aplysiidae , the sea hares .
Platanthera chlorantha , commonly known as greater butterfly - orchid , is a species of orchid in the genus Platanthera .
Proborhyaenidae is an extinct family of metatherian mammals of the order Sparassodonta , which lived in South America from the Eocene ( Casamayoran ) until the Oligocene ( Deseadan ) .
Osteopeltidae is a taxonomic family of small , deep water sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Vetigastropoda ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Microdesmus is a genus of wormfishes native to the Atlantic Ocean and the eastern Pacific Ocean .
Laugiidae is an extinct family of prehistoric sarcopterygian fishes which lived during the Triassic and Jurassic period .
Erethistoides montana is a species of South Asian river catfish endemic to India where it can be found in Tripura , Assam and Darjeeling .
Wolffia brasiliensis is a species of flowering plant known by the common name Brazilian watermeal .
Turritellidae , common name the `` tower shells '' or `` tower snails '' , is a taxonomic family of small to medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Sorbeoconcha .
Matisia exalata is a species of flowering plant in the Malvaceae sensu lato or Bombacaceae family .
Crocodylus anthropophagus is an extinct species of crocodile from Plio - Pleistocene from Tanzania .
Bacillus sonorensis is a species of bacteria with type strain L87 - 10 T (= NRRL B-23154 T ) .
Glossogobius flavipinnis is a species of goby endemic to Lake Towuti in Sulawesi , Indonesia .
Iphiothe criopsoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Iphiothe .
Nacella terroris is a southern , cold - water species of sea snail , a limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Nacellidae , the true limpets .
Setaria verticillata is a species of grass known by the common names hooked bristlegrass , rough bristle - grass and bristly foxtail .
Potentilla pseudosericea is a species of cinquefoil known by the common names silky cinquefoil and Mono cinquefoil .
Amblyeleotris periophthalma is a marine benthic species of goby native to reef environments of the Indo - West Pacific , Red Sea included .
Cassida saucia is a species of beetle in the leaf beetle family , that can be found in various Asian countries , including Armenia , Azerbaijan , Iran and Turkey .
Pseudobiceros bedfordi , ( common names Persian carpet flatworm and Bedford 's flatworm ) is a species of flatworm in the family Pseudocerotidae .
Bullina lineata , common name the red - lined bubble snail , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Bullinidae .
Hemidoras is a small genus of thorny catfishes native to the Amazon basin in South America .
Macrorhamphosodes is a genus of spikefishes native to the Indian and western Pacific Oceans .
Migidae is a family of spiders with about 90 species in 10 genera , known as tree trapdoor spiders .
Mioplosus is an extinct genus of Percid fish that lived from the early to middle Eocene .
Pseudonoseris is a genus of South American plants in the dandelion subfamily of the sunflower family .
Stachystemon is a plant genus in the family Picrodendraceae first described as a genus in 1845 .
Sorbus maderensis , a rowan , is a species of plant in the Rosaceae family .
Hamptonia is a genus of sponge known from the Middle Cambrian Burgess Shale and the Lower Ordovician Fezouata formation .
Watasenia scintillans , also known as the sparkling enope squid or firefly squid , is a species of squid in the family Enoploteuthidae .
Archeria hirtella is a species of shrub in the heath family ( Ericaceae ) .
Lilium ( members of which are true lilies ) is a genus of herbaceous flowering plants growing from bulbs , all with large prominent flowers .
Aspidotis californica is a species of fern known by the common name California lacefern .
Nordstromia japonica is a species of moth belonging to the subfamily Drepaninae .
The Langtang Larch ( Larix himalaica ) is a species of conifer in the genus Larix .
Erigeron robustior is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name White cushion fleabane or Willamette fleabane .
Hypsoblennius ionthas , the freckled blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Atlantic ocean .
Dendropsophus anceps ( common name : Estrella treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Chara vulgaris , the common stonewort , is a green alga species in the genus Chara .
Aulopus is a genus of flagfins native to the Atlantic Ocean and the Pacific Ocean .
Geitoneura minyas , commonly known as the western xenica is a species of butterfly from the Nymphalidae family , found in the south - west of Western Australia .
The Seaweed pipefishes , Syngnathus , is a genus of pipefishes in the family Syngnathidae .
Amyema benthamii , known in the Bardi language as nyilinyil , is a species of flowering plant , an epiphytic hemiparasitic plant of the family Loranthaceae native to northern Australia .
Laureliopsis is a genus of flowering plants with just one species , L. philippiana , known as Tepa , endemic to Chile and Argentina ( 35 to 45 ° S ) .
Blepharipoda occidentalis , the spiny sand crab or spiny mole crab , is a species of sand crab or mole crab which lives in the eastern Pacific Ocean , from Central California to Baja California .
Thamnochortus insignis is a species of grass - like restio of the family Restionaceae , endemic to Cape Province in South Africa .
Gelidiella calcicola is a rare seaweed species in the Rhodophyta , described for the first time in 1988 .
Lysapsus laevis is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in southwestern Guyana and adjacent northern Brazil .
Stephanolepis is a genus of bony fish in the family Monacanthidae , the filefishes .
